--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCalculatedColumn</a> smart constructor.
data CalculatedColumn
CalculatedColumn' :: Text -> Text -> Text -> CalculatedColumn

-- | Column name.
[$sel:columnName:CalculatedColumn'] :: CalculatedColumn -> Text

-- | A unique ID to identify a calculated column. During a dataset update,
--   if the column ID of a calculated column matches that of an existing
--   calculated column, Amazon QuickSight preserves the existing calculated
--   column.

--   calculated column. During a dataset update, if the column ID of a

--   Amazon QuickSight preserves the existing calculated column.

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ColumnLevelPermissionRule

-- | A rule defined to grant access on one or more restricted columns. Each
--   dataset can have multiple rules. To create a restricted column, you
--   add it to one or more rules. Each rule must contain at least one
--   column and at least one user or group. To be able to see a restricted
--   column, a user or group needs to be added to a rule for that column.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newColumnLevelPermissionRule</a> smart constructor.
data ColumnLevelPermissionRule
ColumnLevelPermissionRule' :: Maybe (NonEmpty Text) -> Maybe (NonEmpty Text) -> ColumnLevelPermissionRule

-- | An array of Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) for Amazon QuickSight users
--   or groups.
[$sel:principals:ColumnLevelPermissionRule'] :: ColumnLevelPermissionRule -> Maybe (NonEmpty Text)

-- | An array of column names.
[$sel:columnNames:ColumnLevelPermissionRule'] :: ColumnLevelPermissionRule -> Maybe (NonEmpty Text)

-- | Create a value of <a>ColumnLevelPermissionRule</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:principals:ColumnLevelPermissionRule'</a>,
--   <a>columnLevelPermissionRule_principals</a> - An array of Amazon
--   Resource Names (ARNs) for Amazon QuickSight users or groups.
--   
--   <a>$sel:columnNames:ColumnLevelPermissionRule'</a>,
--   <a>columnLevelPermissionRule_columnNames</a> - An array of column
--   names.
newColumnLevelPermissionRule :: ColumnLevelPermissionRule

-- | An array of Amazon Resource Names (ARNs) for Amazon QuickSight users
--   or groups.
columnLevelPermissionRule_principals :: Lens' ColumnLevelPermissionRule (Maybe (NonEmpty Text))

-- | An array of column names.
columnLevelPermissionRule_columnNames :: Lens' ColumnLevelPermissionRule (Maybe (NonEmpty Text))
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ColumnLevelPermissionRule.ColumnLevelPermissionRule
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ColumnLevelPermissionRule.ColumnLevelPermissionRule
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ColumnLevelPermissionRule.ColumnLevelPermissionRule

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSummary

-- | Dashboard summary.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDashboardSummary</a> smart constructor.
data DashboardSummary
DashboardSummary' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> DashboardSummary

-- | The last time that this dashboard was updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DashboardSummary'] :: DashboardSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:DashboardSummary'] :: DashboardSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that this dashboard was created.
[$sel:createdTime:DashboardSummary'] :: DashboardSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Dashboard ID.
[$sel:dashboardId:DashboardSummary'] :: DashboardSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | Published version number.
[$sel:publishedVersionNumber:DashboardSummary'] :: DashboardSummary -> Maybe Natural

-- | The last time that this dashboard was published.
[$sel:lastPublishedTime:DashboardSummary'] :: DashboardSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | A display name for the dashboard.
[$sel:name:DashboardSummary'] :: DashboardSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DashboardSummary</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DashboardSummary'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSummary_lastUpdatedTime</a> - The last time that this
--   dashboard was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:DashboardSummary'</a>, <a>dashboardSummary_arn</a> - The
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:DashboardSummary'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSummary_createdTime</a> - The time that this dashboard was
--   created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dashboardId:DashboardSummary'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSummary_dashboardId</a> - Dashboard ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:publishedVersionNumber:DashboardSummary'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSummary_publishedVersionNumber</a> - Published version
--   number.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastPublishedTime:DashboardSummary'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSummary_lastPublishedTime</a> - The last time that this
--   dashboard was published.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:DashboardSummary'</a>, <a>dashboardSummary_name</a> - A
--   display name for the dashboard.
newDashboardSummary :: DashboardSummary

-- | The last time that this dashboard was updated.
dashboardSummary_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' DashboardSummary (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
dashboardSummary_arn :: Lens' DashboardSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that this dashboard was created.
dashboardSummary_createdTime :: Lens' DashboardSummary (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Dashboard ID.
dashboardSummary_dashboardId :: Lens' DashboardSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | Published version number.
dashboardSummary_publishedVersionNumber :: Lens' DashboardSummary (Maybe Natural)

-- | The last time that this dashboard was published.
dashboardSummary_lastPublishedTime :: Lens' DashboardSummary (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | A display name for the dashboard.
dashboardSummary_name :: Lens' DashboardSummary (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSummary.DashboardSummary
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSummary.DashboardSummary
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSummary.DashboardSummary

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataColorPalette

-- | The theme colors that are used for data colors in charts. The colors
--   description is a hexadecimal color code that consists of six
--   alphanumerical characters, prefixed with <tt>#</tt>, for example
--   #37BFF5.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataColorPalette</a> smart constructor.
data DataColorPalette
DataColorPalette' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> DataColorPalette

-- | The minimum and maximum hexadecimal codes that describe a color
--   gradient.
[$sel:minMaxGradient:DataColorPalette'] :: DataColorPalette -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The hexadecimal code of a color that applies to charts where a lack of
--   data is highlighted.
[$sel:emptyFillColor:DataColorPalette'] :: DataColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The hexadecimal codes for the colors.
[$sel:colors:DataColorPalette'] :: DataColorPalette -> Maybe [Text]

-- | Create a value of <a>DataColorPalette</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:minMaxGradient:DataColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>dataColorPalette_minMaxGradient</a> - The minimum and maximum
--   hexadecimal codes that describe a color gradient.
--   
--   <a>$sel:emptyFillColor:DataColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>dataColorPalette_emptyFillColor</a> - The hexadecimal code of a
--   color that applies to charts where a lack of data is highlighted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:colors:DataColorPalette'</a>, <a>dataColorPalette_colors</a> -
--   The hexadecimal codes for the colors.
newDataColorPalette :: DataColorPalette

-- | The minimum and maximum hexadecimal codes that describe a color
--   gradient.
dataColorPalette_minMaxGradient :: Lens' DataColorPalette (Maybe [Text])

-- | The hexadecimal code of a color that applies to charts where a lack of
--   data is highlighted.
dataColorPalette_emptyFillColor :: Lens' DataColorPalette (Maybe Text)

-- | The hexadecimal codes for the colors.
dataColorPalette_colors :: Lens' DataColorPalette (Maybe [Text])
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataColorPalette.DataColorPalette
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataColorPalette.DataColorPalette
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataColorPalette.DataColorPalette
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataColorPalette.DataColorPalette
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataColorPalette.DataColorPalette
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataColorPalette.DataColorPalette

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings

-- | The Amazon QuickSight settings associated with your Amazon Web
--   Services account.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAccountSettings</a> smart constructor.
data AccountSettings
AccountSettings' :: Maybe Edition -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> AccountSettings

-- | The edition of Amazon QuickSight that you're currently subscribed to:
--   Enterprise edition or Standard edition.
[$sel:edition:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Edition

-- | The "account name" you provided for the Amazon QuickSight subscription
--   in your Amazon Web Services account. You create this name when you
--   sign up for Amazon QuickSight. It is unique in all of Amazon Web
--   Services and it appears only when users sign in.
[$sel:accountName:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | The default Amazon QuickSight namespace for your Amazon Web Services
--   account.
[$sel:defaultNamespace:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | The main notification email for your Amazon QuickSight subscription.
[$sel:notificationEmail:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>AccountSettings</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:edition:AccountSettings'</a>, <a>accountSettings_edition</a> -
--   The edition of Amazon QuickSight that you're currently subscribed to:
--   Enterprise edition or Standard edition.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accountName:AccountSettings'</a>,
--   <a>accountSettings_accountName</a> - The "account name" you provided
--   for the Amazon QuickSight subscription in your Amazon Web Services
--   account. You create this name when you sign up for Amazon QuickSight.
--   It is unique in all of Amazon Web Services and it appears only when
--   users sign in.
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultNamespace:AccountSettings'</a>,
--   <a>accountSettings_defaultNamespace</a> - The default Amazon
--   QuickSight namespace for your Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:notificationEmail:AccountSettings'</a>,
--   <a>accountSettings_notificationEmail</a> - The main notification email
--   for your Amazon QuickSight subscription.
newAccountSettings :: AccountSettings

-- | The edition of Amazon QuickSight that you're currently subscribed to:
--   Enterprise edition or Standard edition.
accountSettings_edition :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Edition)

-- | The "account name" you provided for the Amazon QuickSight subscription
--   in your Amazon Web Services account. You create this name when you
--   sign up for Amazon QuickSight. It is unique in all of Amazon Web
--   Services and it appears only when users sign in.
accountSettings_accountName :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Text)

-- | The default Amazon QuickSight namespace for your Amazon Web Services
--   account.
accountSettings_defaultNamespace :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Text)

-- | The main notification email for your Amazon QuickSight subscription.
accountSettings_notificationEmail :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings.AccountSettings
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings.AccountSettings
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings.AccountSettings
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings.AccountSettings
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings.AccountSettings
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings.AccountSettings
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AccountSettings.AccountSettings

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder

-- | A FieldFolder element is a folder that contains fields and nested
--   subfolders.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newFieldFolder</a> smart constructor.
data FieldFolder
FieldFolder' :: Maybe [Text] -> Maybe Text -> FieldFolder

-- | A folder has a list of columns. A column can only be in one folder.
[$sel:columns:FieldFolder'] :: FieldFolder -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The description for a field folder.
[$sel:description:FieldFolder'] :: FieldFolder -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>FieldFolder</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:columns:FieldFolder'</a>, <a>fieldFolder_columns</a> - A
--   folder has a list of columns. A column can only be in one folder.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:FieldFolder'</a>, <a>fieldFolder_description</a> -
--   The description for a field folder.
newFieldFolder :: FieldFolder

-- | A folder has a list of columns. A column can only be in one folder.
fieldFolder_columns :: Lens' FieldFolder (Maybe [Text])

-- | The description for a field folder.
fieldFolder_description :: Lens' FieldFolder (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FieldFolder.FieldFolder

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation

-- | A transform operation that filters rows based on a condition.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newFilterOperation</a> smart constructor.
data FilterOperation
FilterOperation' :: Text -> FilterOperation

-- | An expression that must evaluate to a Boolean value. Rows for which
--   the expression evaluates to true are kept in the dataset.
[$sel:conditionExpression:FilterOperation'] :: FilterOperation -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>FilterOperation</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:conditionExpression:FilterOperation'</a>,
--   <a>filterOperation_conditionExpression</a> - An expression that must
--   evaluate to a Boolean value. Rows for which the expression evaluates
--   to true are kept in the dataset.
newFilterOperation :: Text -> FilterOperation

-- | An expression that must evaluate to a Boolean value. Rows for which
--   the expression evaluates to true are kept in the dataset.
filterOperation_conditionExpression :: Lens' FilterOperation Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FilterOperation.FilterOperation

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter

-- | A filter that you apply when searching for dashboards.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDashboardSearchFilter</a> smart constructor.
data DashboardSearchFilter
DashboardSearchFilter' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe DashboardFilterAttribute -> FilterOperator -> DashboardSearchFilter

-- | The value of the named item, in this case <tt>QUICKSIGHT_USER</tt>,
--   that you want to use as a filter, for example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1"</tt>.
[$sel:value:DashboardSearchFilter'] :: DashboardSearchFilter -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the value that you want to use as a filter, for example,
--   <tt>"Name": "QUICKSIGHT_USER"</tt>.
[$sel:name:DashboardSearchFilter'] :: DashboardSearchFilter -> Maybe DashboardFilterAttribute

-- | The comparison operator that you want to use as a filter, for example,
--   <tt>"Operator": "StringEquals"</tt>.
[$sel:operator:DashboardSearchFilter'] :: DashboardSearchFilter -> FilterOperator

-- | Create a value of <a>DashboardSearchFilter</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:DashboardSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSearchFilter_value</a> - The value of the named item, in
--   this case <tt>QUICKSIGHT_USER</tt>, that you want to use as a filter,
--   for example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:DashboardSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSearchFilter_name</a> - The name of the value that you
--   want to use as a filter, for example, <tt>"Name":
--   "QUICKSIGHT_USER"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:DashboardSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardSearchFilter_operator</a> - The comparison operator that
--   you want to use as a filter, for example, <tt>"Operator":
--   "StringEquals"</tt>.
newDashboardSearchFilter :: FilterOperator -> DashboardSearchFilter

-- | The value of the named item, in this case <tt>QUICKSIGHT_USER</tt>,
--   that you want to use as a filter, for example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1"</tt>.
dashboardSearchFilter_value :: Lens' DashboardSearchFilter (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the value that you want to use as a filter, for example,
--   <tt>"Name": "QUICKSIGHT_USER"</tt>.
dashboardSearchFilter_name :: Lens' DashboardSearchFilter (Maybe DashboardFilterAttribute)

-- | The comparison operator that you want to use as a filter, for example,
--   <tt>"Operator": "StringEquals"</tt>.
dashboardSearchFilter_operator :: Lens' DashboardSearchFilter FilterOperator
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter.DashboardSearchFilter
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter.DashboardSearchFilter
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter.DashboardSearchFilter
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter.DashboardSearchFilter
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter.DashboardSearchFilter
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter.DashboardSearchFilter
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardSearchFilter.DashboardSearchFilter


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSearchFilter

-- | A filter that you apply when searching for one or more analyses.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAnalysisSearchFilter</a> smart constructor.
data AnalysisSearchFilter
AnalysisSearchFilter' :: Maybe FilterOperator -> Maybe Text -> Maybe AnalysisFilterAttribute -> AnalysisSearchFilter

-- | The comparison operator that you want to use as a filter, for example
--   <tt>"Operator": "StringEquals"</tt>.
[$sel:operator:AnalysisSearchFilter'] :: AnalysisSearchFilter -> Maybe FilterOperator

-- | The value of the named item, in this case <tt>QUICKSIGHT_USER</tt>,
--   that you want to use as a filter, for example <tt>"Value"</tt>. An
--   example is
--   <tt>"arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1"</tt>.
[$sel:value:AnalysisSearchFilter'] :: AnalysisSearchFilter -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the value that you want to use as a filter, for example
--   <tt>"Name": "QUICKSIGHT_USER"</tt>.
[$sel:name:AnalysisSearchFilter'] :: AnalysisSearchFilter -> Maybe AnalysisFilterAttribute

-- | Create a value of <a>AnalysisSearchFilter</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.

--   fields.
--

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:AnalysisSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>analysisSearchFilter_operator</a> - The comparison operator that
--   you want to use as a filter, for example <tt>"Operator":
--   "StringEquals"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:AnalysisSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>analysisSearchFilter_value</a> - The value of the named item, in
--   this case <tt>QUICKSIGHT_USER</tt>, that you want to use as a filter,
--   for example <tt>"Value"</tt>. An example is
--   <tt>"arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:AnalysisSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>analysisSearchFilter_name</a> - The name of the value that you want
--   to use as a filter, for example <tt>"Name": "QUICKSIGHT_USER"</tt>.
newAnalysisSearchFilter :: AnalysisSearchFilter

-- | The comparison operator that you want to use as a filter, for example
--   <tt>"Operator": "StringEquals"</tt>.
analysisSearchFilter_operator :: Lens' AnalysisSearchFilter (Maybe FilterOperator)

-- | The value of the named item, in this case <tt>QUICKSIGHT_USER</tt>,
--   that you want to use as a filter, for example <tt>"Value"</tt>. An
--   example is
--   <tt>"arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1"</tt>.
analysisSearchFilter_value :: Lens' AnalysisSearchFilter (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the value that you want to use as a filter, for example
--   <tt>"Name": "QUICKSIGHT_USER"</tt>.
analysisSearchFilter_name :: Lens' AnalysisSearchFilter (Maybe AnalysisFilterAttribute)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSearchFilter.AnalysisSearchFilter

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.FolderSearchFilter

-- | Searches a folder by a filter.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newFolderSearchFilter</a> smart constructor.
data FolderSearchFilter
FolderSearchFilter' :: Maybe FilterOperator -> Maybe Text -> Maybe FolderFilterAttribute -> FolderSearchFilter

-- | The comparison operator that you want to use as a filter. For example,
--   <tt>"Operator": "StringEquals"</tt>.
[$sel:operator:FolderSearchFilter'] :: FolderSearchFilter -> Maybe FilterOperator

-- | The value of the named item (in this example,
--   <tt>PARENT_FOLDER_ARN</tt>), that you want to use as a filter. For
--   example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:folder/folderId"</tt>.
[$sel:value:FolderSearchFilter'] :: FolderSearchFilter -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the value that you want to use as a filter. For example,
--   <tt>"Name": "PARENT_FOLDER_ARN"</tt>.
[$sel:name:FolderSearchFilter'] :: FolderSearchFilter -> Maybe FolderFilterAttribute

-- | Create a value of <a>FolderSearchFilter</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:FolderSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>folderSearchFilter_operator</a> - The comparison operator that you
--   want to use as a filter. For example, <tt>"Operator":
--   "StringEquals"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:FolderSearchFilter'</a>, <a>folderSearchFilter_value</a>
--   - The value of the named item (in this example,
--   <tt>PARENT_FOLDER_ARN</tt>), that you want to use as a filter. For
--   example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:folder/folderId"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:FolderSearchFilter'</a>, <a>folderSearchFilter_name</a> -
--   The name of the value that you want to use as a filter. For example,
--   <tt>"Name": "PARENT_FOLDER_ARN"</tt>.
newFolderSearchFilter :: FolderSearchFilter

-- | The comparison operator that you want to use as a filter. For example,
--   <tt>"Operator": "StringEquals"</tt>.
folderSearchFilter_operator :: Lens' FolderSearchFilter (Maybe FilterOperator)

-- | The value of the named item (in this example,
--   <tt>PARENT_FOLDER_ARN</tt>), that you want to use as a filter. For
--   example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:folder/folderId"</tt>.
folderSearchFilter_value :: Lens' FolderSearchFilter (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the value that you want to use as a filter. For example,
--   <tt>"Name": "PARENT_FOLDER_ARN"</tt>.
folderSearchFilter_name :: Lens' FolderSearchFilter (Maybe FolderFilterAttribute)

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Group

-- | A <i>group</i> in Amazon QuickSight consists of a set of users. You
--   can use groups to make it easier to manage access and security.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newGroup</a> smart constructor.
data Group
Group' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Group

-- | The principal ID of the group.
[$sel:principalId:Group'] :: Group -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the group.
[$sel:arn:Group'] :: Group -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the group.
[$sel:groupName:Group'] :: Group -> Maybe Text

-- | The group description.
[$sel:description:Group'] :: Group -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Group</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:principalId:Group'</a>, <a>group_principalId</a> - The
--   principal ID of the group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Group'</a>, <a>group_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) for the group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:groupName:Group'</a>, <a>group_groupName</a> - The name of the
--   group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:Group'</a>, <a>group_description</a> - The group
--   description.
newGroup :: Group

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.InputColumn

-- | Metadata for a column that is used as the input of a transform
--   operation.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInputColumn</a> smart constructor.
data InputColumn
InputColumn' :: Text -> InputColumnDataType -> InputColumn

-- | The name of this column in the underlying data source.
[$sel:name:InputColumn'] :: InputColumn -> Text

-- | The data type of the column.
[$sel:type':InputColumn'] :: InputColumn -> InputColumnDataType

-- | Create a value of <a>InputColumn</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:InputColumn'</a>, <a>inputColumn_name</a> - The name of
--   this column in the underlying data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':InputColumn'</a>, <a>inputColumn_type</a> - The data
--   type of the column.
newInputColumn :: Text -> InputColumnDataType -> InputColumn

-- | The name of this column in the underlying data source.
inputColumn_name :: Lens' InputColumn Text

-- | The data type of the column.
inputColumn_type :: Lens' InputColumn InputColumnDataType
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.InputColumn.InputColumn
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.InputColumn.InputColumn
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.InputColumn.InputColumn

instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.InputColumn.InputColumn
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.InputColumn.InputColumn


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql

-- | A physical table type built from the results of the custom SQL query.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCustomSql</a> smart constructor.
data CustomSql
CustomSql' :: Maybe (NonEmpty InputColumn) -> Text -> Text -> Text -> CustomSql

-- | The column schema from the SQL query result set.
[$sel:columns:CustomSql'] :: CustomSql -> Maybe (NonEmpty InputColumn)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
[$sel:dataSourceArn:CustomSql'] :: CustomSql -> Text

-- | A display name for the SQL query result.
[$sel:name:CustomSql'] :: CustomSql -> Text

-- | The SQL query.
[$sel:sqlQuery:CustomSql'] :: CustomSql -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>CustomSql</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:columns:CustomSql'</a>, <a>customSql_columns</a> - The column
--   schema from the SQL query result set.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceArn:CustomSql'</a>, <a>customSql_dataSourceArn</a> -
--   The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:CustomSql'</a>, <a>customSql_name</a> - A display name
--   for the SQL query result.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sqlQuery:CustomSql'</a>, <a>customSql_sqlQuery</a> - The SQL
--   query.
newCustomSql :: Text -> Text -> Text -> CustomSql

-- | The column schema from the SQL query result set.
customSql_columns :: Lens' CustomSql (Maybe (NonEmpty InputColumn))

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
customSql_dataSourceArn :: Lens' CustomSql Text

-- | A display name for the SQL query result.
customSql_name :: Lens' CustomSql Text

-- | The SQL query.
customSql_sqlQuery :: Lens' CustomSql Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CustomSql.CustomSql

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinKeyProperties

--   optimize query performance.

--   <a>joinKeyProperties_uniqueKey</a> - A value that indicates that a row
--   in a table is uniquely identified by the columns in a join key. This
--   is used by Amazon QuickSight to optimize query performance.
newJoinKeyProperties :: JoinKeyProperties

-- | A value that indicates that a row in a table is uniquely identified by
--   the columns in a join key. This is used by Amazon QuickSight to
--   optimize query performance.
joinKeyProperties_uniqueKey :: Lens' JoinKeyProperties (Maybe Bool)

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction

-- | The instructions associated with a join.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newJoinInstruction</a> smart constructor.
data JoinInstruction
JoinInstruction' :: Maybe JoinKeyProperties -> Maybe JoinKeyProperties -> Text -> Text -> JoinType -> Text -> JoinInstruction

-- | Join key properties of the right operand.
[$sel:rightJoinKeyProperties:JoinInstruction'] :: JoinInstruction -> Maybe JoinKeyProperties

-- | Join key properties of the left operand.
[$sel:leftJoinKeyProperties:JoinInstruction'] :: JoinInstruction -> Maybe JoinKeyProperties

-- | The operand on the left side of a join.
[$sel:leftOperand:JoinInstruction'] :: JoinInstruction -> Text

-- | The operand on the right side of a join.
[$sel:rightOperand:JoinInstruction'] :: JoinInstruction -> Text

-- | The type of join that it is.
[$sel:type':JoinInstruction'] :: JoinInstruction -> JoinType

-- | The join instructions provided in the <tt>ON</tt> clause of a join.
[$sel:onClause:JoinInstruction'] :: JoinInstruction -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>JoinInstruction</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:rightJoinKeyProperties:JoinInstruction'</a>,
--   <a>joinInstruction_rightJoinKeyProperties</a> - Join key properties of
--   the right operand.
--   
--   <a>$sel:leftJoinKeyProperties:JoinInstruction'</a>,
--   <a>joinInstruction_leftJoinKeyProperties</a> - Join key properties of
--   the left operand.
--   
--   <a>$sel:leftOperand:JoinInstruction'</a>,
--   <a>joinInstruction_leftOperand</a> - The operand on the left side of a
--   join.
--   
--   <a>$sel:rightOperand:JoinInstruction'</a>,
--   <a>joinInstruction_rightOperand</a> - The operand on the right side of
--   a join.
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':JoinInstruction'</a>, <a>joinInstruction_type</a> - The
--   type of join that it is.
--   
--   <a>$sel:onClause:JoinInstruction'</a>, <a>joinInstruction_onClause</a>
--   - The join instructions provided in the <tt>ON</tt> clause of a join.
newJoinInstruction :: Text -> Text -> JoinType -> Text -> JoinInstruction

-- | Join key properties of the right operand.
joinInstruction_rightJoinKeyProperties :: Lens' JoinInstruction (Maybe JoinKeyProperties)

-- | Join key properties of the left operand.
joinInstruction_leftJoinKeyProperties :: Lens' JoinInstruction (Maybe JoinKeyProperties)

-- | The operand on the left side of a join.
joinInstruction_leftOperand :: Lens' JoinInstruction Text

-- | The operand on the right side of a join.
joinInstruction_rightOperand :: Lens' JoinInstruction Text

-- | The type of join that it is.
joinInstruction_type :: Lens' JoinInstruction JoinType

-- | The join instructions provided in the <tt>ON</tt> clause of a join.
joinInstruction_onClause :: Lens' JoinInstruction Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.JoinInstruction.JoinInstruction


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTableSource

-- | Information about the source of a logical table. This is a variant
--   type structure. For this structure to be valid, only one of the
--   attributes can be non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newLogicalTableSource</a> smart constructor.
data LogicalTableSource
LogicalTableSource' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe JoinInstruction -> Maybe Text -> LogicalTableSource

-- | The Amazon Resource Number (ARN) of the parent dataset.
[$sel:dataSetArn:LogicalTableSource'] :: LogicalTableSource -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the result of a join of two logical tables.
[$sel:joinInstruction:LogicalTableSource'] :: LogicalTableSource -> Maybe JoinInstruction

-- | Physical table ID.
[$sel:physicalTableId:LogicalTableSource'] :: LogicalTableSource -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>LogicalTableSource</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetArn:LogicalTableSource'</a>,
--   <a>logicalTableSource_dataSetArn</a> - The Amazon Resource Number
--   (ARN) of the parent dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:joinInstruction:LogicalTableSource'</a>,
--   <a>logicalTableSource_joinInstruction</a> - Specifies the result of a
--   join of two logical tables.
--   
--   <a>$sel:physicalTableId:LogicalTableSource'</a>,
--   <a>logicalTableSource_physicalTableId</a> - Physical table ID.
newLogicalTableSource :: LogicalTableSource

-- | The Amazon Resource Number (ARN) of the parent dataset.
logicalTableSource_dataSetArn :: Lens' LogicalTableSource (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the result of a join of two logical tables.
logicalTableSource_joinInstruction :: Lens' LogicalTableSource (Maybe JoinInstruction)

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.QueueInfo

-- | Information about a queued dataset SPICE ingestion.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newQueueInfo</a> smart constructor.
data QueueInfo
QueueInfo' :: Text -> Text -> QueueInfo

-- | The ID of the queued ingestion.
[$sel:waitingOnIngestion:QueueInfo'] :: QueueInfo -> Text

-- | The ID of the ongoing ingestion. The queued ingestion is waiting for
--   the ongoing ingestion to complete.
[$sel:queuedIngestion:QueueInfo'] :: QueueInfo -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>QueueInfo</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   <a>$sel:waitingOnIngestion:QueueInfo'</a>,
--   <a>queueInfo_waitingOnIngestion</a> - The ID of the queued ingestion.
--   
--   <a>$sel:queuedIngestion:QueueInfo'</a>,
--   <a>queueInfo_queuedIngestion</a> - The ID of the ongoing ingestion.
--   The queued ingestion is waiting for the ongoing ingestion to complete.
newQueueInfo :: Text -> Text -> QueueInfo

-- | The ID of the queued ingestion.
queueInfo_waitingOnIngestion :: Lens' QueueInfo Text

-- | The ID of the ongoing ingestion. The queued ingestion is waiting for
--   the ongoing ingestion to complete.
queueInfo_queuedIngestion :: Lens' QueueInfo Text

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RedshiftParameters

-- | The parameters for Amazon Redshift. The <tt>ClusterId</tt> field can
--   be blank if <tt>Host</tt> and <tt>Port</tt> are both set. The
--   <tt>Host</tt> and <tt>Port</tt> fields can be blank if the
--   <tt>ClusterId</tt> field is set.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRedshiftParameters</a> smart constructor.
data RedshiftParameters
RedshiftParameters' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> Text -> RedshiftParameters

-- | Cluster ID. This field can be blank if the <tt>Host</tt> and
--   <tt>Port</tt> are provided.
[$sel:clusterId:RedshiftParameters'] :: RedshiftParameters -> Maybe Text

-- | Host. This field can be blank if <tt>ClusterId</tt> is provided.
[$sel:host:RedshiftParameters'] :: RedshiftParameters -> Maybe Text

-- | Port. This field can be blank if the <tt>ClusterId</tt> is provided.
[$sel:port:RedshiftParameters'] :: RedshiftParameters -> Maybe Natural

-- | Database.
[$sel:database:RedshiftParameters'] :: RedshiftParameters -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RedshiftParameters</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:clusterId:RedshiftParameters'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftParameters_clusterId</a> - Cluster ID. This field can be
--   blank if the <tt>Host</tt> and <tt>Port</tt> are provided.
--   
--   <a>$sel:host:RedshiftParameters'</a>, <a>redshiftParameters_host</a> -
--   Host. This field can be blank if <tt>ClusterId</tt> is provided.
--   
--   <a>$sel:port:RedshiftParameters'</a>, <a>redshiftParameters_port</a> -
--   Port. This field can be blank if the <tt>ClusterId</tt> is provided.
--   
--   <a>$sel:database:RedshiftParameters'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftParameters_database</a> - Database.
newRedshiftParameters :: Text -> RedshiftParameters

-- | Cluster ID. This field can be blank if the <tt>Host</tt> and
--   <tt>Port</tt> are provided.
redshiftParameters_clusterId :: Lens' RedshiftParameters (Maybe Text)

-- | Host. This field can be blank if <tt>ClusterId</tt> is provided.
redshiftParameters_host :: Lens' RedshiftParameters (Maybe Text)

-- | Port. This field can be blank if the <tt>ClusterId</tt> is provided.
redshiftParameters_port :: Lens' RedshiftParameters (Maybe Natural)

-- | Database.
redshiftParameters_database :: Lens' RedshiftParameters Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RedshiftParameters.RedshiftParameters
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RedshiftParameters.RedshiftParameters
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RedshiftParameters.RedshiftParameters
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RedshiftParameters.RedshiftParameters

--   smart constructor.
data RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration
RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration' :: Text -> RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The dashboard ID for the dashboard that you want the user to see
--   first. This ID is included in the output URL. When the URL in response
--   is accessed, Amazon QuickSight renders this dashboard if the user has
--   permissions to view it.
--   
--   If the user does not have permission to view this dashboard, they see
--   a permissions error message.
[$sel:initialDashboardId:RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration -> Text

--   - The dashboard ID for the dashboard that you want the user to see
--   first. This ID is included in the output URL. When the URL in response
--   is accessed, Amazon QuickSight renders this dashboard if the user has
--   permissions to view it.
--   
--   If the user does not have permission to view this dashboard, they see
--   a permissions error message.
newRegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration :: Text -> RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The dashboard ID for the dashboard that you want the user to see
--   first. This ID is included in the output URL. When the URL in response
--   is accessed, Amazon QuickSight renders this dashboard if the user has
--   permissions to view it.

--   a permissions error message.

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration</a>
--   smart constructor.
data RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration
RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration' :: Maybe Text -> RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The ID of the Q topic that you want to make the starting topic in the
--   Q search bar. You can find a topic ID by navigating to the Topics pane
--   in the Amazon QuickSight application and opening a topic. The ID is in
--   the URL for the topic that you open.
--   
--   If you don't specify an initial topic, a list of all shared topics is
--   shown in the Q bar for your readers. When you select an initial topic,
--   you can specify whether or not readers are allowed to select other
--   topics from the available ones in the list.

--   The ID of the Q topic that you want to make the starting topic in the
--   Q search bar. You can find a topic ID by navigating to the Topics pane
--   in the Amazon QuickSight application and opening a topic. The ID is in
--   the URL for the topic that you open.
--   
--   If you don't specify an initial topic, a list of all shared topics is
--   shown in the Q bar for your readers. When you select an initial topic,
--   you can specify whether or not readers are allowed to select other
--   topics from the available ones in the list.
newRegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration :: RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The ID of the Q topic that you want to make the starting topic in the
--   Q search bar. You can find a topic ID by navigating to the Topics pane
--   in the Amazon QuickSight application and opening a topic. The ID is in

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | Information about the Amazon QuickSight console that you want to
--   embed.
--   
--   <i>See:</i>
--   <a>newRegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration</a> smart
--   constructor.
data RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration
RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration' :: Maybe Text -> RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The initial URL path for the Amazon QuickSight console.
--   <tt>InitialPath</tt> is required.
--   
--   The entry point URL is constrained to the following paths:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>/start</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/analyses</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/dashboards</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/favorites</pre></li>
--   <li><tt>/dashboards/DashboardId</tt>. <i>DashboardId</i> is the actual
--   ID key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the dashboard.</li>
--   <li><tt>/analyses/AnalysisId</tt>. <i>AnalysisId</i> is the actual ID
--   key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the analysis.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:initialPath:RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of
--   <a>RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:initialPath:RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>registeredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration_initialPath</a>
--   - The initial URL path for the Amazon QuickSight console.
--   <tt>InitialPath</tt> is required.
--   
--   The entry point URL is constrained to the following paths:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>/start</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/analyses</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/dashboards</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/favorites</pre></li>
--   <li><tt>/dashboards/DashboardId</tt>. <i>DashboardId</i> is the actual
--   ID key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the dashboard.</li>
--   <li><tt>/analyses/AnalysisId</tt>. <i>AnalysisId</i> is the actual ID
--   key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the analysis.</li>
--   </ul>
newRegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration :: RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The initial URL path for the Amazon QuickSight console.
--   <tt>InitialPath</tt> is required.
--   
--   The entry point URL is constrained to the following paths:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>/start</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/analyses</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/dashboards</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/favorites</pre></li>
--   <li><tt>/dashboards/DashboardId</tt>. <i>DashboardId</i> is the actual
--   ID key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the dashboard.</li>
--   <li><tt>/analyses/AnalysisId</tt>. <i>AnalysisId</i> is the actual ID
--   key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the analysis.</li>
--   </ul>
registeredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration_initialPath :: Lens' RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration.RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration.RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration.RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration

-- | The type of experience you want to embed. For registered users, you
--   can embed an Amazon QuickSight dashboard or the Amazon QuickSight
--   console.
--   
--   Exactly one of the experience configurations is required. You can
--   choose <tt>Dashboard</tt> or <tt>QuickSightConsole</tt>. You cannot
--   choose more than one experience configuraton.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration</a>
--   smart constructor.
data RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration
RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration' :: Maybe RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration -> RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration

-- | The configuration details for providing a dashboard embedding
--   experience.
[$sel:dashboard:RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The configuration details for providing an Amazon QuickSight console
--   embedding experience. This can be used along with custom permissions
--   to restrict access to certain features. For more information, see
--   <a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide</i>.
--   
--   Use <tt>GenerateEmbedUrlForRegisteredUser</tt> where you want to
--   provide an authoring portal that allows users to create data sources,
--   datasets, analyses, and dashboards. The users who accesses an embedded
--   Amazon QuickSight console needs to belong to the author or admin
--   security cohort. If you want to restrict permissions to some of these
--   features, add a custom permissions profile to the user with the <tt>
--   UpdateUser </tt> API operation. Use <tt> RegisterUser </tt> API
--   operation to add a new user with a custom permission profile attached.
--   For more information, see the following sections in the <i>Amazon
--   QuickSight User Guide</i>:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><a>Embedding the Full Functionality of the Amazon QuickSight
--   Console for Authenticated Users</a></li>
--   <li><a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information about the high-level steps for embedding and for
--   an interactive demo of the ways you can customize embedding, visit the
--   <a>Amazon QuickSight Developer Portal</a>.
[$sel:quickSightConsole:RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The configuration details for embedding the Q search bar.
--   
--   For more information about embedding the Q search bar, see
--   <a>Embedding Overview</a>.
[$sel:qSearchBar:RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | Create a value of
--   <a>RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RelationalTable

-- | A physical table type for relational data sources.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRelationalTable</a> smart constructor.
data RelationalTable
RelationalTable' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Text -> Text -> NonEmpty InputColumn -> RelationalTable

-- | The catalog associated with a table.
[$sel:catalog:RelationalTable'] :: RelationalTable -> Maybe Text

-- | The schema name. This name applies to certain relational database
--   engines.
[$sel:schema:RelationalTable'] :: RelationalTable -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the data source.
[$sel:dataSourceArn:RelationalTable'] :: RelationalTable -> Text

-- | The name of the relational table.
[$sel:name:RelationalTable'] :: RelationalTable -> Text

-- | The column schema of the table.
[$sel:inputColumns:RelationalTable'] :: RelationalTable -> NonEmpty InputColumn

-- | Create a value of <a>RelationalTable</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:catalog:RelationalTable'</a>, <a>relationalTable_catalog</a> -
--   The catalog associated with a table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:schema:RelationalTable'</a>, <a>relationalTable_schema</a> -
--   The schema name. This name applies to certain relational database
--   engines.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceArn:RelationalTable'</a>,
--   <a>relationalTable_dataSourceArn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   for the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:RelationalTable'</a>, <a>relationalTable_name</a> - The
--   name of the relational table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:inputColumns:RelationalTable'</a>,
--   <a>relationalTable_inputColumns</a> - The column schema of the table.
newRelationalTable :: Text -> Text -> NonEmpty InputColumn -> RelationalTable

-- | The catalog associated with a table.
relationalTable_catalog :: Lens' RelationalTable (Maybe Text)

-- | The schema name. This name applies to certain relational database
--   engines.
relationalTable_schema :: Lens' RelationalTable (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the data source.
relationalTable_dataSourceArn :: Lens' RelationalTable Text

-- | The name of the relational table.
relationalTable_name :: Lens' RelationalTable Text

-- | The column schema of the table.
relationalTable_inputColumns :: Lens' RelationalTable (NonEmpty InputColumn)

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission

-- | Permission for the resource.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newResourcePermission</a> smart constructor.
data ResourcePermission
ResourcePermission' :: Text -> NonEmpty Text -> ResourcePermission

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the principal. This can be one of
--   the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user or group associated with a
--   data source or dataset. (This is common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user, group, or namespace
--   associated with an analysis, dashboard, template, or theme. (This is
--   common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon Web Services account root: This is an IAMARN
--   rather than a Amazon QuickSight ARN. Use this option only to share
--   resources (templates) across Amazon Web Services accounts. (This is
--   less common.)</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:principal:ResourcePermission'] :: ResourcePermission -> Text

-- | The IAMaction to grant or revoke permissions on.
[$sel:actions:ResourcePermission'] :: ResourcePermission -> NonEmpty Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ResourcePermission</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:principal:ResourcePermission'</a>,
--   <a>resourcePermission_principal</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   of the principal. This can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user or group associated with a
--   data source or dataset. (This is common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user, group, or namespace
--   associated with an analysis, dashboard, template, or theme. (This is
--   common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon Web Services account root: This is an IAMARN
--   rather than a Amazon QuickSight ARN. Use this option only to share
--   resources (templates) across Amazon Web Services accounts. (This is
--   less common.)</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:actions:ResourcePermission'</a>,
--   <a>resourcePermission_actions</a> - The IAMaction to grant or revoke
--   permissions on.
newResourcePermission :: Text -> NonEmpty Text -> ResourcePermission

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the principal. This can be one of
--   the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user or group associated with a
--   data source or dataset. (This is common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user, group, or namespace
--   associated with an analysis, dashboard, template, or theme. (This is
--   common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon Web Services account root: This is an IAMARN
--   rather than a Amazon QuickSight ARN. Use this option only to share
--   resources (templates) across Amazon Web Services accounts. (This is
--   less common.)</li>
--   </ul>
resourcePermission_principal :: Lens' ResourcePermission Text

-- | The IAMaction to grant or revoke permissions on.
resourcePermission_actions :: Lens' ResourcePermission (NonEmpty Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ResourcePermission.ResourcePermission

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary

-- | The summary metadata that describes an analysis.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAnalysisSummary</a> smart constructor.
data AnalysisSummary
AnalysisSummary' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> AnalysisSummary

-- | The last known status for the analysis.
[$sel:status:AnalysisSummary'] :: AnalysisSummary -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The ID of the analysis. This ID displays in the URL.
[$sel:analysisId:AnalysisSummary'] :: AnalysisSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that the analysis was last updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:AnalysisSummary'] :: AnalysisSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the analysis.
[$sel:arn:AnalysisSummary'] :: AnalysisSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that the analysis was created.
[$sel:createdTime:AnalysisSummary'] :: AnalysisSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The name of the analysis. This name is displayed in the Amazon
--   QuickSight console.
[$sel:name:AnalysisSummary'] :: AnalysisSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>AnalysisSummary</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:AnalysisSummary'</a>, <a>analysisSummary_status</a> -
--   The last known status for the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:analysisId:AnalysisSummary'</a>,
--   <a>analysisSummary_analysisId</a> - The ID of the analysis. This ID
--   displays in the URL.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:AnalysisSummary'</a>,
--   <a>analysisSummary_lastUpdatedTime</a> - The time that the analysis
--   was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:AnalysisSummary'</a>, <a>analysisSummary_arn</a> - The
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:AnalysisSummary'</a>,
--   <a>analysisSummary_createdTime</a> - The time that the analysis was
--   created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:AnalysisSummary'</a>, <a>analysisSummary_name</a> - The
--   name of the analysis. This name is displayed in the Amazon QuickSight
--   console.
newAnalysisSummary :: AnalysisSummary

-- | The last known status for the analysis.
analysisSummary_status :: Lens' AnalysisSummary (Maybe ResourceStatus)

-- | The ID of the analysis. This ID displays in the URL.
analysisSummary_analysisId :: Lens' AnalysisSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that the analysis was last updated.
analysisSummary_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' AnalysisSummary (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the analysis.
analysisSummary_arn :: Lens' AnalysisSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that the analysis was created.
analysisSummary_createdTime :: Lens' AnalysisSummary (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The name of the analysis. This name is displayed in the Amazon
--   QuickSight console.
analysisSummary_name :: Lens' AnalysisSummary (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary.AnalysisSummary
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary.AnalysisSummary
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary.AnalysisSummary
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary.AnalysisSummary
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary.AnalysisSummary
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary.AnalysisSummary
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.AnalysisSummary.AnalysisSummary

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Ingestion

-- | Information about the SPICE ingestion for a dataset.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newIngestion</a> smart constructor.
data Ingestion
Ingestion' :: Maybe IngestionRequestSource -> Maybe QueueInfo -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe IngestionRequestType -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe RowInfo -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorInfo -> Text -> IngestionStatus -> POSIX -> Ingestion

-- | Event source for this ingestion.
[$sel:requestSource:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe IngestionRequestSource
[$sel:queueInfo:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe QueueInfo

-- | The time that this ingestion took, measured in seconds.
[$sel:ingestionTimeInSeconds:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe Integer

-- | Type of this ingestion.
[$sel:requestType:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe IngestionRequestType

-- | The size of the data ingested, in bytes.
[$sel:ingestionSizeInBytes:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe Integer
[$sel:rowInfo:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe RowInfo

-- | Ingestion ID.
[$sel:ingestionId:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe Text

-- | Error information for this ingestion.
[$sel:errorInfo:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe ErrorInfo

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Text

-- | Ingestion status.
[$sel:ingestionStatus:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> IngestionStatus

-- | The time that this ingestion started.
[$sel:createdTime:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> POSIX

-- | Create a value of <a>Ingestion</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestSource:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_requestSource</a> -
--   Event source for this ingestion.
--   
--   <a>$sel:queueInfo:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_queueInfo</a> -
--   Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:ingestionTimeInSeconds:Ingestion'</a>,
--   <a>ingestion_ingestionTimeInSeconds</a> - The time that this ingestion
--   took, measured in seconds.
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestType:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_requestType</a> -
--   Type of this ingestion.
--   
--   <a>$sel:ingestionSizeInBytes:Ingestion'</a>,
--   <a>ingestion_ingestionSizeInBytes</a> - The size of the data ingested,
--   in bytes.
--   
--   <a>$sel:rowInfo:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_rowInfo</a> -
--   Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:ingestionId:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_ingestionId</a> -
--   Ingestion ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorInfo:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_errorInfo</a> - Error
--   information for this ingestion.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:ingestionStatus:Ingestion'</a>,
--   <a>ingestion_ingestionStatus</a> - Ingestion status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Ingestion'</a>, <a>ingestion_createdTime</a> - The
--   time that this ingestion started.
newIngestion :: Text -> IngestionStatus -> UTCTime -> Ingestion

-- | Undocumented member.
ingestion_queueInfo :: Lens' Ingestion (Maybe QueueInfo)

ingestion_requestType :: Lens' Ingestion (Maybe IngestionRequestType)

-- | The size of the data ingested, in bytes.
ingestion_ingestionSizeInBytes :: Lens' Ingestion (Maybe Integer)

-- | Undocumented member.
ingestion_rowInfo :: Lens' Ingestion (Maybe RowInfo)

-- | Ingestion ID.
ingestion_ingestionId :: Lens' Ingestion (Maybe Text)

-- | Error information for this ingestion.
ingestion_errorInfo :: Lens' Ingestion (Maybe ErrorInfo)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
ingestion_arn :: Lens' Ingestion Text

-- | Ingestion status.
ingestion_ingestionStatus :: Lens' Ingestion IngestionStatus

-- | The time that this ingestion started.
ingestion_createdTime :: Lens' Ingestion UTCTime

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionTagRule

-- | A set of rules associated with a tag.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRowLevelPermissionTagRule</a> smart constructor.
data RowLevelPermissionTagRule
RowLevelPermissionTagRule' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Text -> Text -> RowLevelPermissionTagRule

-- | A string that you want to use to delimit the values when you pass the
--   values at run time. For example, you can delimit the values with a
--   comma.
[$sel:tagMultiValueDelimiter:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Maybe Text

-- | A string that you want to use to filter by all the values in a column
--   in the dataset and dont want to list the values one by one. For
--   example, you can use an asterisk as your match all value.
[$sel:matchAllValue:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The unique key for a tag.
[$sel:tagKey:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Text

-- | The column name that a tag key is assigned to.
[$sel:columnName:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RowLevelPermissionTagRule</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagMultiValueDelimiter:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_tagMultiValueDelimiter</a> - A string
--   that you want to use to delimit the values when you pass the values at
--   run time. For example, you can delimit the values with a comma.
--   
--   <a>$sel:matchAllValue:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_matchAllValue</a> - A string that you
--   want to use to filter by all the values in a column in the dataset and
--   dont want to list the values one by one. For example, you can use an
--   asterisk as your match all value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagKey:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_tagKey</a> - The unique key for a tag.
--   
--   <a>$sel:columnName:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_columnName</a> - The column name that a
--   tag key is assigned to.
newRowLevelPermissionTagRule :: Text -> Text -> RowLevelPermissionTagRule

-- | A string that you want to use to delimit the values when you pass the
--   values at run time. For example, you can delimit the values with a
--   comma.
rowLevelPermissionTagRule_tagMultiValueDelimiter :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionTagRule (Maybe Text)

--   in the dataset and dont want to list the values one by one. For
--   example, you can use an asterisk as your match all value.

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet

-- | A <i>sheet</i>, which is an object that contains a set of visuals that
--   are viewed together on one page in Amazon QuickSight. Every analysis
--   and dashboard contains at least one sheet. Each sheet contains at
--   least one visualization widget, for example a chart, pivot table, or
--   narrative insight. Sheets can be associated with other components,
--   such as controls, filters, and so on.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSheet</a> smart constructor.
data Sheet
Sheet' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Sheet

-- | The name of a sheet. This name is displayed on the sheet's tab in the
--   Amazon QuickSight console.
[$sel:name:Sheet'] :: Sheet -> Maybe Text

-- | The unique identifier associated with a sheet.
[$sel:sheetId:Sheet'] :: Sheet -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Sheet</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Sheet'</a>, <a>sheet_name</a> - The name of a sheet. This
--   name is displayed on the sheet's tab in the Amazon QuickSight console.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sheetId:Sheet'</a>, <a>sheet_sheetId</a> - The unique
--   identifier associated with a sheet.
newSheet :: Sheet

-- | The name of a sheet. This name is displayed on the sheet's tab in the
--   Amazon QuickSight console.
sheet_name :: Lens' Sheet (Maybe Text)

-- | The unique identifier associated with a sheet.
sheet_sheetId :: Lens' Sheet (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet.Sheet
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet.Sheet
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet.Sheet
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet.Sheet
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet.Sheet
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet.Sheet
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Sheet.Sheet


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DashboardVersion

-- | Dashboard version.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDashboardVersion</a> smart constructor.
data DashboardVersion
DashboardVersion' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe [Sheet] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe (NonEmpty DashboardError) -> Maybe Text -> DashboardVersion

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
[$sel:status:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The ARN of the theme associated with a version of the dashboard.
[$sel:themeArn:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Numbers (ARNs) for the datasets that are
--   associated with this version of the dashboard.
[$sel:dataSetArns:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe [Text]

-- | A list of the associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of
--   each sheet.
[$sel:sheets:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe [Sheet]

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that this dashboard version was created.
[$sel:createdTime:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Source entity ARN.
[$sel:sourceEntityArn:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | Version number for this version of the dashboard.
[$sel:versionNumber:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe Natural

-- | Errors associated with this dashboard version.
[$sel:errors:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe (NonEmpty DashboardError)

-- | Description.
[$sel:description:DashboardVersion'] :: DashboardVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DashboardVersion</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DashboardVersion'</a>, <a>dashboardVersion_status</a> -
--   The HTTP status of the request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeArn:DashboardVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardVersion_themeArn</a> - The ARN of the theme associated
--   with a version of the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetArns:DashboardVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardVersion_dataSetArns</a> - The Amazon Resource Numbers
--   (ARNs) for the datasets that are associated with this version of the
--   dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sheets:DashboardVersion'</a>, <a>dashboardVersion_sheets</a> -
--   A list of the associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of
--   each sheet.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:DashboardVersion'</a>, <a>dashboardVersion_arn</a> - The
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:DashboardVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardVersion_createdTime</a> - The time that this dashboard
--   version was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceEntityArn:DashboardVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardVersion_sourceEntityArn</a> - Source entity ARN.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionNumber:DashboardVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardVersion_versionNumber</a> - Version number for this
--   version of the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errors:DashboardVersion'</a>, <a>dashboardVersion_errors</a> -
--   Errors associated with this dashboard version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:DashboardVersion'</a>,
--   <a>dashboardVersion_description</a> - Description.
newDashboardVersion :: DashboardVersion

dashboardVersion_status :: Lens' DashboardVersion (Maybe ResourceStatus)

-- | The ARN of the theme associated with a version of the dashboard.
dashboardVersion_themeArn :: Lens' DashboardVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Numbers (ARNs) for the datasets that are
--   associated with this version of the dashboard.
dashboardVersion_dataSetArns :: Lens' DashboardVersion (Maybe [Text])

--   each sheet.
dashboardVersion_sheets :: Lens' DashboardVersion (Maybe [Sheet])

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
dashboardVersion_arn :: Lens' DashboardVersion (Maybe Text)

-- | Source entity ARN.

-- | Version number for this version of the dashboard.

-- | Errors associated with this dashboard version.

dashboardVersion_description :: Lens' DashboardVersion (Maybe Text)

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Dashboard

-- | Dashboard.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDashboard</a> smart constructor.
data Dashboard
Dashboard' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DashboardVersion -> Dashboard

-- | The last time that this dataset was updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Dashboard'] :: Dashboard -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:Dashboard'] :: Dashboard -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that this dataset was created.
[$sel:createdTime:Dashboard'] :: Dashboard -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Dashboard ID.
[$sel:dashboardId:Dashboard'] :: Dashboard -> Maybe Text

-- | The last time that this dataset was published.
[$sel:lastPublishedTime:Dashboard'] :: Dashboard -> Maybe POSIX

-- | A display name for the dashboard.
[$sel:name:Dashboard'] :: Dashboard -> Maybe Text

-- | Version.
[$sel:version:Dashboard'] :: Dashboard -> Maybe DashboardVersion

--

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Dashboard'</a>, <a>dashboard_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Dashboard'</a>, <a>dashboard_createdTime</a> - The
--   time that this dataset was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dashboardId:Dashboard'</a>, <a>dashboard_dashboardId</a> -
--   Dashboard ID.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastPublishedTime:Dashboard'</a>,
--   <a>dashboard_lastPublishedTime</a> - The last time that this dataset
--   was published.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Dashboard'</a>, <a>dashboard_name</a> - A display name
--   for the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:version:Dashboard'</a>, <a>dashboard_version</a> - Version.
newDashboard :: Dashboard
