module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Analysis

-- | Metadata structure for an analysis in Amazon QuickSight
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAnalysis</a> smart constructor.
data Analysis
Analysis' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe [Sheet] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (NonEmpty AnalysisError) -> Analysis

-- | Status associated with the analysis.
[$sel:status:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The ARN of the theme of the analysis.
[$sel:themeArn:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARNs of the datasets of the analysis.
[$sel:dataSetArns:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe [Text]

-- | A list of the associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of
--   each sheet.
[$sel:sheets:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe [Sheet]

-- | The ID of the analysis.
[$sel:analysisId:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that the analysis was last updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the analysis.
[$sel:arn:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that the analysis was created.
[$sel:createdTime:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The descriptive name of the analysis.
[$sel:name:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | Errors associated with the analysis.
[$sel:errors:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe (NonEmpty AnalysisError)

-- | Create a value of <a>Analysis</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_status</a> - Status
--   associated with the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeArn:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_themeArn</a> - The ARN of
--   the theme of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetArns:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_dataSetArns</a> - The
--   ARNs of the datasets of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sheets:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_sheets</a> - A list of the
--   associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of each sheet.
--   
--   <a>$sel:analysisId:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_analysisId</a> - The ID
--   of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_lastUpdatedTime</a>
--   - The time that the analysis was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_createdTime</a> - The
--   time that the analysis was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_name</a> - The descriptive
--   name of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errors:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_errors</a> - Errors
--   associated with the analysis.
newAnalysis :: Analysis

-- | Status associated with the analysis.
analysis_status :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe ResourceStatus)

-- | The ARN of the theme of the analysis.
analysis_themeArn :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe Text)

-- | The ARNs of the datasets of the analysis.
analysis_dataSetArns :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe [Text])

-- | A list of the associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of
--   each sheet.
analysis_sheets :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe [Sheet])

-- | The ID of the analysis.
analysis_analysisId :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that the analysis was last updated.
analysis_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the analysis.
analysis_arn :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that the analysis was created.
analysis_createdTime :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The descriptive name of the analysis.
analysis_name :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe Text)

-- | Errors associated with the analysis.
analysis_errors :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe (NonEmpty AnalysisError))

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | Information about a dataset that contains permissions for row-level
--   security (RLS). The permissions dataset maps fields to users or
--   groups. For more information, see <a>Using Row-Level Security (RLS) to
--   Restrict Access to a Dataset</a> in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User
--   Guide</i>.
--   
--   The option to deny permissions by setting <tt>PermissionPolicy</tt> to
--   <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is not supported for new RLS datasets.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> smart constructor.
data RowLevelPermissionDataSet
RowLevelPermissionDataSet' :: Maybe Status -> Maybe Text -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionFormatVersion -> Text -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy -> RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | The status of the row-level security permission dataset. If enabled,
--   the status is <tt>ENABLED</tt>. If disabled, the status is
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>.
[$sel:status:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe Status

-- | The namespace associated with the dataset that contains permissions
--   for RLS.
[$sel:namespace:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | The user or group rules associated with the dataset that contains
--   permissions for RLS.
--   
--   By default, <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>. When
--   <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>, <tt>UserName</tt> and
--   <tt>GroupName</tt> are required. When <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is
--   <tt>VERSION_2</tt>, <tt>UserARN</tt> and <tt>GroupARN</tt> are
--   required, and <tt>Namespace</tt> must not exist.
[$sel:formatVersion:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionFormatVersion

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the dataset that contains
--   permissions for RLS.
[$sel:arn:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Text

-- | The type of permissions to use when interpreting the permissions for
--   RLS. <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is included for backward compatibility only.
[$sel:permissionPolicy:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy

-- | Create a value of <a>RowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_status</a> - The status of the row-level
--   security permission dataset. If enabled, the status is
--   <tt>ENABLED</tt>. If disabled, the status is <tt>DISABLED</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_namespace</a> - The namespace associated
--   with the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   <a>$sel:formatVersion:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_formatVersion</a> - The user or group
--   rules associated with the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   By default, <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>. When
--   <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>, <tt>UserName</tt> and
--   <tt>GroupName</tt> are required. When <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is
--   <tt>VERSION_2</tt>, <tt>UserARN</tt> and <tt>GroupARN</tt> are
--   required, and <tt>Namespace</tt> must not exist.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   of the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   <a>$sel:permissionPolicy:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_permissionPolicy</a> - The type of
--   permissions to use when interpreting the permissions for RLS.
--   <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is included for backward compatibility only.
newRowLevelPermissionDataSet :: Text -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy -> RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | The status of the row-level security permission dataset. If enabled,
--   the status is <tt>ENABLED</tt>. If disabled, the status is
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>.
rowLevelPermissionDataSet_status :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionDataSet (Maybe Status)

-- | The namespace associated with the dataset that contains permissions
--   for RLS.
rowLevelPermissionDataSet_namespace :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionDataSet (Maybe Text)

-- | The user or group rules associated with the dataset that contains
--   permissions for RLS.
--   
--   By default, <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>. When
--   <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>, <tt>UserName</tt> and
--   <tt>GroupName</tt> are required. When <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is
--   <tt>VERSION_2</tt>, <tt>UserARN</tt> and <tt>GroupARN</tt> are
--   required, and <tt>Namespace</tt> must not exist.
rowLevelPermissionDataSet_formatVersion :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionDataSet (Maybe RowLevelPermissionFormatVersion)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the dataset that contains
--   permissions for RLS.
rowLevelPermissionDataSet_arn :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionDataSet Text

-- | The type of permissions to use when interpreting the permissions for
--   RLS. <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is included for backward compatibility only.
rowLevelPermissionDataSet_permissionPolicy :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionDataSet RowLevelPermissionPolicy
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.RowLevelPermissionDataSet.RowLevelPermissionDataSet

--   type of integer.

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TemplateVersion

-- | A version of a template.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTemplateVersion</a> smart constructor.
data TemplateVersion
TemplateVersion' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Sheet] -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [DataSetConfiguration] -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe (NonEmpty TemplateError) -> Maybe Text -> TemplateVersion

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
[$sel:status:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The ARN of the theme associated with this version of the template.
[$sel:themeArn:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of the associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of
--   each sheet.

-- | The time that this template version was created.
[$sel:createdTime:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an analysis or template that was
--   used to create this template.
[$sel:sourceEntityArn:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | Schema of the dataset identified by the placeholder. Any dashboard
--   created from this template should be bound to new datasets matching
--   the same schema described through this API operation.
[$sel:dataSetConfigurations:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe [DataSetConfiguration]

-- | The version number of the template version.
[$sel:versionNumber:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe Natural

-- | Errors associated with this template version.
[$sel:errors:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe (NonEmpty TemplateError)

-- | The description of the template.
[$sel:description:TemplateVersion'] :: TemplateVersion -> Maybe Text

--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   The HTTP status of the request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeArn:TemplateVersion'</a>, <a>templateVersion_themeArn</a>
--   - The ARN of the theme associated with this version of the template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sheets:TemplateVersion'</a>, <a>templateVersion_sheets</a> - A
--   list of the associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of
--   each sheet.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:TemplateVersion'</a>,
--   <a>templateVersion_createdTime</a> - The time that this template
--   version was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceEntityArn:TemplateVersion'</a>,
--   <a>templateVersion_sourceEntityArn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) of an analysis or template that was used to create this
--   template.
--

--   <a>templateVersion_dataSetConfigurations</a> - Schema of the dataset

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template

-- | A template object. A <i>template</i> is an entity in Amazon QuickSight
--   that encapsulates the metadata required to create an analysis and that
--   you can use to create a dashboard. A template adds a layer of
--   abstraction by using placeholders to replace the dataset associated
--   with an analysis. You can use templates to create dashboards by
--   replacing dataset placeholders with datasets that follow the same
--   schema that was used to create the source analysis and template.
--   
--   You can share templates across Amazon Web Services accounts by
--   allowing users in other Amazon Web Services accounts to create a
--   template or a dashboard from an existing template.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTemplate</a> smart constructor.
data Template
Template' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe TemplateVersion -> Template

-- | Time when this was last updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the template.
[$sel:arn:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe Text

-- | Time when this was created.
[$sel:createdTime:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The ID for the template. This is unique per Amazon Web Services Region
--   for each Amazon Web Services account.
[$sel:templateId:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe Text

-- | The display name of the template.
[$sel:name:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe Text

-- | A structure describing the versions of the template.
[$sel:version:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe TemplateVersion

-- | Create a value of <a>Template</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Template'</a>, <a>template_lastUpdatedTime</a>
--   - Time when this was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Template'</a>, <a>template_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Template'</a>, <a>template_createdTime</a> - Time
--   when this was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateId:Template'</a>, <a>template_templateId</a> - The ID
--   for the template. This is unique per Amazon Web Services Region for
--   each Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Template'</a>, <a>template_name</a> - The display name of
--   the template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:version:Template'</a>, <a>template_version</a> - A structure
--   describing the versions of the template.
newTemplate :: Template

-- | Time when this was last updated.
template_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' Template (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the template.
template_arn :: Lens' Template (Maybe Text)

-- | Time when this was created.
template_createdTime :: Lens' Template (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The ID for the template. This is unique per Amazon Web Services Region
--   for each Amazon Web Services account.
template_templateId :: Lens' Template (Maybe Text)

-- | The display name of the template.
template_name :: Lens' Template (Maybe Text)

-- | A structure describing the versions of the template.
template_version :: Lens' Template (Maybe TemplateVersion)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template.Template
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template.Template
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template.Template
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template.Template
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template.Template
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template.Template
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Template.Template

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeSummary

-- | The theme summary.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newThemeSummary</a> smart constructor.
data ThemeSummary
ThemeSummary' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> ThemeSummary

-- | The ID of the theme. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services Region
--   for each Amazon Web Services account.
[$sel:themeId:ThemeSummary'] :: ThemeSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The last date and time that this theme was updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:ThemeSummary'] :: ThemeSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The latest version number for the theme.
[$sel:latestVersionNumber:ThemeSummary'] :: ThemeSummary -> Maybe Natural

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:ThemeSummary'] :: ThemeSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The date and time that this theme was created.
[$sel:createdTime:ThemeSummary'] :: ThemeSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | the display name for the theme.
[$sel:name:ThemeSummary'] :: ThemeSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ThemeSummary</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeId:ThemeSummary'</a>, <a>themeSummary_themeId</a> - The
--   ID of the theme. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services Region for
--   each Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:ThemeSummary'</a>,
--   <a>themeSummary_lastUpdatedTime</a> - The last date and time that this
--   theme was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:latestVersionNumber:ThemeSummary'</a>,
--   <a>themeSummary_latestVersionNumber</a> - The latest version number
--   for the theme.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:ThemeSummary'</a>, <a>themeSummary_arn</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:ThemeSummary'</a>, <a>themeSummary_createdTime</a>
--   - The date and time that this theme was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:ThemeSummary'</a>, <a>themeSummary_name</a> - the display
--   name for the theme.
newThemeSummary :: ThemeSummary

-- | The ID of the theme. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services Region
--   for each Amazon Web Services account.
themeSummary_themeId :: Lens' ThemeSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | The last date and time that this theme was updated.
themeSummary_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' ThemeSummary (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The latest version number for the theme.
themeSummary_latestVersionNumber :: Lens' ThemeSummary (Maybe Natural)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
themeSummary_arn :: Lens' ThemeSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | The date and time that this theme was created.
themeSummary_createdTime :: Lens' ThemeSummary (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | the display name for the theme.
themeSummary_name :: Lens' ThemeSummary (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeSummary.ThemeSummary
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeSummary.ThemeSummary
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeSummary.ThemeSummary
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeSummary.ThemeSummary

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceParameters

-- | The parameters that Amazon QuickSight uses to connect to your
--   underlying data source. This is a variant type structure. For this
--   structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSourceParameters</a> smart constructor.
data DataSourceParameters
DataSourceParameters' :: Maybe RdsParameters -> Maybe S3Parameters -> Maybe AthenaParameters -> Maybe TeradataParameters -> Maybe AuroraParameters -> Maybe AwsIotAnalyticsParameters -> Maybe AmazonOpenSearchParameters -> Maybe SqlServerParameters -> Maybe RedshiftParameters -> Maybe PostgreSqlParameters -> Maybe OracleParameters -> Maybe AmazonElasticsearchParameters -> Maybe TwitterParameters -> Maybe MariaDbParameters -> Maybe JiraParameters -> Maybe SnowflakeParameters -> Maybe PrestoParameters -> Maybe MySqlParameters -> Maybe AuroraPostgreSqlParameters -> Maybe SparkParameters -> Maybe ServiceNowParameters -> DataSourceParameters

-- | The parameters for Amazon RDS.
[$sel:rdsParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe RdsParameters

-- | The parameters for S3.
[$sel:s3Parameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe S3Parameters

-- | The parameters for Amazon Athena.
[$sel:athenaParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe AthenaParameters

-- | The parameters for Teradata.
[$sel:teradataParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe TeradataParameters

-- | The parameters for Amazon Aurora MySQL.
[$sel:auroraParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe AuroraParameters

-- | The parameters for IoT Analytics.
[$sel:awsIotAnalyticsParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe AwsIotAnalyticsParameters
[$sel:amazonOpenSearchParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe AmazonOpenSearchParameters

-- | The parameters for SQL Server.
[$sel:sqlServerParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe SqlServerParameters

-- | The parameters for Amazon Redshift.
[$sel:redshiftParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe RedshiftParameters

-- | The parameters for PostgreSQL.
[$sel:postgreSqlParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe PostgreSqlParameters

-- | The parameters for Oracle.
[$sel:oracleParameters:DataSourceParameters'] :: DataSourceParameters -> Maybe OracleParameters

-- | The parameters for OpenSearch.

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair

-- | The combination of user name and password that are used as
--   credentials.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCredentialPair</a> smart constructor.
data CredentialPair
CredentialPair' :: Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters) -> Text -> Text -> CredentialPair

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   these credentials. The credentials are applied in tandem with the data
--   source parameters when you copy a data source by using a create or
--   update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the new data source with the existing credentials. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> originally used with these
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> is automatically allowed.
[$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:CredentialPair'] :: CredentialPair -> Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters)

-- | User name.
[$sel:username:CredentialPair'] :: CredentialPair -> Text

-- | Password.
[$sel:password:CredentialPair'] :: CredentialPair -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>CredentialPair</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:CredentialPair'</a>,
--   <a>credentialPair_alternateDataSourceParameters</a> - A set of
--   alternate data source parameters that you want to share for these
--   credentials. The credentials are applied in tandem with the data
--   source parameters when you copy a data source by using a create or
--   update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the new data source with the existing credentials. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> originally used with these
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> is automatically allowed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:username:CredentialPair'</a>, <a>credentialPair_username</a> -
--   User name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:password:CredentialPair'</a>, <a>credentialPair_password</a> -
--   Password.
newCredentialPair :: Text -> Text -> CredentialPair

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   these credentials. The credentials are applied in tandem with the data
--   source parameters when you copy a data source by using a create or
--   update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the new data source with the existing credentials. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> originally used with these
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> is automatically allowed.
credentialPair_alternateDataSourceParameters :: Lens' CredentialPair (Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters))

-- | User name.
credentialPair_username :: Lens' CredentialPair Text

-- | Password.
credentialPair_password :: Lens' CredentialPair Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair.CredentialPair
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair.CredentialPair
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair.CredentialPair
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair.CredentialPair
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair.CredentialPair
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair.CredentialPair
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.CredentialPair.CredentialPair


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceCredentials

-- | Data source credentials. This is a variant type structure. For this
--   structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSourceCredentials</a> smart constructor.
data DataSourceCredentials
DataSourceCredentials' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe CredentialPair -> DataSourceCredentials

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a data source that has the
--   credential pair that you want to use. When <tt>CopySourceArn</tt> is
--   not null, the credential pair from the data source in the ARN is used
--   as the credentials for the <tt>DataSourceCredentials</tt> structure.
[$sel:copySourceArn:DataSourceCredentials'] :: DataSourceCredentials -> Maybe Text

-- | Credential pair. For more information, see CredentialPair.
[$sel:credentialPair:DataSourceCredentials'] :: DataSourceCredentials -> Maybe CredentialPair

-- | Create a value of <a>DataSourceCredentials</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:copySourceArn:DataSourceCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>dataSourceCredentials_copySourceArn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) of a data source that has the credential pair that you want to
--   use. When <tt>CopySourceArn</tt> is not null, the credential pair from
--   the data source in the ARN is used as the credentials for the
--   <tt>DataSourceCredentials</tt> structure.
--   
--   <a>$sel:credentialPair:DataSourceCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>dataSourceCredentials_credentialPair</a> - Credential pair. For
--   more information, see CredentialPair.
newDataSourceCredentials :: DataSourceCredentials

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a data source that has the
--   credential pair that you want to use. When <tt>CopySourceArn</tt> is
--   not null, the credential pair from the data source in the ARN is used
--   as the credentials for the <tt>DataSourceCredentials</tt> structure.
dataSourceCredentials_copySourceArn :: Lens' DataSourceCredentials (Maybe Text)

-- | Credential pair. For more information, see CredentialPair.
dataSourceCredentials_credentialPair :: Lens' DataSourceCredentials (Maybe CredentialPair)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceCredentials.DataSourceCredentials
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceCredentials.DataSourceCredentials
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceCredentials.DataSourceCredentials
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceCredentials.DataSourceCredentials
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceCredentials.DataSourceCredentials
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSourceCredentials.DataSourceCredentials


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.UIColorPalette

-- | The theme colors that apply to UI and to charts, excluding data
--   colors. The colors description is a hexadecimal color code that
--   consists of six alphanumerical characters, prefixed with <tt>#</tt>,
--   for example #37BFF5. For more information, see <a>Using Themes in
--   Amazon QuickSight</a> in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide.</i>
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUIColorPalette</a> smart constructor.
data UIColorPalette
UIColorPalette' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> UIColorPalette

-- | The background color that applies to the sheet background and sheet
--   controls.
[$sel:secondaryBackground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the success color.
[$sel:successForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color that applies to the names of fields that are identified as
--   dimensions.
[$sel:dimension:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the dimension color.
[$sel:dimensionForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color that applies to success messages, for example the check mark
--   for a successful download.
[$sel:success:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | This color is that applies to selected states and buttons.
[$sel:accent:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any sheet title, sheet control
--   text, or UI that appears over the secondary background.
[$sel:secondaryForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color of text and other foreground elements that appear over the
--   primary background regions, such as grid lines, borders, table
--   banding, icons, and so on.
[$sel:primaryForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | This color that applies to warning and informational messages.
[$sel:warning:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The background color that applies to visuals and other high emphasis
--   UI.
[$sel:primaryBackground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the accent color.
[$sel:accentForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color that applies to the names of fields that are identified as
--   measures.
[$sel:measure:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the error color.
[$sel:dangerForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the measure color.
[$sel:measureForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color that applies to error messages.
[$sel:danger:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the warning color.
[$sel:warningForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>UIColorPalette</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:secondaryBackground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_secondaryBackground</a> - The background color that
--   applies to the sheet background and sheet controls.
--   
--   <a>$sel:successForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_successForeground</a> - The foreground color that
--   applies to any text or other elements that appear over the success
--   color.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dimension:UIColorPalette'</a>, <a>uIColorPalette_dimension</a>
--   - The color that applies to the names of fields that are identified as
--   dimensions.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dimensionForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_dimensionForeground</a> - The foreground color that
--   applies to any text or other elements that appear over the dimension
--   color.
--   
--   <a>$sel:success:UIColorPalette'</a>, <a>uIColorPalette_success</a> -
--   The color that applies to success messages, for example the check mark
--   for a successful download.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accent:UIColorPalette'</a>, <a>uIColorPalette_accent</a> -
--   This color is that applies to selected states and buttons.
--   
--   <a>$sel:secondaryForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_secondaryForeground</a> - The foreground color that
--   applies to any sheet title, sheet control text, or UI that appears
--   over the secondary background.
--   
--   <a>$sel:primaryForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_primaryForeground</a> - The color of text and other
--   foreground elements that appear over the primary background regions,
--   such as grid lines, borders, table banding, icons, and so on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:warning:UIColorPalette'</a>, <a>uIColorPalette_warning</a> -
--   This color that applies to warning and informational messages.
--   
--   <a>$sel:primaryBackground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_primaryBackground</a> - The background color that
--   applies to visuals and other high emphasis UI.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accentForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_accentForeground</a> - The foreground color that
--   applies to any text or other elements that appear over the accent
--   color.
--   
--   <a>$sel:measure:UIColorPalette'</a>, <a>uIColorPalette_measure</a> -
--   The color that applies to the names of fields that are identified as
--   measures.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dangerForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_dangerForeground</a> - The foreground color that
--   applies to any text or other elements that appear over the error
--   color.
--   
--   <a>$sel:measureForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_measureForeground</a> - The foreground color that
--   applies to any text or other elements that appear over the measure
--   color.
--   
--   <a>$sel:danger:UIColorPalette'</a>, <a>uIColorPalette_danger</a> - The
--   color that applies to error messages.
--   
--   <a>$sel:warningForeground:UIColorPalette'</a>,
--   <a>uIColorPalette_warningForeground</a> - The foreground color that
--   applies to any text or other elements that appear over the warning
--   color.
newUIColorPalette :: UIColorPalette

--   controls.

--   appear over the success color.

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration

-- | The theme configuration. This configuration contains all of the
--   display properties for a theme.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newThemeConfiguration</a> smart constructor.
data ThemeConfiguration
ThemeConfiguration' :: Maybe UIColorPalette -> Maybe SheetStyle -> Maybe DataColorPalette -> ThemeConfiguration

-- | Color properties that apply to the UI and to charts, excluding the
--   colors that apply to data.
[$sel:uIColorPalette:ThemeConfiguration'] :: ThemeConfiguration -> Maybe UIColorPalette

-- | Display options related to sheets.
[$sel:sheet:ThemeConfiguration'] :: ThemeConfiguration -> Maybe SheetStyle

-- | Color properties that apply to chart data colors.
[$sel:dataColorPalette:ThemeConfiguration'] :: ThemeConfiguration -> Maybe DataColorPalette

-- | Create a value of <a>ThemeConfiguration</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:uIColorPalette:ThemeConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>themeConfiguration_uIColorPalette</a> - Color properties that apply
--   to the UI and to charts, excluding the colors that apply to data.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sheet:ThemeConfiguration'</a>, <a>themeConfiguration_sheet</a>
--   - Display options related to sheets.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataColorPalette:ThemeConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>themeConfiguration_dataColorPalette</a> - Color properties that
--   apply to chart data colors.
newThemeConfiguration :: ThemeConfiguration

-- | Color properties that apply to the UI and to charts, excluding the
--   colors that apply to data.
themeConfiguration_uIColorPalette :: Lens' ThemeConfiguration (Maybe UIColorPalette)

-- | Display options related to sheets.
themeConfiguration_sheet :: Lens' ThemeConfiguration (Maybe SheetStyle)

-- | Color properties that apply to chart data colors.
themeConfiguration_dataColorPalette :: Lens' ThemeConfiguration (Maybe DataColorPalette)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeConfiguration.ThemeConfiguration


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.ThemeVersion

-- | A version of a theme.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newThemeVersion</a> smart constructor.
data ThemeVersion
ThemeVersion' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe ThemeConfiguration -> Maybe (NonEmpty ThemeError) -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ThemeVersion

-- | The status of the theme version.
[$sel:status:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | The date and time that this theme version was created.
[$sel:createdTime:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The version number of the theme.
[$sel:versionNumber:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe Natural

-- | The theme configuration, which contains all the theme display
--   properties.
[$sel:configuration:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe ThemeConfiguration

-- | Errors associated with the theme.
[$sel:errors:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe (NonEmpty ThemeError)

-- | The description of the theme.
[$sel:description:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight-defined ID of the theme that a custom theme
--   inherits from. All themes initially inherit from a default Amazon
--   QuickSight theme.
[$sel:baseThemeId:ThemeVersion'] :: ThemeVersion -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ThemeVersion</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:ThemeVersion'</a>, <a>themeVersion_status</a> - The
--   status of the theme version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:ThemeVersion'</a>, <a>themeVersion_arn</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:ThemeVersion'</a>, <a>themeVersion_createdTime</a>
--   - The date and time that this theme version was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionNumber:ThemeVersion'</a>,
--   <a>themeVersion_versionNumber</a> - The version number of the theme.
--   
--   <a>$sel:configuration:ThemeVersion'</a>,
--   <a>themeVersion_configuration</a> - The theme configuration, which
--   contains all the theme display properties.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errors:ThemeVersion'</a>, <a>themeVersion_errors</a> - Errors
--   associated with the theme.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ThemeVersion'</a>, <a>themeVersion_description</a>
--   - The description of the theme.
--   
--   <a>$sel:baseThemeId:ThemeVersion'</a>, <a>themeVersion_baseThemeId</a>
--   - The Amazon QuickSight-defined ID of the theme that a custom theme
--   inherits from. All themes initially inherit from a default Amazon
--   QuickSight theme.
newThemeVersion :: ThemeVersion

-- | The status of the theme version.
themeVersion_status :: Lens' ThemeVersion (Maybe ResourceStatus)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.

-- | The date and time that this theme version was created.
themeVersion_createdTime :: Lens' ThemeVersion (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The version number of the theme.
themeVersion_versionNumber :: Lens' ThemeVersion (Maybe Natural)

-- | The theme configuration, which contains all the theme display
--   properties.
themeVersion_configuration :: Lens' ThemeVersion (Maybe ThemeConfiguration)

-- | Errors associated with the theme.
themeVersion_errors :: Lens' ThemeVersion (Maybe (NonEmpty ThemeError))

-- | The description of the theme.

--   inherits from. All themes initially inherit from a default Amazon
--   QuickSight theme.
themeVersion_baseThemeId :: Lens' ThemeVersion (Maybe Text)

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.Theme

-- | Summary information about a theme.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTheme</a> smart constructor.
data Theme
Theme' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ThemeVersion -> Maybe ThemeType -> Theme

-- | The identifier that the user gives to the theme.
[$sel:themeId:Theme'] :: Theme -> Maybe Text

-- | The date and time that the theme was last updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Theme'] :: Theme -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme.
[$sel:arn:Theme'] :: Theme -> Maybe Text

-- | The date and time that the theme was created.
[$sel:createdTime:Theme'] :: Theme -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The name that the user gives to the theme.
[$sel:name:Theme'] :: Theme -> Maybe Text
[$sel:version:Theme'] :: Theme -> Maybe ThemeVersion

-- | The type of theme, based on how it was created. Valid values include:
--   <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt> and <tt>CUSTOM</tt>.
[$sel:type':Theme'] :: Theme -> Maybe ThemeType

-- | Create a value of <a>Theme</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

--   the user gives to the theme.
--

--   date and time that the theme was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Theme'</a>, <a>theme_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) of the theme.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Theme'</a>, <a>theme_createdTime</a> - The date
--   and time that the theme was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Theme'</a>, <a>theme_name</a> - The name that the user

--   member.

--   <a>$sel:type':Theme'</a>, <a>theme_type</a> - The type of theme, based
--   on how it was created. Valid values include: <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt> and
--   <tt>CUSTOM</tt>.
newTheme :: Theme

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation

-- | A data transformation on a logical table. This is a variant type
--   structure. For this structure to be valid, only one of the attributes
--   can be non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTransformOperation</a> smart constructor.
data TransformOperation
TransformOperation' :: Maybe CastColumnTypeOperation -> Maybe TagColumnOperation -> Maybe CreateColumnsOperation -> Maybe UntagColumnOperation -> Maybe FilterOperation -> Maybe ProjectOperation -> Maybe RenameColumnOperation -> TransformOperation

-- | A transform operation that casts a column to a different type.
[$sel:castColumnTypeOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe CastColumnTypeOperation

-- | An operation that tags a column with additional information.
[$sel:tagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe TagColumnOperation

-- | An operation that creates calculated columns. Columns created in one
--   such operation form a lexical closure.
[$sel:createColumnsOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe CreateColumnsOperation
[$sel:untagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe UntagColumnOperation

-- | An operation that filters rows based on some condition.
[$sel:filterOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe FilterOperation

-- | An operation that projects columns. Operations that come after a
--   projection can only refer to projected columns.
[$sel:projectOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe ProjectOperation

-- | An operation that renames a column.
[$sel:renameColumnOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe RenameColumnOperation

-- | Create a value of <a>TransformOperation</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:castColumnTypeOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_castColumnTypeOperation</a> - A transform
--   operation that casts a column to a different type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_tagColumnOperation</a> - An operation that tags
--   a column with additional information.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createColumnsOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_createColumnsOperation</a> - An operation that
--   creates calculated columns. Columns created in one such operation form
--   a lexical closure.
--   
--   <a>$sel:untagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_untagColumnOperation</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:filterOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_filterOperation</a> - An operation that filters
--   rows based on some condition.
--   
--   <a>$sel:projectOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_projectOperation</a> - An operation that
--   projects columns. Operations that come after a projection can only
--   refer to projected columns.
--   
--   <a>$sel:renameColumnOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_renameColumnOperation</a> - An operation that
--   renames a column.
newTransformOperation :: TransformOperation

-- | A transform operation that casts a column to a different type.
transformOperation_castColumnTypeOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe CastColumnTypeOperation)

-- | An operation that tags a column with additional information.
transformOperation_tagColumnOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe TagColumnOperation)

-- | An operation that creates calculated columns. Columns created in one
--   such operation form a lexical closure.
transformOperation_createColumnsOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe CreateColumnsOperation)

-- | Undocumented member.
transformOperation_untagColumnOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe UntagColumnOperation)

-- | An operation that filters rows based on some condition.
transformOperation_filterOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe FilterOperation)

-- | An operation that projects columns. Operations that come after a
--   projection can only refer to projected columns.
transformOperation_projectOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe ProjectOperation)

-- | An operation that renames a column.
transformOperation_renameColumnOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe RenameColumnOperation)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.TransformOperation.TransformOperation


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable

-- | A <i>logical table</i> is a unit that joins and that data
--   transformations operate on. A logical table has a source, which can be
--   either a physical table or result of a join. When a logical table
--   points to a physical table, the logical table acts as a mutable copy
--   of that physical table through transform operations.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newLogicalTable</a> smart constructor.
data LogicalTable
LogicalTable' :: Maybe (NonEmpty TransformOperation) -> Text -> LogicalTableSource -> LogicalTable

-- | Transform operations that act on this logical table.
[$sel:dataTransforms:LogicalTable'] :: LogicalTable -> Maybe (NonEmpty TransformOperation)

-- | A display name for the logical table.
[$sel:alias:LogicalTable'] :: LogicalTable -> Text

-- | Source of this logical table.
[$sel:source:LogicalTable'] :: LogicalTable -> LogicalTableSource

-- | Create a value of <a>LogicalTable</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataTransforms:LogicalTable'</a>,
--   <a>logicalTable_dataTransforms</a> - Transform operations that act on
--   this logical table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:alias:LogicalTable'</a>, <a>logicalTable_alias</a> - A display
--   name for the logical table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:source:LogicalTable'</a>, <a>logicalTable_source</a> - Source
--   of this logical table.
newLogicalTable :: Text -> LogicalTableSource -> LogicalTable

-- | Transform operations that act on this logical table.
logicalTable_dataTransforms :: Lens' LogicalTable (Maybe (NonEmpty TransformOperation))

-- | A display name for the logical table.
logicalTable_alias :: Lens' LogicalTable Text

-- | Source of this logical table.
logicalTable_source :: Lens' LogicalTable LogicalTableSource
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.LogicalTable.LogicalTable


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.UploadSettings

-- | Information about the format for a source file or files.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUploadSettings</a> smart constructor.
data UploadSettings

-- | A row number to start reading data from.
[$sel:startFromRow:UploadSettings'] :: UploadSettings -> Maybe Natural

--   row.

[$sel:textQualifier:UploadSettings'] :: UploadSettings -> Maybe TextQualifier

-- | File format.

--   <a>uploadSettings_textQualifier</a> - Text qualifier.
--   
--   <a>$sel:format:UploadSettings'</a>, <a>uploadSettings_format</a> -
--   File format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:delimiter:UploadSettings'</a>, <a>uploadSettings_delimiter</a>
--   - The delimiter between values in the file.
newUploadSettings :: UploadSettings

-- | A row number to start reading data from.

--   row.

--   physical table type for an S3 data source.
--   
--   For files that aren't JSON, only <tt>STRING</tt> data types are
--   supported in input columns.

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable

-- | A view of a data source that contains information about the shape of
--   the data in the underlying source. This is a variant type structure.
--   For this structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be
--   non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPhysicalTable</a> smart constructor.
data PhysicalTable
PhysicalTable' :: Maybe S3Source -> Maybe RelationalTable -> Maybe CustomSql -> PhysicalTable

-- | A physical table type for as S3 data source.
[$sel:s3Source:PhysicalTable'] :: PhysicalTable -> Maybe S3Source

-- | A physical table type for relational data sources.
[$sel:relationalTable:PhysicalTable'] :: PhysicalTable -> Maybe RelationalTable

-- | A physical table type built from the results of the custom SQL query.
[$sel:customSql:PhysicalTable'] :: PhysicalTable -> Maybe CustomSql

-- | Create a value of <a>PhysicalTable</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:s3Source:PhysicalTable'</a>, <a>physicalTable_s3Source</a> - A
--   physical table type for as S3 data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:relationalTable:PhysicalTable'</a>,
--   <a>physicalTable_relationalTable</a> - A physical table type for
--   relational data sources.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customSql:PhysicalTable'</a>, <a>physicalTable_customSql</a> -
--   A physical table type built from the results of the custom SQL query.
newPhysicalTable :: PhysicalTable

-- | A physical table type for as S3 data source.
physicalTable_s3Source :: Lens' PhysicalTable (Maybe S3Source)

-- | A physical table type for relational data sources.
physicalTable_relationalTable :: Lens' PhysicalTable (Maybe RelationalTable)

-- | A physical table type built from the results of the custom SQL query.
physicalTable_customSql :: Lens' PhysicalTable (Maybe CustomSql)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.PhysicalTable.PhysicalTable


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSet

-- | Dataset.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSet</a> smart constructor.
data DataSet
DataSet' :: Maybe (HashMap Text FieldFolder) -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnGroup) -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe DataSetImportMode -> Maybe (HashMap Text PhysicalTable) -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DataSetUsageConfiguration -> Maybe [OutputColumn] -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule) -> Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable) -> DataSet

-- | The folder that contains fields and nested subfolders for your
--   dataset.
[$sel:fieldFolders:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text FieldFolder)

-- | Groupings of columns that work together in certain Amazon QuickSight
--   features. Currently, only geospatial hierarchy is supported.
[$sel:columnGroups:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnGroup)

-- | The last time that this dataset was updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that this dataset was created.
[$sel:createdTime:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The amount of SPICE capacity used by this dataset. This is 0 if the
--   dataset isn't imported into SPICE.
[$sel:consumedSpiceCapacityInBytes:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Integer

-- | A value that indicates whether you want to import the data into SPICE.
[$sel:importMode:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe DataSetImportMode

-- | Declares the physical tables that are available in the underlying data
--   sources.
[$sel:physicalTableMap:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text PhysicalTable)

-- | The ID of the dataset.
[$sel:dataSetId:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | A display name for the dataset.
[$sel:name:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | The usage configuration to apply to child datasets that reference this
--   dataset as a source.
[$sel:dataSetUsageConfiguration:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe DataSetUsageConfiguration

-- | The list of columns after all transforms. These columns are available
--   in templates, analyses, and dashboards.
[$sel:outputColumns:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe [OutputColumn]

-- | The element you can use to define tags for row-level security.
[$sel:rowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration

-- | The row-level security configuration for the dataset.
[$sel:rowLevelPermissionDataSet:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | A set of one or more definitions of a <tt> ColumnLevelPermissionRule
--   </tt>.
[$sel:columnLevelPermissionRules:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule)

-- | Configures the combination and transformation of the data from the
--   physical tables.
[$sel:logicalTableMap:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable)

-- | Create a value of <a>DataSet</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:fieldFolders:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_fieldFolders</a> - The
--   folder that contains fields and nested subfolders for your dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:columnGroups:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_columnGroups</a> -
--   Groupings of columns that work together in certain Amazon QuickSight
--   features. Currently, only geospatial hierarchy is supported.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_lastUpdatedTime</a> -
--   The last time that this dataset was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_createdTime</a> - The
--   time that this dataset was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:consumedSpiceCapacityInBytes:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_consumedSpiceCapacityInBytes</a> - The amount of SPICE
--   capacity used by this dataset. This is 0 if the dataset isn't imported
--   into SPICE.
--   
--   <a>$sel:importMode:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_importMode</a> - A value
--   that indicates whether you want to import the data into SPICE.
--   
--   <a>$sel:physicalTableMap:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_physicalTableMap</a>
--   - Declares the physical tables that are available in the underlying
--   data sources.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetId:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_dataSetId</a> - The ID of
--   the dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_name</a> - A display name for
--   the dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetUsageConfiguration:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_dataSetUsageConfiguration</a> - The usage configuration to
--   apply to child datasets that reference this dataset as a source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:outputColumns:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_outputColumns</a> - The
--   list of columns after all transforms. These columns are available in
--   templates, analyses, and dashboards.
--   
--   <a>$sel:rowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_rowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration</a> - The element you
--   can use to define tags for row-level security.
--   
--   <a>$sel:rowLevelPermissionDataSet:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_rowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> - The row-level security
--   configuration for the dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:columnLevelPermissionRules:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_columnLevelPermissionRules</a> - A set of one or more
--   definitions of a <tt> ColumnLevelPermissionRule </tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:logicalTableMap:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_logicalTableMap</a> -
--   Configures the combination and transformation of the data from the
--   physical tables.
newDataSet :: DataSet

-- | The folder that contains fields and nested subfolders for your
--   dataset.
dataSet_fieldFolders :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe (HashMap Text FieldFolder))

-- | Groupings of columns that work together in certain Amazon QuickSight
--   features. Currently, only geospatial hierarchy is supported.
dataSet_columnGroups :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnGroup))

-- | The last time that this dataset was updated.
dataSet_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
dataSet_arn :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that this dataset was created.
dataSet_createdTime :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The amount of SPICE capacity used by this dataset. This is 0 if the
--   dataset isn't imported into SPICE.
dataSet_consumedSpiceCapacityInBytes :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe Integer)

-- | A value that indicates whether you want to import the data into SPICE.
dataSet_importMode :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe DataSetImportMode)

-- | Declares the physical tables that are available in the underlying data
--   sources.
dataSet_physicalTableMap :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe (HashMap Text PhysicalTable))

-- | The ID of the dataset.
dataSet_dataSetId :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe Text)

-- | A display name for the dataset.
dataSet_name :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe Text)

-- | The usage configuration to apply to child datasets that reference this
--   dataset as a source.
dataSet_dataSetUsageConfiguration :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe DataSetUsageConfiguration)

-- | The list of columns after all transforms. These columns are available
--   in templates, analyses, and dashboards.
dataSet_outputColumns :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe [OutputColumn])

-- | The element you can use to define tags for row-level security.
dataSet_rowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe RowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration)

-- | The row-level security configuration for the dataset.
dataSet_rowLevelPermissionDataSet :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet)

-- | A set of one or more definitions of a <tt> ColumnLevelPermissionRule
--   </tt>.
dataSet_columnLevelPermissionRules :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule))

-- | Configures the combination and transformation of the data from the
--   physical tables.
dataSet_logicalTableMap :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable))
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSet.DataSet

module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User

-- | A registered user of Amazon QuickSight.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUser</a> smart constructor.
data User
User' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe IdentityType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe UserRole -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> User

-- | The user's email address.
[$sel:email:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The principal ID of the user.
[$sel:principalId:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the user.
[$sel:arn:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The user's user name.
[$sel:userName:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of identity authentication used by the user.
[$sel:identityType:User'] :: User -> Maybe IdentityType

-- | The URL of the external login provider.
[$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderUrl:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The custom permissions profile associated with this user.
[$sel:customPermissionsName:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The active status of user. When you create an Amazon QuickSight user
--   thats not an IAM user or an Active Directory user, that user is
--   inactive until they sign in and provide a password.
[$sel:active:User'] :: User -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon QuickSight role for the user. The user role can be one of
--   the following:.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:role':User'] :: User -> Maybe UserRole

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let the user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   IAMrole. The type can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The identity ID for the user in the external login provider.
[$sel:externalLoginId:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>User</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:email:User'</a>, <a>user_email</a> - The user's email address.
--   
--   <a>$sel:principalId:User'</a>, <a>user_principalId</a> - The principal
--   ID of the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:User'</a>, <a>user_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) for the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userName:User'</a>, <a>user_userName</a> - The user's user
--   name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:identityType:User'</a>, <a>user_identityType</a> - The type of
--   identity authentication used by the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderUrl:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_externalLoginFederationProviderUrl</a> - The URL of the
--   external login provider.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customPermissionsName:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_customPermissionsName</a> - The custom permissions profile
--   associated with this user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:active:User'</a>, <a>user_active</a> - The active status of
--   user. When you create an Amazon QuickSight user thats not an IAM user
--   or an Active Directory user, that user is inactive until they sign in
--   and provide a password.
--   
--   <a>$sel:role':User'</a>, <a>user_role</a> - The Amazon QuickSight role
--   for the user. The user role can be one of the following:.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_externalLoginFederationProviderType</a> - The type of
--   supported external login provider that provides identity to let the
--   user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated IAMrole. The
--   type can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginId:User'</a>, <a>user_externalLoginId</a> - The
--   identity ID for the user in the external login provider.
newUser :: User

-- | The user's email address.
user_email :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The principal ID of the user.
user_principalId :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the user.
user_arn :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The user's user name.
user_userName :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The type of identity authentication used by the user.
user_identityType :: Lens' User (Maybe IdentityType)

-- | The URL of the external login provider.
user_externalLoginFederationProviderUrl :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The custom permissions profile associated with this user.
user_customPermissionsName :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The active status of user. When you create an Amazon QuickSight user
--   thats not an IAM user or an Active Directory user, that user is
--   inactive until they sign in and provide a password.
user_active :: Lens' User (Maybe Bool)

-- | The Amazon QuickSight role for the user. The user role can be one of
--   the following:.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
user_role :: Lens' User (Maybe UserRole)

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let the user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   IAMrole. The type can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider.</li>
--   </ul>
user_externalLoginFederationProviderType :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The identity ID for the user in the external login provider.
user_externalLoginId :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User.User
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User.User
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User.User
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User.User
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User.User
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User.User
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.User.User


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.VpcConnectionProperties

data VpcConnectionProperties
VpcConnectionProperties' :: Text -> VpcConnectionProperties
