module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource

-- | The structure of a data source.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSource</a> smart constructor.
data DataSource
DataSource' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe DataSourceParameters -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe SslProperties -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters) -> Maybe VpcConnectionProperties -> Maybe DataSourceType -> Maybe DataSourceErrorInfo -> DataSource

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
[$sel:status:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The parameters that Amazon QuickSight uses to connect to your
--   underlying source. This is a variant type structure. For this
--   structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be non-null.
[$sel:dataSourceParameters:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe DataSourceParameters

-- | The last time that this data source was updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
[$sel:arn:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that this data source was created.
[$sel:createdTime:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Secure Socket Layer (SSL) properties that apply when Amazon QuickSight
--   connects to your underlying source.
[$sel:sslProperties:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe SslProperties

-- | The ID of the data source. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
[$sel:dataSourceId:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe Text

-- | A display name for the data source.
[$sel:name:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe Text

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   the credentials stored with this data source. The credentials are
--   applied in tandem with the data source parameters when you copy a data
--   source by using a create or update request. The API operation compares
--   the <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with
--   the structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow
--   list. If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to
--   use the credentials from this existing data source. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> originally used with this
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> are automatically allowed.
[$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters)

-- | The VPC connection information. You need to use this parameter only
--   when you want Amazon QuickSight to use a VPC connection when
--   connecting to your underlying source.
[$sel:vpcConnectionProperties:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe VpcConnectionProperties

-- | The type of the data source. This type indicates which database engine
--   the data source connects to.
[$sel:type':DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe DataSourceType

-- | Error information from the last update or the creation of the data
--   source.
[$sel:errorInfo:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe DataSourceErrorInfo

-- | Create a value of <a>DataSource</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_status</a> - The HTTP
--   status of the request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceParameters:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_dataSourceParameters</a> - The parameters that Amazon
--   QuickSight uses to connect to your underlying source. This is a
--   variant type structure. For this structure to be valid, only one of
--   the attributes can be non-null.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_lastUpdatedTime</a> - The last time that this data
--   source was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_arn</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_createdTime</a> -
--   The time that this data source was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sslProperties:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_sslProperties</a>
--   - Secure Socket Layer (SSL) properties that apply when Amazon
--   QuickSight connects to your underlying source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceId:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_dataSourceId</a> -
--   The ID of the data source. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_name</a> - A display name
--   for the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_alternateDataSourceParameters</a> - A set of alternate
--   data source parameters that you want to share for the credentials
--   stored with this data source. The credentials are applied in tandem
--   with the data source parameters when you copy a data source by using a
--   create or update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the credentials from this existing data source. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> originally used with this
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> are automatically allowed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcConnectionProperties:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_vpcConnectionProperties</a> - The VPC connection
--   information. You need to use this parameter only when you want Amazon
--   QuickSight to use a VPC connection when connecting to your underlying
--   source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_type</a> - The type of
--   the data source. This type indicates which database engine the data
--   source connects to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorInfo:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_errorInfo</a> - Error
--   information from the last update or the creation of the data source.
newDataSource :: DataSource

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
dataSource_status :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe ResourceStatus)

-- | The parameters that Amazon QuickSight uses to connect to your
--   underlying source. This is a variant type structure. For this
--   structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be non-null.
dataSource_dataSourceParameters :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe DataSourceParameters)

-- | The last time that this data source was updated.
dataSource_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
dataSource_arn :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that this data source was created.
dataSource_createdTime :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Secure Socket Layer (SSL) properties that apply when Amazon QuickSight
--   connects to your underlying source.
dataSource_sslProperties :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe SslProperties)

-- | The ID of the data source. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
dataSource_dataSourceId :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe Text)

-- | A display name for the data source.
dataSource_name :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe Text)

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   the credentials stored with this data source. The credentials are
--   applied in tandem with the data source parameters when you copy a data
--   source by using a create or update request. The API operation compares
--   the <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with
--   the structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow
--   list. If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to
--   use the credentials from this existing data source. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> originally used with this
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> are automatically allowed.
dataSource_alternateDataSourceParameters :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters))

-- | The VPC connection information. You need to use this parameter only
--   when you want Amazon QuickSight to use a VPC connection when
--   connecting to your underlying source.
dataSource_vpcConnectionProperties :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe VpcConnectionProperties)

-- | The type of the data source. This type indicates which database engine
--   the data source connects to.
dataSource_type :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe DataSourceType)

-- | Error information from the last update or the creation of the data
--   source.
dataSource_errorInfo :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe DataSourceErrorInfo)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource.DataSource
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource.DataSource
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource.DataSource
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource.DataSource
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource.DataSource
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource.DataSource
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types.DataSource.DataSource


module Network.AWS.QuickSight.Types

-- | API version <tt>2018-04-01</tt> of the Amazon QuickSight SDK
--   configuration.
defaultService :: Service

-- | You don't have access to this item. The provided credentials couldn't
--   be validated. You might not be authorized to carry out the request.
--   Make sure that your account is authorized to use the Amazon QuickSight
--   service, that your policies have the correct permissions, and that you
--   are using the correct access keys.
_AccessDeniedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | This resource is currently unavailable.
_ResourceUnavailableException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The identity type specified isn't supported. Supported identity types
--   include <tt>IAM</tt> and <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt>.
_IdentityTypeNotSupportedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The domain specified isn't on the allow list. All domains for embedded
--   dashboards must be added to the approved list by an Amazon QuickSight
--   admin.
_DomainNotWhitelistedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Updating or deleting a resource can cause an inconsistent state.
_ConflictException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | This error indicates that you are calling an embedding operation in
--   Amazon QuickSight without the required pricing plan on your Amazon Web
--   Services account. Before you can use embedding for anonymous users, a
--   Amazon QuickSight administrator needs to add capacity pricing to
--   Amazon QuickSight. You can do this on the <b>Manage Amazon
--   QuickSight</b> page.
--   
--   After capacity pricing is added, you can use the GetDashboardEmbedUrl
--   API operation with the <tt>--identity-type ANONYMOUS</tt> option.
_UnsupportedPricingPlanException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more parameters has a value that isn't valid.
_InvalidParameterValueException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | This error indicates that you are calling an operation on an Amazon
--   QuickSight subscription where the edition doesn't include support for
--   that operation. Amazon Amazon QuickSight currently has Standard
--   Edition and Enterprise Edition. Not every operation and capability is
--   available in every edition.
_UnsupportedUserEditionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Access is throttled.
_ThrottlingException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more preconditions aren't met.
_PreconditionNotMetException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The <tt>NextToken</tt> value isn't valid.
_InvalidNextTokenException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The resource specified already exists.
_ResourceExistsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An internal failure occurred.
_InternalFailureException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A resource is already in a state that indicates an operation is
--   happening that must complete before a new update can be applied.
_ConcurrentUpdatingException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more resources can't be found.
_ResourceNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The user with the provided name isn't found. This error can happen in
--   any operation that requires finding a user based on a provided user
--   name, such as <tt>DeleteUser</tt>, <tt>DescribeUser</tt>, and so on.
_QuickSightUserNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A limit is exceeded.
_LimitExceededException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The number of minutes specified for the lifetime of a session isn't
--   valid. The session lifetime must be 15-600 minutes.
_SessionLifetimeInMinutesInvalidException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The Amazon QuickSight customizations associated with your Amazon Web
--   Services account or a Amazon QuickSight namespace in a specific Amazon
--   Web Services Region.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAccountCustomization</a> smart constructor.
data AccountCustomization
AccountCustomization' :: Maybe Text -> AccountCustomization

-- | The default theme for this Amazon QuickSight subscription.
[$sel:defaultTheme:AccountCustomization'] :: AccountCustomization -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>AccountCustomization</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultTheme:AccountCustomization'</a>,
--   <a>accountCustomization_defaultTheme</a> - The default theme for this
--   Amazon QuickSight subscription.
newAccountCustomization :: AccountCustomization

-- | The default theme for this Amazon QuickSight subscription.
accountCustomization_defaultTheme :: Lens' AccountCustomization (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon QuickSight settings associated with your Amazon Web
--   Services account.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAccountSettings</a> smart constructor.
data AccountSettings
AccountSettings' :: Maybe Edition -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> AccountSettings

-- | The edition of Amazon QuickSight that you're currently subscribed to:
--   Enterprise edition or Standard edition.
[$sel:edition:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Edition

-- | The "account name" you provided for the Amazon QuickSight subscription
--   in your Amazon Web Services account. You create this name when you
--   sign up for Amazon QuickSight. It is unique in all of Amazon Web
--   Services and it appears only when users sign in.
[$sel:accountName:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | The default Amazon QuickSight namespace for your Amazon Web Services
--   account.
[$sel:defaultNamespace:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | The main notification email for your Amazon QuickSight subscription.
[$sel:notificationEmail:AccountSettings'] :: AccountSettings -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>AccountSettings</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:edition:AccountSettings'</a>, <a>accountSettings_edition</a> -
--   The edition of Amazon QuickSight that you're currently subscribed to:
--   Enterprise edition or Standard edition.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accountName:AccountSettings'</a>,
--   <a>accountSettings_accountName</a> - The "account name" you provided
--   for the Amazon QuickSight subscription in your Amazon Web Services
--   account. You create this name when you sign up for Amazon QuickSight.
--   It is unique in all of Amazon Web Services and it appears only when
--   users sign in.
--   
--   <a>$sel:defaultNamespace:AccountSettings'</a>,
--   <a>accountSettings_defaultNamespace</a> - The default Amazon
--   QuickSight namespace for your Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:notificationEmail:AccountSettings'</a>,
--   <a>accountSettings_notificationEmail</a> - The main notification email
--   for your Amazon QuickSight subscription.
newAccountSettings :: AccountSettings

-- | The edition of Amazon QuickSight that you're currently subscribed to:
--   Enterprise edition or Standard edition.
accountSettings_edition :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Edition)

-- | The "account name" you provided for the Amazon QuickSight subscription
--   in your Amazon Web Services account. You create this name when you
--   sign up for Amazon QuickSight. It is unique in all of Amazon Web
--   Services and it appears only when users sign in.
accountSettings_accountName :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Text)

-- | The default Amazon QuickSight namespace for your Amazon Web Services
--   account.
accountSettings_defaultNamespace :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Text)

-- | The main notification email for your Amazon QuickSight subscription.
accountSettings_notificationEmail :: Lens' AccountSettings (Maybe Text)

-- | Metadata structure for an analysis in Amazon QuickSight
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAnalysis</a> smart constructor.
data Analysis
Analysis' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe [Sheet] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (NonEmpty AnalysisError) -> Analysis

-- | Status associated with the analysis.
[$sel:status:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The ARN of the theme of the analysis.
[$sel:themeArn:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARNs of the datasets of the analysis.
[$sel:dataSetArns:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe [Text]

-- | A list of the associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of
--   each sheet.
[$sel:sheets:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe [Sheet]

-- | The ID of the analysis.
[$sel:analysisId:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that the analysis was last updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the analysis.
[$sel:arn:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that the analysis was created.
[$sel:createdTime:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The descriptive name of the analysis.
[$sel:name:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe Text

-- | Errors associated with the analysis.
[$sel:errors:Analysis'] :: Analysis -> Maybe (NonEmpty AnalysisError)

-- | Create a value of <a>Analysis</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_status</a> - Status
--   associated with the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeArn:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_themeArn</a> - The ARN of
--   the theme of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetArns:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_dataSetArns</a> - The
--   ARNs of the datasets of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sheets:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_sheets</a> - A list of the
--   associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of each sheet.
--   
--   <a>$sel:analysisId:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_analysisId</a> - The ID
--   of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_lastUpdatedTime</a>
--   - The time that the analysis was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_createdTime</a> - The
--   time that the analysis was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_name</a> - The descriptive
--   name of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errors:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_errors</a> - Errors
--   associated with the analysis.
newAnalysis :: Analysis

analysis_status :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe ResourceStatus)

--   each sheet.
analysis_sheets :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe [Sheet])

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the analysis.
analysis_arn :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that the analysis was created.
analysis_createdTime :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The descriptive name of the analysis.
analysis_name :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe Text)

-- | Errors associated with the analysis.
analysis_errors :: Lens' Analysis (Maybe (NonEmpty AnalysisError))

-- | The combination of user name and password that are used as
--   credentials.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCredentialPair</a> smart constructor.
data CredentialPair
CredentialPair' :: Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters) -> Text -> Text -> CredentialPair

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   these credentials. The credentials are applied in tandem with the data
--   source parameters when you copy a data source by using a create or
--   update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the new data source with the existing credentials. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> originally used with these
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> is automatically allowed.
[$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:CredentialPair'] :: CredentialPair -> Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters)

-- | User name.
[$sel:username:CredentialPair'] :: CredentialPair -> Text

-- | Password.
[$sel:password:CredentialPair'] :: CredentialPair -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>CredentialPair</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:CredentialPair'</a>,
--   <a>credentialPair_alternateDataSourceParameters</a> - A set of
--   alternate data source parameters that you want to share for these
--   credentials. The credentials are applied in tandem with the data
--   source parameters when you copy a data source by using a create or
--   update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the new data source with the existing credentials. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> originally used with these
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> is automatically allowed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:username:CredentialPair'</a>, <a>credentialPair_username</a> -
--   User name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:password:CredentialPair'</a>, <a>credentialPair_password</a> -
--   Password.
newCredentialPair :: Text -> Text -> CredentialPair

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   these credentials. The credentials are applied in tandem with the data
--   source parameters when you copy a data source by using a create or
--   update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the new data source with the existing credentials. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> originally used with these
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> is automatically allowed.
credentialPair_alternateDataSourceParameters :: Lens' CredentialPair (Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters))

credentialPair_username :: Lens' CredentialPair Text

-- | Password.
credentialPair_password :: Lens' CredentialPair Text

--   that you want to use as a filter, for example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1"</tt>.

--   description is a hexadecimal color code that consists of six
--   alphanumerical characters, prefixed with <tt>#</tt>, for example
--   #37BFF5.

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataColorPalette</a> smart constructor.

--   data is highlighted.
[$sel:emptyFillColor:DataColorPalette'] :: DataColorPalette -> Maybe Text

[$sel:colors:DataColorPalette'] :: DataColorPalette -> Maybe [Text]

--   omitted.

--   hexadecimal codes that describe a color gradient.
--   
--   <a>$sel:emptyFillColor:DataColorPalette'</a>,

--   color that applies to charts where a lack of data is highlighted.

--   The hexadecimal codes for the colors.

-- | Dataset.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSet</a> smart constructor.
data DataSet
DataSet' :: Maybe (HashMap Text FieldFolder) -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnGroup) -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe DataSetImportMode -> Maybe (HashMap Text PhysicalTable) -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DataSetUsageConfiguration -> Maybe [OutputColumn] -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule) -> Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable) -> DataSet

-- | The folder that contains fields and nested subfolders for your
--   dataset.
[$sel:fieldFolders:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text FieldFolder)

-- | Groupings of columns that work together in certain Amazon QuickSight
--   features. Currently, only geospatial hierarchy is supported.
[$sel:columnGroups:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnGroup)

-- | The last time that this dataset was updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource.
[$sel:arn:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that this dataset was created.
[$sel:createdTime:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The amount of SPICE capacity used by this dataset. This is 0 if the
--   dataset isn't imported into SPICE.
[$sel:consumedSpiceCapacityInBytes:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Integer

-- | A value that indicates whether you want to import the data into SPICE.
[$sel:importMode:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe DataSetImportMode

-- | Declares the physical tables that are available in the underlying data
--   sources.
[$sel:physicalTableMap:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text PhysicalTable)

-- | The ID of the dataset.
[$sel:dataSetId:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | A display name for the dataset.
[$sel:name:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | The usage configuration to apply to child datasets that reference this
--   dataset as a source.
[$sel:dataSetUsageConfiguration:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe DataSetUsageConfiguration

-- | The list of columns after all transforms. These columns are available
--   in templates, analyses, and dashboards.
[$sel:outputColumns:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe [OutputColumn]

-- | The element you can use to define tags for row-level security.
[$sel:rowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration

-- | The row-level security configuration for the dataset.
[$sel:rowLevelPermissionDataSet:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | A set of one or more definitions of a <tt> ColumnLevelPermissionRule
--   </tt>.
[$sel:columnLevelPermissionRules:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule)

-- | Configures the combination and transformation of the data from the
--   physical tables.
[$sel:logicalTableMap:DataSet'] :: DataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable)

-- | Create a value of <a>DataSet</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:fieldFolders:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_fieldFolders</a> - The
--   folder that contains fields and nested subfolders for your dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:columnGroups:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_columnGroups</a> -
--   Groupings of columns that work together in certain Amazon QuickSight
--   features. Currently, only geospatial hierarchy is supported.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_lastUpdatedTime</a> -
--   The last time that this dataset was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_createdTime</a> - The
--   time that this dataset was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:consumedSpiceCapacityInBytes:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_consumedSpiceCapacityInBytes</a> - The amount of SPICE
--   capacity used by this dataset. This is 0 if the dataset isn't imported
--   into SPICE.
--

--   that indicates whether you want to import the data into SPICE.
--   
--   <a>$sel:physicalTableMap:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_physicalTableMap</a>
--   - Declares the physical tables that are available in the underlying
--   data sources.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetId:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_dataSetId</a> - The ID of
--   the dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_name</a> - A display name for
--   the dataset.

--   can use to define tags for row-level security.
--   
--   <a>$sel:rowLevelPermissionDataSet:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_rowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> - The row-level security
--   configuration for the dataset.
--   
--   <a>$sel:columnLevelPermissionRules:DataSet'</a>,
--   <a>dataSet_columnLevelPermissionRules</a> - A set of one or more
--   definitions of a <tt> ColumnLevelPermissionRule </tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:logicalTableMap:DataSet'</a>, <a>dataSet_logicalTableMap</a> -
--   Configures the combination and transformation of the data from the
--   physical tables.

dataSet_rowLevelPermissionDataSet :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet)

-- | A set of one or more definitions of a <tt> ColumnLevelPermissionRule
--   </tt>.
dataSet_columnLevelPermissionRules :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule))

-- | Configures the combination and transformation of the data from the
--   physical tables.
dataSet_logicalTableMap :: Lens' DataSet (Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable))

-- | The structure of a data source.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSource</a> smart constructor.
data DataSource
DataSource' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe DataSourceParameters -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe SslProperties -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters) -> Maybe VpcConnectionProperties -> Maybe DataSourceType -> Maybe DataSourceErrorInfo -> DataSource

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
[$sel:status:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The parameters that Amazon QuickSight uses to connect to your
--   underlying source. This is a variant type structure. For this
--   structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be non-null.
[$sel:dataSourceParameters:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe DataSourceParameters

-- | The last time that this data source was updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
[$sel:arn:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe Text

-- | The time that this data source was created.
[$sel:createdTime:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Secure Socket Layer (SSL) properties that apply when Amazon QuickSight
--   connects to your underlying source.
[$sel:sslProperties:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe SslProperties

-- | The ID of the data source. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
[$sel:dataSourceId:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe Text

-- | A display name for the data source.
[$sel:name:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe Text

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   the credentials stored with this data source. The credentials are
--   applied in tandem with the data source parameters when you copy a data
--   source by using a create or update request. The API operation compares
--   the <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with
--   the structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow
--   list. If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to
--   use the credentials from this existing data source. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> originally used with this
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> are automatically allowed.
[$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters)

-- | The VPC connection information. You need to use this parameter only
--   when you want Amazon QuickSight to use a VPC connection when
--   connecting to your underlying source.
[$sel:vpcConnectionProperties:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe VpcConnectionProperties

-- | The type of the data source. This type indicates which database engine
--   the data source connects to.
[$sel:type':DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe DataSourceType

-- | Error information from the last update or the creation of the data
--   source.
[$sel:errorInfo:DataSource'] :: DataSource -> Maybe DataSourceErrorInfo

-- | Create a value of <a>DataSource</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_status</a> - The HTTP
--   status of the request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceParameters:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_dataSourceParameters</a> - The parameters that Amazon
--   QuickSight uses to connect to your underlying source. This is a
--   variant type structure. For this structure to be valid, only one of
--   the attributes can be non-null.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_lastUpdatedTime</a> - The last time that this data
--   source was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_arn</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_createdTime</a> -
--   The time that this data source was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sslProperties:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_sslProperties</a>
--   - Secure Socket Layer (SSL) properties that apply when Amazon
--   QuickSight connects to your underlying source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceId:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_dataSourceId</a> -
--   The ID of the data source. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_name</a> - A display name
--   for the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_alternateDataSourceParameters</a> - A set of alternate
--   data source parameters that you want to share for the credentials
--   stored with this data source. The credentials are applied in tandem
--   with the data source parameters when you copy a data source by using a
--   create or update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the credentials from this existing data source. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> originally used with this
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> are automatically allowed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcConnectionProperties:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_vpcConnectionProperties</a> - The VPC connection
--   information. You need to use this parameter only when you want Amazon
--   QuickSight to use a VPC connection when connecting to your underlying
--   source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_type</a> - The type of
--   the data source. This type indicates which database engine the data
--   source connects to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorInfo:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_errorInfo</a> - Error
--   information from the last update or the creation of the data source.
newDataSource :: DataSource

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
dataSource_status :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe ResourceStatus)

-- | The parameters that Amazon QuickSight uses to connect to your
--   underlying source. This is a variant type structure. For this
--   structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be non-null.
dataSource_dataSourceParameters :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe DataSourceParameters)

-- | The last time that this data source was updated.
dataSource_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
dataSource_arn :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe Text)

-- | The time that this data source was created.
dataSource_createdTime :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Secure Socket Layer (SSL) properties that apply when Amazon QuickSight
--   connects to your underlying source.
dataSource_sslProperties :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe SslProperties)

-- | The ID of the data source. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
dataSource_dataSourceId :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe Text)

-- | A display name for the data source.
dataSource_name :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe Text)

-- | A set of alternate data source parameters that you want to share for
--   the credentials stored with this data source. The credentials are
--   applied in tandem with the data source parameters when you copy a data
--   source by using a create or update request. The API operation compares
--   the <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with
--   the structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow

--   connecting to your underlying source.

-- | The type of the data source. This type indicates which database engine
--   the data source connects to.
dataSource_type :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe DataSourceType)

-- | Error information from the last update or the creation of the data
--   source.
dataSource_errorInfo :: Lens' DataSource (Maybe DataSourceErrorInfo)

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSourceCredentials</a> smart constructor.

--   <tt>"Operator": "StringEquals"</tt>.
[$sel:operator:FolderSearchFilter'] :: FolderSearchFilter -> Maybe FilterOperator

-- | The value of the named item (in this example,
--   <tt>PARENT_FOLDER_ARN</tt>), that you want to use as a filter. For
--   example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:folder/folderId"</tt>.

-- | The name of the value that you want to use as a filter. For example,
--   <tt>"Name": "PARENT_FOLDER_ARN"</tt>.
[$sel:name:FolderSearchFilter'] :: FolderSearchFilter -> Maybe FolderFilterAttribute

--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:operator:FolderSearchFilter'</a>,
--   <a>folderSearchFilter_operator</a> - The comparison operator that you
--   want to use as a filter. For example, <tt>"Operator":
--   "StringEquals"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:FolderSearchFilter'</a>, <a>folderSearchFilter_value</a>
--   - The value of the named item (in this example,
--   <tt>PARENT_FOLDER_ARN</tt>), that you want to use as a filter. For
--   example, <tt>"Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:folder/folderId"</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:FolderSearchFilter'</a>, <a>folderSearchFilter_name</a> -
--   The name of the value that you want to use as a filter. For example,
--   <tt>"Name": "PARENT_FOLDER_ARN"</tt>.

-- | A <i>group</i> in Amazon QuickSight consists of a set of users. You
--   can use groups to make it easier to manage access and security.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newGroup</a> smart constructor.
data Group

--

--   (ARN) for the group.
--   
--   <a>$sel:groupName:Group'</a>, <a>group_groupName</a> - The name of the
--   group.

[$sel:rowInfo:Ingestion'] :: Ingestion -> Maybe RowInfo

-- | A <i>logical table</i> is a unit that joins and that data
--   transformations operate on. A logical table has a source, which can be
--   either a physical table or result of a join. When a logical table
--   points to a physical table, the logical table acts as a mutable copy
--   of that physical table through transform operations.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newLogicalTable</a> smart constructor.
data LogicalTable
LogicalTable' :: Maybe (NonEmpty TransformOperation) -> Text -> LogicalTableSource -> LogicalTable

-- | Transform operations that act on this logical table.
[$sel:dataTransforms:LogicalTable'] :: LogicalTable -> Maybe (NonEmpty TransformOperation)

-- | A display name for the logical table.
[$sel:alias:LogicalTable'] :: LogicalTable -> Text

-- | Source of this logical table.
[$sel:source:LogicalTable'] :: LogicalTable -> LogicalTableSource

-- | Create a value of <a>LogicalTable</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataTransforms:LogicalTable'</a>,
--   <a>logicalTable_dataTransforms</a> - Transform operations that act on
--   this logical table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:alias:LogicalTable'</a>, <a>logicalTable_alias</a> - A display
--   name for the logical table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:source:LogicalTable'</a>, <a>logicalTable_source</a> - Source
--   of this logical table.
newLogicalTable :: Text -> LogicalTableSource -> LogicalTable

-- | Transform operations that act on this logical table.
logicalTable_dataTransforms :: Lens' LogicalTable (Maybe (NonEmpty TransformOperation))

-- | A display name for the logical table.
logicalTable_alias :: Lens' LogicalTable Text

-- | Source of this logical table.
logicalTable_source :: Lens' LogicalTable LogicalTableSource

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newNamespaceError</a> smart constructor.
data NamespaceError
NamespaceError' :: Maybe NamespaceErrorType -> Maybe Text -> NamespaceError

-- | The error type.
[$sel:type':NamespaceError'] :: NamespaceError -> Maybe NamespaceErrorType

-- | The message for the error.
[$sel:message:NamespaceError'] :: NamespaceError -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>NamespaceError</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':NamespaceError'</a>, <a>namespaceError_type</a> - The
--   error type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:NamespaceError'</a>, <a>namespaceError_message</a> -
--   The message for the error.
newNamespaceError :: NamespaceError

-- | The error type.
namespaceError_type :: Lens' NamespaceError (Maybe NamespaceErrorType)

-- | The message for the error.
namespaceError_message :: Lens' NamespaceError (Maybe Text)

-- | The error type.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newNamespaceInfoV2</a> smart constructor.
data NamespaceInfoV2

-- | A list of Amazon QuickSight parameters and the list's override values.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newParameters</a> smart constructor.
data Parameters
Parameters' :: Maybe [DateTimeParameter] -> Maybe [DecimalParameter] -> Maybe [IntegerParameter] -> Maybe [StringParameter] -> Parameters

-- | The parameters that have a data type of date-time.
[$sel:dateTimeParameters:Parameters'] :: Parameters -> Maybe [DateTimeParameter]

-- | The parameters that have a data type of decimal.
[$sel:decimalParameters:Parameters'] :: Parameters -> Maybe [DecimalParameter]

-- | The parameters that have a data type of integer.
[$sel:integerParameters:Parameters'] :: Parameters -> Maybe [IntegerParameter]

-- | The parameters that have a data type of string.
[$sel:stringParameters:Parameters'] :: Parameters -> Maybe [StringParameter]

-- | Create a value of <a>Parameters</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:dateTimeParameters:Parameters'</a>,
--   <a>parameters_dateTimeParameters</a> - The parameters that have a data
--   type of date-time.
--   
--   <a>$sel:decimalParameters:Parameters'</a>,
--   <a>parameters_decimalParameters</a> - The parameters that have a data
--   type of decimal.
--   
--   <a>$sel:integerParameters:Parameters'</a>,
--   <a>parameters_integerParameters</a> - The parameters that have a data
--   type of integer.
--   
--   <a>$sel:stringParameters:Parameters'</a>,
--   <a>parameters_stringParameters</a> - The parameters that have a data
--   type of string.
newParameters :: Parameters

-- | The parameters that have a data type of date-time.
parameters_dateTimeParameters :: Lens' Parameters (Maybe [DateTimeParameter])

-- | The parameters that have a data type of decimal.
parameters_decimalParameters :: Lens' Parameters (Maybe [DecimalParameter])

-- | The parameters that have a data type of integer.
parameters_integerParameters :: Lens' Parameters (Maybe [IntegerParameter])

-- | The parameters that have a data type of string.
parameters_stringParameters :: Lens' Parameters (Maybe [StringParameter])

-- | A view of a data source that contains information about the shape of
--   the data in the underlying source. This is a variant type structure.
--   For this structure to be valid, only one of the attributes can be
--   non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPhysicalTable</a> smart constructor.
data PhysicalTable
PhysicalTable' :: Maybe S3Source -> Maybe RelationalTable -> Maybe CustomSql -> PhysicalTable

-- | A physical table type for as S3 data source.
[$sel:s3Source:PhysicalTable'] :: PhysicalTable -> Maybe S3Source

-- | A physical table type for relational data sources.
[$sel:relationalTable:PhysicalTable'] :: PhysicalTable -> Maybe RelationalTable

-- | A physical table type built from the results of the custom SQL query.
[$sel:customSql:PhysicalTable'] :: PhysicalTable -> Maybe CustomSql

-- | Create a value of <a>PhysicalTable</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:s3Source:PhysicalTable'</a>, <a>physicalTable_s3Source</a> - A
--   physical table type for as S3 data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:relationalTable:PhysicalTable'</a>,
--   <a>physicalTable_relationalTable</a> - A physical table type for
--   relational data sources.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customSql:PhysicalTable'</a>, <a>physicalTable_customSql</a> -
--   A physical table type built from the results of the custom SQL query.
newPhysicalTable :: PhysicalTable

-- | A physical table type for as S3 data source.
physicalTable_s3Source :: Lens' PhysicalTable (Maybe S3Source)

-- | A physical table type for relational data sources.
physicalTable_relationalTable :: Lens' PhysicalTable (Maybe RelationalTable)

-- | A physical table type built from the results of the custom SQL query.
physicalTable_customSql :: Lens' PhysicalTable (Maybe CustomSql)

--   a permissions error message.

-- | The type of experience you want to embed. For registered users, you
--   can embed an Amazon QuickSight dashboard or the Amazon QuickSight
--   console.
--   
--   Exactly one of the experience configurations is required. You can
--   choose <tt>Dashboard</tt> or <tt>QuickSightConsole</tt>. You cannot
--   choose more than one experience configuraton.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration</a>
--   smart constructor.
data RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration
RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration' :: Maybe RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration -> RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration

-- | The configuration details for providing a dashboard embedding
--   experience.
[$sel:dashboard:RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserDashboardEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The configuration details for providing an Amazon QuickSight console
--   embedding experience. This can be used along with custom permissions
--   to restrict access to certain features. For more information, see
--   <a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide</i>.
--   
--   Use <tt>GenerateEmbedUrlForRegisteredUser</tt> where you want to
--   provide an authoring portal that allows users to create data sources,
--   datasets, analyses, and dashboards. The users who accesses an embedded
--   Amazon QuickSight console needs to belong to the author or admin
--   security cohort. If you want to restrict permissions to some of these
--   features, add a custom permissions profile to the user with the <tt>
--   UpdateUser </tt> API operation. Use <tt> RegisterUser </tt> API
--   operation to add a new user with a custom permission profile attached.
--   For more information, see the following sections in the <i>Amazon
--   QuickSight User Guide</i>:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><a>Embedding the Full Functionality of the Amazon QuickSight
--   Console for Authenticated Users</a></li>
--   <li><a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information about the high-level steps for embedding and for
--   an interactive demo of the ways you can customize embedding, visit the
--   <a>Amazon QuickSight Developer Portal</a>.
[$sel:quickSightConsole:RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQuickSightConsoleEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | The configuration details for embedding the Q search bar.
--   
--   For more information about embedding the Q search bar, see
--   <a>Embedding Overview</a>.
[$sel:qSearchBar:RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration'] :: RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration -> Maybe RegisteredUserQSearchBarEmbeddingConfiguration

-- | Create a value of
--   <a>RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration</a> with all

--   configuration details for providing a dashboard embedding experience.
--   
--   
--   <a>$sel:quickSightConsole:RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration'</a>,
--   <a>registeredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration_quickSightConsole</a>
--   - The configuration details for providing an Amazon QuickSight console
--   embedding experience. This can be used along with custom permissions
--   to restrict access to certain features. For more information, see
--   <a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide</i>.
--   
--   Use <tt>GenerateEmbedUrlForRegisteredUser</tt> where you want to
--   provide an authoring portal that allows users to create data sources,

--   For more information, see the following sections in the <i>Amazon
--   QuickSight User Guide</i>:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><a>Embedding the Full Functionality of the Amazon QuickSight
--   Console for Authenticated Users</a></li>
--   <li><a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a></li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information about the high-level steps for embedding and for
--   an interactive demo of the ways you can customize embedding, visit the

newRegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration :: RegisteredUserEmbeddingExperienceConfiguration

-- | The configuration details for providing an Amazon QuickSight console
--   embedding experience. This can be used along with custom permissions
--   to restrict access to certain features. For more information, see
--   <a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a> in the
--   <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide</i>.
--   
--   Use <tt>GenerateEmbedUrlForRegisteredUser</tt> where you want to
--   provide an authoring portal that allows users to create data sources,
--   datasets, analyses, and dashboards. The users who accesses an embedded
--   Amazon QuickSight console needs to belong to the author or admin
--   security cohort. If you want to restrict permissions to some of these
--   features, add a custom permissions profile to the user with the <tt>
--   UpdateUser </tt> API operation. Use <tt> RegisterUser </tt> API
--   operation to add a new user with a custom permission profile attached.
--   For more information, see the following sections in the <i>Amazon
--   QuickSight User Guide</i>:
--   
--   <ul>

--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information about the high-level steps for embedding and for
--   an interactive demo of the ways you can customize embedding, visit the
--   <a>Amazon QuickSight Developer Portal</a>.

-- | Permission for the resource.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newResourcePermission</a> smart constructor.
data ResourcePermission
ResourcePermission' :: Text -> NonEmpty Text -> ResourcePermission

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the principal. This can be one of
--   the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user or group associated with a
--   data source or dataset. (This is common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user, group, or namespace
--   associated with an analysis, dashboard, template, or theme. (This is
--   common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon Web Services account root: This is an IAMARN
--   rather than a Amazon QuickSight ARN. Use this option only to share
--   resources (templates) across Amazon Web Services accounts. (This is
--   less common.)</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:principal:ResourcePermission'] :: ResourcePermission -> Text

-- | The IAMaction to grant or revoke permissions on.
[$sel:actions:ResourcePermission'] :: ResourcePermission -> NonEmpty Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ResourcePermission</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   <a>resourcePermission_principal</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   of the principal. This can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user or group associated with a
--   data source or dataset. (This is common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon QuickSight user, group, or namespace
--   associated with an analysis, dashboard, template, or theme. (This is
--   common.)</li>
--   <li>The ARN of an Amazon Web Services account root: This is an IAMARN
--   rather than a Amazon QuickSight ARN. Use this option only to share
--   resources (templates) across Amazon Web Services accounts. (This is
--   less common.)</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:actions:ResourcePermission'</a>,
--   <a>resourcePermission_actions</a> - The IAMaction to grant or revoke
--   permissions on.
newResourcePermission :: Text -> NonEmpty Text -> ResourcePermission

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the principal. This can be one of
--   the following:
--   
--   <ul>

--   </ul>

-- | Information about a dataset that contains permissions for row-level
--   security (RLS). The permissions dataset maps fields to users or
--   groups. For more information, see <a>Using Row-Level Security (RLS) to
--   Restrict Access to a Dataset</a> in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User
--   Guide</i>.
--   
--   The option to deny permissions by setting <tt>PermissionPolicy</tt> to
--   <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is not supported for new RLS datasets.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> smart constructor.
data RowLevelPermissionDataSet
RowLevelPermissionDataSet' :: Maybe Status -> Maybe Text -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionFormatVersion -> Text -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy -> RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | The status of the row-level security permission dataset. If enabled,
--   the status is <tt>ENABLED</tt>. If disabled, the status is
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>.
[$sel:status:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe Status

-- | The namespace associated with the dataset that contains permissions
--   for RLS.
[$sel:namespace:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe Text

-- | The user or group rules associated with the dataset that contains
--   permissions for RLS.
--   
--   By default, <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>. When
--   <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>, <tt>UserName</tt> and
--   <tt>GroupName</tt> are required. When <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is
--   <tt>VERSION_2</tt>, <tt>UserARN</tt> and <tt>GroupARN</tt> are
--   required, and <tt>Namespace</tt> must not exist.
[$sel:formatVersion:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionFormatVersion

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the dataset that contains
--   permissions for RLS.
[$sel:arn:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Text

-- | The type of permissions to use when interpreting the permissions for
--   RLS. <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is included for backward compatibility only.
[$sel:permissionPolicy:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'] :: RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy

-- | Create a value of <a>RowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_status</a> - The status of the row-level
--   security permission dataset. If enabled, the status is
--   <tt>ENABLED</tt>. If disabled, the status is <tt>DISABLED</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_namespace</a> - The namespace associated
--   with the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   <a>$sel:formatVersion:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_formatVersion</a> - The user or group
--   rules associated with the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   By default, <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>. When
--   <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>, <tt>UserName</tt> and
--   <tt>GroupName</tt> are required. When <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is
--   <tt>VERSION_2</tt>, <tt>UserARN</tt> and <tt>GroupARN</tt> are
--   required, and <tt>Namespace</tt> must not exist.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   of the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   <a>$sel:permissionPolicy:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_permissionPolicy</a> - The type of
--   permissions to use when interpreting the permissions for RLS.
--   <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is included for backward compatibility only.
newRowLevelPermissionDataSet :: Text -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy -> RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | The status of the row-level security permission dataset. If enabled,
--   the status is <tt>ENABLED</tt>. If disabled, the status is
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>.

--   for RLS.
rowLevelPermissionDataSet_namespace :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionDataSet (Maybe Text)

-- | The user or group rules associated with the dataset that contains
--   permissions for RLS.
--   
--   By default, <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>. When
--   <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>, <tt>UserName</tt> and
--   <tt>GroupName</tt> are required. When <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is
--   <tt>VERSION_2</tt>, <tt>UserARN</tt> and <tt>GroupARN</tt> are
--   required, and <tt>Namespace</tt> must not exist.

-- | A set of rules associated with a tag.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRowLevelPermissionTagRule</a> smart constructor.
data RowLevelPermissionTagRule
RowLevelPermissionTagRule' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Text -> Text -> RowLevelPermissionTagRule

-- | A string that you want to use to delimit the values when you pass the
--   values at run time. For example, you can delimit the values with a
--   comma.
[$sel:tagMultiValueDelimiter:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Maybe Text

-- | A string that you want to use to filter by all the values in a column
--   in the dataset and dont want to list the values one by one. For
--   example, you can use an asterisk as your match all value.
[$sel:matchAllValue:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The unique key for a tag.
[$sel:tagKey:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Text

-- | The column name that a tag key is assigned to.
[$sel:columnName:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'] :: RowLevelPermissionTagRule -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RowLevelPermissionTagRule</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagMultiValueDelimiter:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_tagMultiValueDelimiter</a> - A string
--   that you want to use to delimit the values when you pass the values at
--   run time. For example, you can delimit the values with a comma.
--   
--   <a>$sel:matchAllValue:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_matchAllValue</a> - A string that you
--   want to use to filter by all the values in a column in the dataset and
--   dont want to list the values one by one. For example, you can use an
--   asterisk as your match all value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagKey:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_tagKey</a> - The unique key for a tag.
--   
--   <a>$sel:columnName:RowLevelPermissionTagRule'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionTagRule_columnName</a> - The column name that a
--   tag key is assigned to.
newRowLevelPermissionTagRule :: Text -> Text -> RowLevelPermissionTagRule

-- | A string that you want to use to delimit the values when you pass the
--   values at run time. For example, you can delimit the values with a
--   comma.
rowLevelPermissionTagRule_tagMultiValueDelimiter :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionTagRule (Maybe Text)

-- | A string that you want to use to filter by all the values in a column
--   in the dataset and dont want to list the values one by one. For
--   example, you can use an asterisk as your match all value.
rowLevelPermissionTagRule_matchAllValue :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionTagRule (Maybe Text)

-- | The unique key for a tag.
rowLevelPermissionTagRule_tagKey :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionTagRule Text

-- | The column name that a tag key is assigned to.
rowLevelPermissionTagRule_columnName :: Lens' RowLevelPermissionTagRule Text

-- | A <i>sheet</i>, which is an object that contains a set of visuals that
--   are viewed together on one page in Amazon QuickSight. Every analysis
--   and dashboard contains at least one sheet. Each sheet contains at

--   narrative insight. Sheets can be associated with other components,

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSheet</a> smart constructor.

-- | A template object. A <i>template</i> is an entity in Amazon QuickSight
--   that encapsulates the metadata required to create an analysis and that
--   you can use to create a dashboard. A template adds a layer of
--   abstraction by using placeholders to replace the dataset associated
--   with an analysis. You can use templates to create dashboards by
--   replacing dataset placeholders with datasets that follow the same
--   schema that was used to create the source analysis and template.
--   
--   You can share templates across Amazon Web Services accounts by
--   allowing users in other Amazon Web Services accounts to create a
--   template or a dashboard from an existing template.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTemplate</a> smart constructor.
data Template
Template' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe TemplateVersion -> Template

-- | Time when this was last updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the template.
[$sel:arn:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe Text

-- | Time when this was created.
[$sel:createdTime:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The ID for the template. This is unique per Amazon Web Services Region
--   for each Amazon Web Services account.
[$sel:templateId:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe Text

-- | The display name of the template.
[$sel:name:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe Text

-- | A structure describing the versions of the template.
[$sel:version:Template'] :: Template -> Maybe TemplateVersion

-- | Create a value of <a>Template</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Template'</a>, <a>template_lastUpdatedTime</a>
--   - Time when this was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Template'</a>, <a>template_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Template'</a>, <a>template_createdTime</a> - Time
--   when this was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateId:Template'</a>, <a>template_templateId</a> - The ID
--   for the template. This is unique per Amazon Web Services Region for
--   each Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Template'</a>, <a>template_name</a> - The display name of
--   the template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:version:Template'</a>, <a>template_version</a> - A structure
--   describing the versions of the template.
newTemplate :: Template

-- | Time when this was last updated.
template_lastUpdatedTime :: Lens' Template (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the template.
template_arn :: Lens' Template (Maybe Text)

-- | Time when this was created.
template_createdTime :: Lens' Template (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The ID for the template. This is unique per Amazon Web Services Region
--   for each Amazon Web Services account.
template_templateId :: Lens' Template (Maybe Text)

-- | The display name of the template.
template_name :: Lens' Template (Maybe Text)

-- | A structure describing the versions of the template.
template_version :: Lens' Template (Maybe TemplateVersion)

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newThemeVersionSummary</a> smart constructor.
data ThemeVersionSummary
ThemeVersionSummary' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe Text -> ThemeVersionSummary

-- | The status of the theme version.
[$sel:status:ThemeVersionSummary'] :: ThemeVersionSummary -> Maybe ResourceStatus

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme version.
[$sel:arn:ThemeVersionSummary'] :: ThemeVersionSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | The date and time that this theme version was created.
[$sel:createdTime:ThemeVersionSummary'] :: ThemeVersionSummary -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The version number of the theme version.
[$sel:versionNumber:ThemeVersionSummary'] :: ThemeVersionSummary -> Maybe Natural

-- | The description of the theme version.
[$sel:description:ThemeVersionSummary'] :: ThemeVersionSummary -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ThemeVersionSummary</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   <a>themeVersionSummary_status</a> - The status of the theme version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:ThemeVersionSummary'</a>, <a>themeVersionSummary_arn</a> -
--   The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:ThemeVersionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>themeVersionSummary_createdTime</a> - The date and time that this
--   theme version was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionNumber:ThemeVersionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>themeVersionSummary_versionNumber</a> - The version number of the
--   theme version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ThemeVersionSummary'</a>,
--   <a>themeVersionSummary_description</a> - The description of the theme
--   version.
newThemeVersionSummary :: ThemeVersionSummary

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme version.

-- | The date and time that this theme version was created.

-- | The version number of the theme version.
themeVersionSummary_versionNumber :: Lens' ThemeVersionSummary (Maybe Natural)

-- | The description of the theme version.
themeVersionSummary_description :: Lens' ThemeVersionSummary (Maybe Text)

-- | A data transformation on a logical table. This is a variant type
--   structure. For this structure to be valid, only one of the attributes
--   can be non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTransformOperation</a> smart constructor.
data TransformOperation
TransformOperation' :: Maybe CastColumnTypeOperation -> Maybe TagColumnOperation -> Maybe CreateColumnsOperation -> Maybe UntagColumnOperation -> Maybe FilterOperation -> Maybe ProjectOperation -> Maybe RenameColumnOperation -> TransformOperation

-- | A transform operation that casts a column to a different type.
[$sel:castColumnTypeOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe CastColumnTypeOperation

-- | An operation that tags a column with additional information.
[$sel:tagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe TagColumnOperation

-- | An operation that creates calculated columns. Columns created in one
--   such operation form a lexical closure.
[$sel:createColumnsOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe CreateColumnsOperation
[$sel:untagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe UntagColumnOperation

-- | An operation that filters rows based on some condition.
[$sel:filterOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe FilterOperation

-- | An operation that projects columns. Operations that come after a
--   projection can only refer to projected columns.
[$sel:projectOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe ProjectOperation

-- | An operation that renames a column.
[$sel:renameColumnOperation:TransformOperation'] :: TransformOperation -> Maybe RenameColumnOperation

-- | Create a value of <a>TransformOperation</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:castColumnTypeOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_castColumnTypeOperation</a> - A transform
--   operation that casts a column to a different type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_tagColumnOperation</a> - An operation that tags
--   a column with additional information.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createColumnsOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_createColumnsOperation</a> - An operation that
--   creates calculated columns. Columns created in one such operation form
--   a lexical closure.
--   
--   <a>$sel:untagColumnOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_untagColumnOperation</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:filterOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_filterOperation</a> - An operation that filters
--   rows based on some condition.
--   
--   <a>$sel:projectOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_projectOperation</a> - An operation that
--   projects columns. Operations that come after a projection can only
--   refer to projected columns.
--   
--   <a>$sel:renameColumnOperation:TransformOperation'</a>,
--   <a>transformOperation_renameColumnOperation</a> - An operation that
--   renames a column.
newTransformOperation :: TransformOperation

-- | A transform operation that casts a column to a different type.
transformOperation_castColumnTypeOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe CastColumnTypeOperation)

-- | An operation that tags a column with additional information.
transformOperation_tagColumnOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe TagColumnOperation)

-- | An operation that creates calculated columns. Columns created in one
--   such operation form a lexical closure.
transformOperation_createColumnsOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe CreateColumnsOperation)

-- | Undocumented member.
transformOperation_untagColumnOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe UntagColumnOperation)

-- | An operation that filters rows based on some condition.
transformOperation_filterOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe FilterOperation)

-- | An operation that projects columns. Operations that come after a
--   projection can only refer to projected columns.
transformOperation_projectOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe ProjectOperation)

-- | An operation that renames a column.
transformOperation_renameColumnOperation :: Lens' TransformOperation (Maybe RenameColumnOperation)

-- | The theme colors that apply to UI and to charts, excluding data
--   colors. The colors description is a hexadecimal color code that
--   consists of six alphanumerical characters, prefixed with <tt>#</tt>,
--   for example #37BFF5. For more information, see <a>Using Themes in
--   Amazon QuickSight</a> in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide.</i>
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUIColorPalette</a> smart constructor.
data UIColorPalette
UIColorPalette' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> UIColorPalette

-- | The background color that applies to the sheet background and sheet
--   controls.
[$sel:secondaryBackground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the success color.
[$sel:successForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color that applies to the names of fields that are identified as
--   dimensions.
[$sel:dimension:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the dimension color.
[$sel:dimensionForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color that applies to success messages, for example the check mark
--   for a successful download.
[$sel:success:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | This color is that applies to selected states and buttons.
[$sel:accent:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any sheet title, sheet control
--   text, or UI that appears over the secondary background.
[$sel:secondaryForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color of text and other foreground elements that appear over the
--   primary background regions, such as grid lines, borders, table
--   banding, icons, and so on.
[$sel:primaryForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | This color that applies to warning and informational messages.
[$sel:warning:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The background color that applies to visuals and other high emphasis
--   UI.
[$sel:primaryBackground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the accent color.
[$sel:accentForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The color that applies to the names of fields that are identified as
--   measures.
[$sel:measure:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

-- | The foreground color that applies to any text or other elements that
--   appear over the error color.
[$sel:dangerForeground:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

--   appear over the measure color.

[$sel:danger:UIColorPalette'] :: UIColorPalette -> Maybe Text

--   appear over the warning color.

-- | A transform operation that removes tags associated with a column.

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUntagColumnOperation</a> smart constructor.
data UntagColumnOperation

[$sel:columnName:UntagColumnOperation'] :: UntagColumnOperation -> Text

-- | The column tags to remove from this column.

-- | Create a value of <a>UntagColumnOperation</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   operation acts on.

--   <a>$sel:tagNames:UntagColumnOperation'</a>,
--   <a>untagColumnOperation_tagNames</a> - The column tags to remove from
--   this column.

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUploadSettings</a> smart constructor.
data UploadSettings

[$sel:startFromRow:UploadSettings'] :: UploadSettings -> Maybe Natural

[$sel:textQualifier:UploadSettings'] :: UploadSettings -> Maybe TextQualifier

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   data from.
--

--   <a>uploadSettings_containsHeader</a> - Whether the file has a header
--   row, or the files each have a header row.

--   <a>$sel:textQualifier:UploadSettings'</a>,
--   <a>uploadSettings_textQualifier</a> - Text qualifier.
--   
--   <a>$sel:format:UploadSettings'</a>, <a>uploadSettings_format</a> -
--   File format.
--
