-- | A registered user of Amazon QuickSight.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUser</a> smart constructor.
data User
User' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe IdentityType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe UserRole -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> User

-- | The user's email address.
[$sel:email:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The principal ID of the user.
[$sel:principalId:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the user.
[$sel:arn:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The user's user name.
[$sel:userName:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of identity authentication used by the user.
[$sel:identityType:User'] :: User -> Maybe IdentityType

-- | The URL of the external login provider.
[$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderUrl:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The custom permissions profile associated with this user.
[$sel:customPermissionsName:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The active status of user. When you create an Amazon QuickSight user
--   thats not an IAM user or an Active Directory user, that user is
--   inactive until they sign in and provide a password.
[$sel:active:User'] :: User -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon QuickSight role for the user. The user role can be one of
--   the following:.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:role':User'] :: User -> Maybe UserRole

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let the user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   IAMrole. The type can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | The identity ID for the user in the external login provider.
[$sel:externalLoginId:User'] :: User -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>User</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:email:User'</a>, <a>user_email</a> - The user's email address.
--   
--   <a>$sel:principalId:User'</a>, <a>user_principalId</a> - The principal
--   ID of the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:User'</a>, <a>user_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) for the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userName:User'</a>, <a>user_userName</a> - The user's user
--   name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:identityType:User'</a>, <a>user_identityType</a> - The type of
--   identity authentication used by the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderUrl:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_externalLoginFederationProviderUrl</a> - The URL of the
--   external login provider.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customPermissionsName:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_customPermissionsName</a> - The custom permissions profile
--   associated with this user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:active:User'</a>, <a>user_active</a> - The active status of
--   user. When you create an Amazon QuickSight user thats not an IAM user
--   or an Active Directory user, that user is inactive until they sign in
--   and provide a password.
--   
--   <a>$sel:role':User'</a>, <a>user_role</a> - The Amazon QuickSight role
--   for the user. The user role can be one of the following:.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_externalLoginFederationProviderType</a> - The type of
--   supported external login provider that provides identity to let the
--   user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated IAMrole. The
--   type can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginId:User'</a>, <a>user_externalLoginId</a> - The
--   identity ID for the user in the external login provider.
newUser :: User

-- | The user's email address.
user_email :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The principal ID of the user.
user_principalId :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the user.
user_arn :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The user's user name.
user_userName :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The type of identity authentication used by the user.
user_identityType :: Lens' User (Maybe IdentityType)

-- | The URL of the external login provider.
user_externalLoginFederationProviderUrl :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The custom permissions profile associated with this user.
user_customPermissionsName :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The active status of user. When you create an Amazon QuickSight user
--   thats not an IAM user or an Active Directory user, that user is
--   inactive until they sign in and provide a password.
user_active :: Lens' User (Maybe Bool)

-- | The Amazon QuickSight role for the user. The user role can be one of
--   the following:.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
user_role :: Lens' User (Maybe UserRole)

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let the user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   IAMrole. The type can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider.</li>
--   </ul>
user_externalLoginFederationProviderType :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | The identity ID for the user in the external login provider.
user_externalLoginId :: Lens' User (Maybe Text)

-- | VPC connection properties.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newVpcConnectionProperties</a> smart constructor.
data VpcConnectionProperties
VpcConnectionProperties' :: Text -> VpcConnectionProperties

[$sel:vpcConnectionArn:VpcConnectionProperties'] :: VpcConnectionProperties -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>VpcConnectionProperties</a> with all optional

-- | Assigns one or more tags (key-value pairs) to the specified Amazon
--   QuickSight resource.
--   
--   Tags can help you organize and categorize your resources. You can also
--   use them to scope user permissions, by granting a user permission to
--   access or change only resources with certain tag values. You can use
--   the <tt>TagResource</tt> operation with a resource that already has
--   tags. If you specify a new tag key for the resource, this tag is
--   appended to the list of tags associated with the resource. If you
--   specify a tag key that is already associated with the resource, the
--   new tag value that you specify replaces the previous value for that
--   tag.
--   
--   You can associate as many as 50 tags with a resource. Amazon
--   QuickSight supports tagging on data set, data source, dashboard, and
--   template.
--   
--   Tagging for Amazon QuickSight works in a similar way to tagging for
--   other AWS services, except for the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>You can't use tags to track AWS costs for Amazon QuickSight. This
--   restriction is because Amazon QuickSight costs are based on users and
--   SPICE capacity, which aren't taggable resources.</li>
--   <li>Amazon QuickSight doesn't currently support the Tag Editor for
--   Resource Groups.</li>
--   </ul>
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.TagResource

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newTagResource</a> smart constructor.
data TagResource
TagResource' :: Text -> NonEmpty Tag -> TagResource

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource that you want to tag.
[$sel:resourceArn:TagResource'] :: TagResource -> Text

-- | Contains a map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or tags
--   assigned to the resource.
[$sel:tags:TagResource'] :: TagResource -> NonEmpty Tag

-- | Create a value of <a>TagResource</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:resourceArn:TagResource'</a>, <a>tagResource_resourceArn</a> -
--   The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource that you want to tag.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:TagResource'</a>, <a>tagResource_tags</a> - Contains a
--   map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or tags assigned to
--   the resource.
newTagResource :: Text -> NonEmpty Tag -> TagResource

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the resource that you want to tag.
tagResource_resourceArn :: Lens' TagResource Text

-- | Contains a map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or tags
--   assigned to the resource.
tagResource_tags :: Lens' TagResource (NonEmpty Tag)

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newTagResourceResponse</a> smart constructor.
data TagResourceResponse
TagResourceResponse' :: Maybe Text -> Int -> TagResourceResponse

-- | The Amazon Web Services request ID for this operation.
[$sel:requestId:TagResourceResponse'] :: TagResourceResponse -> Maybe Text

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
[$sel:status:TagResourceResponse'] :: TagResourceResponse -> Int

-- | Create a value of <a>TagResourceResponse</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestId:TagResourceResponse'</a>,
--   <a>tagResourceResponse_requestId</a> - The Amazon Web Services request
--   ID for this operation.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:TagResourceResponse'</a>,
--   <a>tagResourceResponse_status</a> - The HTTP status of the request.
newTagResourceResponse :: Int -> TagResourceResponse

-- | The Amazon Web Services request ID for this operation.
tagResourceResponse_requestId :: Lens' TagResourceResponse (Maybe Text)

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
tagResourceResponse_status :: Lens' TagResourceResponse Int

-- | Searches the subfolders in a folder.

data SearchFolders

--   results.

-- | The filters to apply to the search. Currently, you can search only by
--   the parent folder ARN. For example, <tt>"Filters": [ { "Name":
--   "PARENT_FOLDER_ARN", "Operator": "StringEquals", "Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:folder/folderId" } ]</tt>.
[$sel:filters:SearchFolders'] :: SearchFolders -> [FolderSearchFilter]

-- | Create a value of <a>SearchFolders</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   The token for the next set of results, or null if there are no more
--   results.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxResults:SearchFolders'</a>, <a>searchFolders_maxResults</a>
--   - The maximum number of results to be returned per request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:SearchFolders'</a>,
--   <a>searchFolders_awsAccountId</a> - The AWS account ID.

--   <a>$sel:filters:SearchFolders'</a>, <a>searchFolders_filters</a> - The
--   filters to apply to the search. Currently, you can search only by the

-- | The filters to apply to the search. Currently, you can search only by

--   "PARENT_FOLDER_ARN", "Operator": "StringEquals", "Value":

-- | Searches for dashboards that belong to a user.
--   
--   This operation is eventually consistent. The results are best effort
--   and may not reflect very recent updates and changes.
--   
--   This operation returns paginated results.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.SearchDashboards

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newSearchDashboards</a> smart constructor.
data SearchDashboards

--   dashboards you're searching for.

-- | The filters to apply to the search. Currently, you can search only by
--   user name, for example, <tt>"Filters": [ { "Name": "QUICKSIGHT_USER",
--   "Operator": "StringEquals", "Value":
--   "arn:aws:quicksight:us-east-1:1:user/default/UserName1" } ]</tt>
[$sel:filters:SearchDashboards'] :: SearchDashboards -> NonEmpty DashboardSearchFilter

-- | Create a value of <a>SearchDashboards</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   results, or null if there are no more results.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxResults:SearchDashboards'</a>,
--   <a>searchDashboards_maxResults</a> - The maximum number of results to
--   be returned per request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:SearchDashboards'</a>,
--   <a>searchDashboards_awsAccountId</a> - The ID of the Amazon Web
--   Services account that contains the user whose dashboards you're
--   searching for.

-- | Searches for analyses that belong to the user specified in the filter.
--   
--   This operation is eventually consistent. The results are best effort
--   and may not reflect very recent updates and changes.
--   
--   This operation returns paginated results.

--   search.
[$sel:filters:SearchAnalyses'] :: SearchAnalyses -> NonEmpty AnalysisSearchFilter

-- | Create a value of <a>SearchAnalyses</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   - A pagination token that can be used in a subsequent request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:maxResults:SearchAnalyses'</a>,
--   <a>searchAnalyses_maxResults</a> - The maximum number of results to
--   return.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:SearchAnalyses'</a>,
--   <a>searchAnalyses_awsAccountId</a> - The ID of the Amazon Web Services
--   account that contains the analyses that you're searching for.
--   
--   <a>$sel:filters:SearchAnalyses'</a>, <a>searchAnalyses_filters</a> -
--   The structure for the search filters that you want to apply to your
--   search.
newSearchAnalyses :: Text -> NonEmpty AnalysisSearchFilter -> SearchAnalyses

-- | A pagination token that can be used in a subsequent request.
searchAnalyses_nextToken :: Lens' SearchAnalyses (Maybe Text)

-- | The maximum number of results to return.
searchAnalyses_maxResults :: Lens' SearchAnalyses (Maybe Natural)

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that contains the analyses
--   that you're searching for.
searchAnalyses_awsAccountId :: Lens' SearchAnalyses Text

-- | The structure for the search filters that you want to apply to your
--   search.
searchAnalyses_filters :: Lens' SearchAnalyses (NonEmpty AnalysisSearchFilter)

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newSearchAnalysesResponse</a> smart constructor.
data SearchAnalysesResponse

-- | The Amazon Web Services request ID for this operation.

-- | A pagination token that can be used in a subsequent request.

-- | Metadata describing the analyses that you searched for.
[$sel:analysisSummaryList:SearchAnalysesResponse'] :: SearchAnalysesResponse -> Maybe [AnalysisSummary]

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
[$sel:status:SearchAnalysesResponse'] :: SearchAnalysesResponse -> Int

--   fields omitted.

-- | Creates an Amazon QuickSight user, whose identity is associated with
--   the AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) identity or role
--   specified in the request.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.RegisterUser

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newRegisterUser</a> smart constructor.
data RegisterUser
RegisterUser' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> IdentityType -> Text -> UserRole -> Text -> Text -> RegisterUser

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user name that you want to create for the user
--   you are registering.
[$sel:userName:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Maybe Text

-- | (Enterprise edition only) The name of the custom permissions profile
--   that you want to assign to this user. Customized permissions allows
--   you to control a user's access by restricting access the following
--   operations:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Create and update data sources</li>
--   <li>Create and update datasets</li>
--   <li>Create and update email reports</li>
--   <li>Subscribe to email reports</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   To add custom permissions to an existing user, use <tt> UpdateUser
--   </tt> instead.
--   
--   A set of custom permissions includes any combination of these
--   restrictions. Currently, you need to create the profile names for
--   custom permission sets by using the Amazon QuickSight console. Then,
--   you use the <tt>RegisterUser</tt> API operation to assign the named
--   set of permissions to a Amazon QuickSight user.
--   
--   Amazon QuickSight custom permissions are applied through IAMpolicies.
--   Therefore, they override the permissions typically granted by
--   assigning Amazon QuickSight users to one of the default security
--   cohorts in Amazon QuickSight (admin, author, reader).
--   
--   This feature is available only to Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition
--   subscriptions.
[$sel:customPermissionsName:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The URL of the custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider that provides
--   identity to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an
--   associated Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. This parameter
--   should only be used when <tt>ExternalLoginFederationProviderType</tt>
--   parameter is set to <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>.
[$sel:customFederationProviderUrl:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. The type of supported
--   external login provider can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com. When choosing the <tt>COGNITO</tt>
--   provider type, dont use the "CustomFederationProviderUrl" parameter
--   which is only needed when the external provider is custom.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider. When
--   choosing <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt> type, use the
--   <tt>CustomFederationProviderUrl</tt> parameter to provide the custom
--   OIDC provider URL.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The ARN of the IAMuser or role that you are registering with Amazon
--   QuickSight.
[$sel:iamArn:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The identity ID for a user in the external login provider.
[$sel:externalLoginId:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Maybe Text

-- | You need to use this parameter only when you register one or more
--   users using an assumed IAMrole. You don't need to provide the session
--   name for other scenarios, for example when you are registering an
--   IAMuser or an Amazon QuickSight user. You can register multiple users
--   using the same IAMrole if each user has a different session name. For
--   more information on assuming IAMroles, see <a>assume-role</a> in the
--   <i>AWS CLI Reference.</i>
[$sel:sessionName:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Maybe Text

-- | Amazon QuickSight supports several ways of managing the identity of
--   users. This parameter accepts two values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>IAM</tt>: A user whose identity maps to an existing IAMuser or
--   role.</li>
--   <li><tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt>: A user whose identity is owned and managed
--   internally by Amazon QuickSight.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:identityType:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> IdentityType

-- | The email address of the user that you want to register.
[$sel:email:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight role for the user. The user role can be one of
--   the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:userRole:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> UserRole

-- | The ID for the Amazon Web Services account that the user is in.
--   Currently, you use the ID for the Amazon Web Services account that
--   contains your Amazon QuickSight account.
[$sel:awsAccountId:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Text

-- | The namespace. Currently, you should set this to <tt>default</tt>.
[$sel:namespace:RegisterUser'] :: RegisterUser -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RegisterUser</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:userName:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_userName</a> - The
--   Amazon QuickSight user name that you want to create for the user you
--   are registering.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customPermissionsName:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_customPermissionsName</a> - (Enterprise edition only)
--   The name of the custom permissions profile that you want to assign to
--   this user. Customized permissions allows you to control a user's
--   access by restricting access the following operations:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Create and update data sources</li>
--   <li>Create and update datasets</li>
--   <li>Create and update email reports</li>
--   <li>Subscribe to email reports</li>
--   </ul>

--   To add custom permissions to an existing user, use <tt> UpdateUser
--   </tt> instead.

--   A set of custom permissions includes any combination of these
--   restrictions. Currently, you need to create the profile names for

--   Therefore, they override the permissions typically granted by
--   assigning Amazon QuickSight users to one of the default security
--   cohorts in Amazon QuickSight (admin, author, reader).

--   This feature is available only to Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition
--   subscriptions.

--   <a>$sel:customFederationProviderUrl:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_customFederationProviderUrl</a> - The URL of the

--   <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>.

--   OIDC provider URL.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:iamArn:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_iamArn</a> - The ARN
--   of the IAMuser or role that you are registering with Amazon
--   QuickSight.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginId:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_externalLoginId</a> - The identity ID for a user in
--   the external login provider.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sessionName:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_sessionName</a>
--   - You need to use this parameter only when you register one or more
--   users using an assumed IAMrole. You don't need to provide the session
--   name for other scenarios, for example when you are registering an
--   IAMuser or an Amazon QuickSight user. You can register multiple users
--   using the same IAMrole if each user has a different session name. For
--   more information on assuming IAMroles, see <a>assume-role</a> in the
--   <i>AWS CLI Reference.</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:identityType:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_identityType</a> - Amazon QuickSight supports several
--   ways of managing the identity of users. This parameter accepts two
--   values:

--   role.</li>
--   <li><tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt>: A user whose identity is owned and managed
--   internally by Amazon QuickSight.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:email:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_email</a> - The email
--   address of the user that you want to register.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userRole:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_userRole</a> - The
--   Amazon QuickSight role for the user. The user role can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>

--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>

newRegisterUser :: IdentityType -> Text -> UserRole -> Text -> Text -> RegisterUser

RegisterUserResponse' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe User -> Int -> RegisterUserResponse

[$sel:requestId:RegisterUserResponse'] :: RegisterUserResponse -> Maybe Text

-- | The URL the user visits to complete registration and provide a
--   password. This is returned only for users with an identity type of

-- | Generates a session URL and authorization code that you can use to
--   embed the Amazon Amazon QuickSight console in your web server code.
--   Use <tt>GetSessionEmbedUrl</tt> where you want to provide an authoring
--   portal that allows users to create data sources, datasets, analyses,
--   and dashboards. The users who access an embedded Amazon QuickSight
--   console need belong to the author or admin security cohort. If you
--   want to restrict permissions to some of these features, add a custom
--   permissions profile to the user with the <tt> UpdateUser </tt> API
--   operation. Use <tt> RegisterUser </tt> API operation to add a new user
--   with a custom permission profile attached. For more information, see
--   the following sections in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide</i>:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><a>Embedding Analytics</a></li>
--   <li><a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a></li>
--   </ul>
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.GetSessionEmbedUrl

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newGetSessionEmbedUrl</a> smart constructor.
data GetSessionEmbedUrl
GetSessionEmbedUrl' :: Maybe Natural -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Text -> GetSessionEmbedUrl

-- | How many minutes the session is valid. The session lifetime must be
--   15-600 minutes.
[$sel:sessionLifetimeInMinutes:GetSessionEmbedUrl'] :: GetSessionEmbedUrl -> Maybe Natural

-- | The URL you use to access the embedded session. The entry point URL is
--   constrained to the following paths:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>/start</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/analyses</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/dashboards</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/favorites</pre></li>
--   <li><tt>/dashboards/DashboardId </tt> - where <tt>DashboardId</tt> is
--   the actual ID key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the
--   dashboard</li>
--   <li><tt>/analyses/AnalysisId </tt> - where <tt>AnalysisId</tt> is the
--   actual ID key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the
--   analysis</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:entryPoint:GetSessionEmbedUrl'] :: GetSessionEmbedUrl -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), for use with
--   <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt> identity type. You can use this for any type of
--   Amazon QuickSight users in your account (readers, authors, or admins).
--   They need to be authenticated as one of the following:
--   
--   <ol>
--   <li>Active Directory (AD) users or group members</li>
--   <li>Invited nonfederated users</li>
--   <li>Identity and Access Management (IAM) users and IAM role-based
--   sessions authenticated through Federated Single Sign-On using SAML,
--   OpenID Connect, or IAM federation</li>
--   </ol>
--   
--   Omit this parameter for users in the third group, IAM users and IAM
--   role-based sessions.
[$sel:userArn:GetSessionEmbedUrl'] :: GetSessionEmbedUrl -> Maybe Text

-- | The ID for the Amazon Web Services account associated with your Amazon
--   QuickSight subscription.
[$sel:awsAccountId:GetSessionEmbedUrl'] :: GetSessionEmbedUrl -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>GetSessionEmbedUrl</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:sessionLifetimeInMinutes:GetSessionEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getSessionEmbedUrl_sessionLifetimeInMinutes</a> - How many minutes
--   the session is valid. The session lifetime must be 15-600 minutes.
--   
--   <a>$sel:entryPoint:GetSessionEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getSessionEmbedUrl_entryPoint</a> - The URL you use to access the
--   embedded session. The entry point URL is constrained to the following
--   paths:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><pre>/start</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/analyses</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/dashboards</pre></li>
--   <li><pre>/start/favorites</pre></li>
--   <li><tt>/dashboards/DashboardId </tt> - where <tt>DashboardId</tt> is
--   the actual ID key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the
--   dashboard</li>
--   <li><tt>/analyses/AnalysisId </tt> - where <tt>AnalysisId</tt> is the
--   actual ID key from the Amazon QuickSight console URL of the
--   analysis</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:userArn:GetSessionEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getSessionEmbedUrl_userArn</a> - The Amazon QuickSight user's
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN), for use with <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt> identity
--   type. You can use this for any type of Amazon QuickSight users in your
--   account (readers, authors, or admins). They need to be authenticated
--   as one of the following:
--   
--   <ol>
--   <li>Active Directory (AD) users or group members</li>
--   <li>Invited nonfederated users</li>
--   <li>Identity and Access Management (IAM) users and IAM role-based
--   sessions authenticated through Federated Single Sign-On using SAML,
--   OpenID Connect, or IAM federation</li>
--   </ol>
--   
--   Omit this parameter for users in the third group, IAM users and IAM
--   role-based sessions.

--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:GetSessionEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getSessionEmbedUrl_awsAccountId</a> - The ID for the Amazon Web
--   Services account associated with your Amazon QuickSight subscription.
newGetSessionEmbedUrl :: Text -> GetSessionEmbedUrl

-- | How many minutes the session is valid. The session lifetime must be
--   15-600 minutes.
getSessionEmbedUrl_sessionLifetimeInMinutes :: Lens' GetSessionEmbedUrl (Maybe Natural)

-- | The URL you use to access the embedded session. The entry point URL is
--   constrained to the following paths:

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), for use with

-- | Generates a session URL and authorization code that you can use to
--   embed an Amazon Amazon QuickSight read-only dashboard in your web
--   server code. Before you use this command, make sure that you have
--   configured the dashboards and permissions.
--   
--   Currently, you can use <tt>GetDashboardEmbedURL</tt> only from the
--   server, not from the user's browser. The following rules apply to the
--   combination of URL and authorization code:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>They must be used together.</li>
--   <li>They can be used one time only.</li>
--   <li>They are valid for 5 minutes after you run this command.</li>
--   <li>The resulting user session is valid for 10 hours.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Embedding Analytics Using
--   GetDashboardEmbedUrl</a> in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide</i>.
--   
--   For more information about the high-level steps for embedding and for
--   an interactive demo of the ways you can customize embedding, visit the
--   <a>Amazon QuickSight Developer Portal</a>.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.GetDashboardEmbedUrl

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newGetDashboardEmbedUrl</a> smart constructor.
data GetDashboardEmbedUrl
GetDashboardEmbedUrl' :: Maybe Natural -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (NonEmpty Text) -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Text -> Text -> EmbeddingIdentityType -> GetDashboardEmbedUrl

-- | How many minutes the session is valid. The session lifetime must be
--   15-600 minutes.
[$sel:sessionLifetimeInMinutes:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Maybe Natural

-- | Adds persistence of state for the user session in an embedded
--   dashboard. Persistence applies to the sheet and the parameter
--   settings. These are control settings that the dashboard subscriber
--   (Amazon QuickSight reader) chooses while viewing the dashboard. If
--   this is set to <tt>TRUE</tt>, the settings are the same when the
--   subscriber reopens the same dashboard URL. The state is stored in
--   Amazon QuickSight, not in a browser cookie. If this is set to FALSE,
--   the state of the user session is not persisted. The default is
--   <tt>FALSE</tt>.
[$sel:statePersistenceEnabled:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon QuickSight namespace that contains the dashboard IDs in
--   this request. If you're not using a custom namespace, set
--   <tt>Namespace = default</tt>.
[$sel:namespace:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of one or more dashboard IDs that you want to add to a session
--   that includes anonymous users. The <tt>IdentityType</tt> parameter
--   must be set to <tt>ANONYMOUS</tt> for this to work, because other
--   identity types authenticate as Amazon QuickSight or IAMusers. For
--   example, if you set "<tt>--dashboard-id dash_id1 --dashboard-id
--   dash_id2 dash_id3 identity-type ANONYMOUS</tt>", the session can
--   access all three dashboards.
[$sel:additionalDashboardIds:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Maybe (NonEmpty Text)

-- | Remove the undo/redo button on the embedded dashboard. The default is
--   FALSE, which enables the undo/redo button.
[$sel:undoRedoDisabled:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Maybe Bool

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), for use with
--   <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt> identity type. You can use this for any Amazon
--   QuickSight users in your account (readers, authors, or admins)
--   authenticated as one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Active Directory (AD) users or group members</li>
--   <li>Invited nonfederated users</li>
--   <li>IAMusers and IAMrole-based sessions authenticated through
--   Federated Single Sign-On using SAML, OpenID Connect, or
--   IAMfederation.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Omit this parameter for users in the third group  IAMusers and IAM
--   role-based sessions.
[$sel:userArn:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Maybe Text

-- | Remove the reset button on the embedded dashboard. The default is
--   FALSE, which enables the reset button.
[$sel:resetDisabled:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Maybe Bool

-- | The ID for the Amazon Web Services account that contains the dashboard
--   that you're embedding.
[$sel:awsAccountId:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Text

-- | The ID for the dashboard, also added to the Identity and Access
--   Management (IAM) policy.
[$sel:dashboardId:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> Text

-- | The authentication method that the user uses to sign in.
[$sel:identityType:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'] :: GetDashboardEmbedUrl -> EmbeddingIdentityType

-- | Create a value of <a>GetDashboardEmbedUrl</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:sessionLifetimeInMinutes:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_sessionLifetimeInMinutes</a> - How many
--   minutes the session is valid. The session lifetime must be 15-600
--   minutes.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statePersistenceEnabled:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_statePersistenceEnabled</a> - Adds persistence
--   of state for the user session in an embedded dashboard. Persistence
--   applies to the sheet and the parameter settings. These are control
--   settings that the dashboard subscriber (Amazon QuickSight reader)
--   chooses while viewing the dashboard. If this is set to <tt>TRUE</tt>,
--   the settings are the same when the subscriber reopens the same
--   dashboard URL. The state is stored in Amazon QuickSight, not in a
--   browser cookie. If this is set to FALSE, the state of the user session
--   is not persisted. The default is <tt>FALSE</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_namespace</a> - The Amazon QuickSight
--   namespace that contains the dashboard IDs in this request. If you're
--   not using a custom namespace, set <tt>Namespace = default</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:additionalDashboardIds:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_additionalDashboardIds</a> - A list of one or
--   more dashboard IDs that you want to add to a session that includes
--   anonymous users. The <tt>IdentityType</tt> parameter must be set to
--   <tt>ANONYMOUS</tt> for this to work, because other identity types
--   authenticate as Amazon QuickSight or IAMusers. For example, if you set
--   "<tt>--dashboard-id dash_id1 --dashboard-id dash_id2 dash_id3
--   identity-type ANONYMOUS</tt>", the session can access all three
--   dashboards.
--   
--   <a>$sel:undoRedoDisabled:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_undoRedoDisabled</a> - Remove the undo/redo
--   button on the embedded dashboard. The default is FALSE, which enables
--   the undo/redo button.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userArn:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_userArn</a> - The Amazon QuickSight user's
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN), for use with <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt> identity

--   (readers, authors, or admins) authenticated as one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>

--   <li>Invited nonfederated users</li>
--   <li>IAMusers and IAMrole-based sessions authenticated through
--   Federated Single Sign-On using SAML, OpenID Connect, or
--   IAMfederation.</li>
--   </ul>

--   Omit this parameter for users in the third group  IAMusers and IAM
--   role-based sessions.
--   
--   <a>$sel:resetDisabled:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_resetDisabled</a> - Remove the reset button on
--   the embedded dashboard. The default is FALSE, which enables the reset
--   button.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_awsAccountId</a> - The ID for the Amazon Web
--   Services account that contains the dashboard that you're embedding.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dashboardId:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_dashboardId</a> - The ID for the dashboard,
--   also added to the Identity and Access Management (IAM) policy.
--   
--   <a>$sel:identityType:GetDashboardEmbedUrl'</a>,
--   <a>getDashboardEmbedUrl_identityType</a> - The authentication method
--   that the user uses to sign in.
newGetDashboardEmbedUrl :: Text -> Text -> EmbeddingIdentityType -> GetDashboardEmbedUrl

-- | How many minutes the session is valid. The session lifetime must be
--   15-600 minutes.
getDashboardEmbedUrl_sessionLifetimeInMinutes :: Lens' GetDashboardEmbedUrl (Maybe Natural)

-- | Adds persistence of state for the user session in an embedded
--   dashboard. Persistence applies to the sheet and the parameter
--   settings. These are control settings that the dashboard subscriber
--   (Amazon QuickSight reader) chooses while viewing the dashboard. If
--   this is set to <tt>TRUE</tt>, the settings are the same when the
--   subscriber reopens the same dashboard URL. The state is stored in
--   Amazon QuickSight, not in a browser cookie. If this is set to FALSE,
--   the state of the user session is not persisted. The default is
--   <tt>FALSE</tt>.
getDashboardEmbedUrl_statePersistenceEnabled :: Lens' GetDashboardEmbedUrl (Maybe Bool)

-- | The Amazon QuickSight namespace that contains the dashboard IDs in
--   this request. If you're not using a custom namespace, set
--   <tt>Namespace = default</tt>.
getDashboardEmbedUrl_namespace :: Lens' GetDashboardEmbedUrl (Maybe Text)

-- | A list of one or more dashboard IDs that you want to add to a session
--   that includes anonymous users. The <tt>IdentityType</tt> parameter
--   must be set to <tt>ANONYMOUS</tt> for this to work, because other
--   identity types authenticate as Amazon QuickSight or IAMusers. For
--   example, if you set "<tt>--dashboard-id dash_id1 --dashboard-id
--   dash_id2 dash_id3 identity-type ANONYMOUS</tt>", the session can
--   access all three dashboards.
getDashboardEmbedUrl_additionalDashboardIds :: Lens' GetDashboardEmbedUrl (Maybe (NonEmpty Text))

-- | Remove the undo/redo button on the embedded dashboard. The default is
--   FALSE, which enables the undo/redo button.
getDashboardEmbedUrl_undoRedoDisabled :: Lens' GetDashboardEmbedUrl (Maybe Bool)

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user's Amazon Resource Name (ARN), for use with
--   <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt> identity type. You can use this for any Amazon
--   QuickSight users in your account (readers, authors, or admins)
--   authenticated as one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Active Directory (AD) users or group members</li>
--   <li>Invited nonfederated users</li>
--   <li>IAMusers and IAMrole-based sessions authenticated through
--   Federated Single Sign-On using SAML, OpenID Connect, or
--   IAMfederation.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   Omit this parameter for users in the third group  IAMusers and IAM
--   role-based sessions.
getDashboardEmbedUrl_userArn :: Lens' GetDashboardEmbedUrl (Maybe Text)

-- | Remove the reset button on the embedded dashboard. The default is
--   FALSE, which enables the reset button.
getDashboardEmbedUrl_resetDisabled :: Lens' GetDashboardEmbedUrl (Maybe Bool)

-- | Generates an embed URL that you can use to embed an Amazon QuickSight
--   experience in your website. This action can be used for any type of
--   user registered in an Amazon QuickSight account. Before you use this
--   action, make sure that you have configured the relevant Amazon
--   QuickSight resource and permissions.
--   
--   The following rules apply to the generated URL:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>It contains a temporary bearer token. It is valid for 5 minutes
--   after it is generated. Once redeemed within this period, it cannot be
--   re-used again.</li>
--   <li>The URL validity period should not be confused with the actual
--   session lifetime that can be customized using the <tt>
--   SessionLifetimeInMinutes </tt> parameter.The resulting user session is
--   valid for 15 minutes (default) to 10 hours (maximum).</li>
--   <li>You are charged only when the URL is used or there is interaction
--   with Amazon QuickSight.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Embedded Analytics</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   QuickSight User Guide</i>.
--   
--   For more information about the high-level steps for embedding and for
--   an interactive demo of the ways you can customize embedding, visit the
--   <a>Amazon QuickSight Developer Portal</a>.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.GenerateEmbedUrlForRegisteredUser

-- | Generates an embed URL that you can use to embed an Amazon QuickSight
--   dashboard in your website, without having to register any reader
--   users. Before you use this action, make sure that you have configured
--   the dashboards and permissions.
--   
--   The following rules apply to the generated URL:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>It contains a temporary bearer token. It is valid for 5 minutes
--   after it is generated. Once redeemed within this period, it cannot be
--   re-used again.</li>
--   <li>The URL validity period should not be confused with the actual
--   session lifetime that can be customized using the <tt>
--   SessionLifetimeInMinutes </tt> parameter.The resulting user session is
--   valid for 15 minutes (default) to 10 hours (maximum).</li>
--   <li>You are charged only when the URL is used or there is interaction
--   with Amazon QuickSight.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Embedded Analytics</a> in the <i>Amazon
--   QuickSight User Guide</i>.

--   For more information about the high-level steps for embedding and for
--   an interactive demo of the ways you can customize embedding, visit the
--   <a>Amazon QuickSight Developer Portal</a>.

-- | Describes a theme.

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newDescribeTheme</a> smart constructor.
data DescribeTheme
DescribeTheme' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Natural -> Text -> Text -> DescribeTheme

-- | The alias of the theme that you want to describe. If you name a
--   specific alias, you describe the version that the alias points to. You
--   can specify the latest version of the theme by providing the keyword
--   <tt>$LATEST</tt> in the <tt>AliasName</tt> parameter. The keyword
--   <tt>$PUBLISHED</tt> doesn't apply to themes.
[$sel:aliasName:DescribeTheme'] :: DescribeTheme -> Maybe Text

-- | The version number for the version to describe. If a
--   <tt>VersionNumber</tt> parameter value isn't provided, the latest
--   version of the theme is described.
[$sel:versionNumber:DescribeTheme'] :: DescribeTheme -> Maybe Natural

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that contains the theme that
--   you're describing.
[$sel:awsAccountId:DescribeTheme'] :: DescribeTheme -> Text

--   <tt>$LATEST</tt> in the <tt>AliasName</tt> parameter. The keyword

-- | Describes read and write permissions for a dashboard.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.DescribeDashboardPermissions

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newDescribeDashboardPermissions</a> smart constructor.
data DescribeDashboardPermissions
DescribeDashboardPermissions' :: Text -> Text -> DescribeDashboardPermissions

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that contains the dashboard
--   that you're describing permissions for.
[$sel:awsAccountId:DescribeDashboardPermissions'] :: DescribeDashboardPermissions -> Text

-- | Describes the settings that were used when your Amazon QuickSight

--   that you want to list.

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newDescribeAccountSettingsResponse</a> smart
--   constructor.
data DescribeAccountSettingsResponse
DescribeAccountSettingsResponse' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe AccountSettings -> Int -> DescribeAccountSettingsResponse

-- | The Amazon Web Services request ID for this operation.
[$sel:requestId:DescribeAccountSettingsResponse'] :: DescribeAccountSettingsResponse -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight settings for this Amazon Web Services account.
--   This information includes the edition of Amazon Amazon QuickSight that
--   you subscribed to (Standard or Enterprise) and the notification email
--   for the Amazon QuickSight subscription. In the Amazon QuickSight
--   console, the Amazon QuickSight subscription is sometimes referred to
--   as a Amazon QuickSight "account" even though it's technically not an
--   account by itself. Instead, it's a subscription to the Amazon
--   QuickSight service for your Amazon Web Services account. The edition
--   that you subscribe to applies to Amazon QuickSight in every Amazon Web
--   Services Region where you use it.
[$sel:accountSettings:DescribeAccountSettingsResponse'] :: DescribeAccountSettingsResponse -> Maybe AccountSettings

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
[$sel:status:DescribeAccountSettingsResponse'] :: DescribeAccountSettingsResponse -> Int

-- | Create a value of <a>DescribeAccountSettingsResponse</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:requestId:DescribeAccountSettingsResponse'</a>,
--   <a>describeAccountSettingsResponse_requestId</a> - The Amazon Web
--   Services request ID for this operation.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accountSettings:DescribeAccountSettingsResponse'</a>,
--   <a>describeAccountSettingsResponse_accountSettings</a> - The Amazon
--   QuickSight settings for this Amazon Web Services account. This
--   information includes the edition of Amazon Amazon QuickSight that you
--   subscribed to (Standard or Enterprise) and the notification email for
--   the Amazon QuickSight subscription. In the Amazon QuickSight console,
--   the Amazon QuickSight subscription is sometimes referred to as a
--   Amazon QuickSight "account" even though it's technically not an
--   account by itself. Instead, it's a subscription to the Amazon
--   QuickSight service for your Amazon Web Services account. The edition
--   that you subscribe to applies to Amazon QuickSight in every Amazon Web
--   Services Region where you use it.
--

--   console, the Amazon QuickSight subscription is sometimes referred to
--   as a Amazon QuickSight "account" even though it's technically not an
--   account by itself. Instead, it's a subscription to the Amazon
--   QuickSight service for your Amazon Web Services account. The edition

--   Services Region where you use it.

-- | Describes the customizations associated with the provided Amazon Web
--   Services account and Amazon Amazon QuickSight namespace in an Amazon
--   Web Services Region. The Amazon QuickSight console evaluates which
--   customizations to apply by running this API operation with the
--   <tt>Resolved</tt> flag included.
--   
--   To determine what customizations display when you run this command, it
--   can help to visualize the relationship of the entities involved.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>Amazon Web Services account</tt> - The Amazon Web Services
--   account exists at the top of the hierarchy. It has the potential to
--   use all of the Amazon Web Services Regions and AWS Services. When you
--   subscribe to Amazon QuickSight, you choose one Amazon Web Services
--   Region to use as your home Region. That's where your free SPICE
--   capacity is located. You can use Amazon QuickSight in any supported
--   Amazon Web Services Region.</li>
--   <li><tt>Amazon Web Services Region</tt> - In each Amazon Web Services
--   Region where you sign in to Amazon QuickSight at least once, Amazon
--   QuickSight acts as a separate instance of the same service. If you
--   have a user directory, it resides in us-east-1, which is the US East
--   (N. Virginia). Generally speaking, these users have access to Amazon
--   QuickSight in any Amazon Web Services Region, unless they are
--   constrained to a namespace.To run the command in a different Amazon
--   Web Services Region, you change your Region settings. If you're using
--   the AWS CLI, you can use one of the following options:<ul><li>Use
--   <a>command line options</a>.</li><li>Use <a>named
--   profiles</a>.</li><li>Run <tt>aws configure</tt> to change your
--   default Amazon Web Services Region. Use Enter to key the same settings
--   for your keys. For more information, see <a>Configuring the AWS
--   CLI</a>.</li></ul></li>
--   <li><tt>Namespace</tt> - A Amazon QuickSight namespace is a partition
--   that contains users and assets (data sources, datasets, dashboards,
--   and so on). To access assets that are in a specific namespace, users
--   and groups must also be part of the same namespace. People who share a
--   namespace are completely isolated from users and assets in other
--   namespaces, even if they are in the same Amazon Web Services account
--   and Amazon Web Services Region.</li>
--   <li><tt>Applied customizations</tt> - Within an Amazon Web Services
--   Region, a set of Amazon QuickSight customizations can apply to an
--   Amazon Web Services account or to a namespace. Settings that you apply
--   to a namespace override settings that you apply to an Amazon Web
--   Services account. All settings are isolated to a single Amazon Web
--   Services Region. To apply them in other Amazon Web Services Regions,
--   run the <tt>CreateAccountCustomization</tt> command in each Amazon Web
--   Services Region where you want to apply the same customizations.</li>
--   </ul>
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.DescribeAccountCustomization

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newDescribeAccountCustomization</a> smart constructor.
data DescribeAccountCustomization
DescribeAccountCustomization' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Text -> DescribeAccountCustomization

--   You can add this flag to your command to use the same view that Amazon
--   QuickSight uses to identify which customizations to apply to the
--   console. Omit this flag, or set it to <tt>no-resolved</tt>, to reveal
--   customizations that are configured at different levels.

-- | Deletes an analysis from Amazon QuickSight. You can optionally include
--   a recovery window during which you can restore the analysis. If you
--   don't specify a recovery window value, the operation defaults to 30
--   days. Amazon QuickSight attaches a <tt>DeletionTime</tt> stamp to the
--   response that specifies the end of the recovery window. At the end of
--   the recovery window, Amazon QuickSight deletes the analysis
--   permanently.
--   
--   At any time before recovery window ends, you can use the
--   <tt>RestoreAnalysis</tt> API operation to remove the
--   <tt>DeletionTime</tt> stamp and cancel the deletion of the analysis.
--   The analysis remains visible in the API until it's deleted, so you can
--   describe it but you can't make a template from it.
--   
--   An analysis that's scheduled for deletion isn't accessible in the
--   Amazon QuickSight console. To access it in the console, restore it.
--   Deleting an analysis doesn't delete the dashboards that you publish
--   from it.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.DeleteAnalysis

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newDeleteAnalysis</a> smart constructor.
data DeleteAnalysis
DeleteAnalysis' :: Maybe Natural -> Maybe Bool -> Text -> Text -> DeleteAnalysis

-- | A value that specifies the number of days that Amazon QuickSight waits
--   before it deletes the analysis. You can't use this parameter with the
--   <tt>ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt> option in the same API call. The
--   default value is 30.
[$sel:recoveryWindowInDays:DeleteAnalysis'] :: DeleteAnalysis -> Maybe Natural

-- | This option defaults to the value
--   <tt>NoForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt>. To immediately delete the
--   analysis, add the <tt>ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt> option. You
--   can't restore an analysis after it's deleted.
[$sel:forceDeleteWithoutRecovery:DeleteAnalysis'] :: DeleteAnalysis -> Maybe Bool

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account where you want to delete an
--   analysis.
[$sel:awsAccountId:DeleteAnalysis'] :: DeleteAnalysis -> Text

-- | The ID of the analysis that you're deleting.
[$sel:analysisId:DeleteAnalysis'] :: DeleteAnalysis -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DeleteAnalysis</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:recoveryWindowInDays:DeleteAnalysis'</a>,
--   <a>deleteAnalysis_recoveryWindowInDays</a> - A value that specifies
--   the number of days that Amazon QuickSight waits before it deletes the
--   analysis. You can't use this parameter with the
--   <tt>ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt> option in the same API call. The
--   default value is 30.
--   
--   <a>$sel:forceDeleteWithoutRecovery:DeleteAnalysis'</a>,
--   <a>deleteAnalysis_forceDeleteWithoutRecovery</a> - This option
--   defaults to the value <tt>NoForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt>. To
--   immediately delete the analysis, add the
--   <tt>ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt> option. You can't restore an
--   analysis after it's deleted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:DeleteAnalysis'</a>,
--   <a>deleteAnalysis_awsAccountId</a> - The ID of the Amazon Web Services
--   account where you want to delete an analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:analysisId:DeleteAnalysis'</a>,
--   <a>deleteAnalysis_analysisId</a> - The ID of the analysis that you're
--   deleting.
newDeleteAnalysis :: Text -> Text -> DeleteAnalysis

-- | A value that specifies the number of days that Amazon QuickSight waits
--   before it deletes the analysis. You can't use this parameter with the
--   <tt>ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt> option in the same API call. The
--   default value is 30.
deleteAnalysis_recoveryWindowInDays :: Lens' DeleteAnalysis (Maybe Natural)

-- | This option defaults to the value
--   <tt>NoForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt>. To immediately delete the
--   analysis, add the <tt>ForceDeleteWithoutRecovery</tt> option. You
--   can't restore an analysis after it's deleted.

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account where you want to delete an

--   Services account that contains the theme for the new theme alias.
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeId:CreateThemeAlias'</a>, <a>createThemeAlias_themeId</a>
--   - An ID for the theme alias.
--   
--   <a>$sel:aliasName:CreateThemeAlias'</a>,
--   <a>createThemeAlias_aliasName</a> - The name that you want to give to
--   the theme alias that you are creating. The alias name can't begin with
--   a <tt>$</tt>. Alias names that start with <tt>$</tt> are reserved by
--   Amazon QuickSight.
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeVersionNumber:CreateThemeAlias'</a>,
--   <a>createThemeAlias_themeVersionNumber</a> - The version number of the
--   theme.

--   creating. The alias name can't begin with a <tt>$</tt>. Alias names
--   that start with <tt>$</tt> are reserved by Amazon QuickSight.

-- | Creates a template from an existing Amazon QuickSight analysis or
--   template. You can use the resulting template to create a dashboard.
--   
--   A <i>template</i> is an entity in Amazon QuickSight that encapsulates
--   the metadata required to create an analysis and that you can use to
--   create s dashboard. A template adds a layer of abstraction by using
--   placeholders to replace the dataset associated with the analysis. You
--   can use templates to create dashboards by replacing dataset
--   placeholders with datasets that follow the same schema that was used
--   to create the source analysis and template.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.CreateTemplate

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateTemplate</a> smart constructor.
data CreateTemplate
CreateTemplate' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (NonEmpty ResourcePermission) -> Maybe (NonEmpty Tag) -> Text -> Text -> TemplateSourceEntity -> CreateTemplate

-- | A description of the current template version being created. This API
--   operation creates the first version of the template. Every time
--   <tt>UpdateTemplate</tt> is called, a new version is created. Each
--   version of the template maintains a description of the version in the
--   <tt>VersionDescription</tt> field.
[$sel:versionDescription:CreateTemplate'] :: CreateTemplate -> Maybe Text

-- | A display name for the template.
[$sel:name:CreateTemplate'] :: CreateTemplate -> Maybe Text

-- | A list of resource permissions to be set on the template.
[$sel:permissions:CreateTemplate'] :: CreateTemplate -> Maybe (NonEmpty ResourcePermission)

-- | Contains a map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or tags
--   assigned to the resource.
[$sel:tags:CreateTemplate'] :: CreateTemplate -> Maybe (NonEmpty Tag)

-- | The ID for the Amazon Web Services account that the group is in. You
--   use the ID for the Amazon Web Services account that contains your
--   Amazon QuickSight account.
[$sel:awsAccountId:CreateTemplate'] :: CreateTemplate -> Text

-- | An ID for the template that you want to create. This template is
--   unique per Amazon Web Services Region; in each Amazon Web Services
--   account.
[$sel:templateId:CreateTemplate'] :: CreateTemplate -> Text

-- | The entity that you are using as a source when you create the
--   template. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you specify the type of object
--   you're using as source: <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> for a template or
--   <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> for an analysis. Both of these require an
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN). For <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the
--   ARN of the source template. For <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt>, specify the
--   ARN of the source analysis. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can
--   contain any Amazon Web Services account and any Amazon
--   QuickSight-supported Amazon Web Services Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> or <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> to list the
--   replacement datasets for the placeholders listed in the original. The
--   schema in each dataset must match its placeholder.
[$sel:sourceEntity:CreateTemplate'] :: CreateTemplate -> TemplateSourceEntity

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateTemplate</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional

--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:CreateTemplate'</a>, <a>createTemplate_tags</a> -
--   Contains a map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or tags
--   assigned to the resource.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:CreateTemplate'</a>,

-- | (Enterprise edition only) Creates a new namespace for you to use with
--   Amazon QuickSight.
--   
--   A namespace allows you to isolate the Amazon QuickSight users and
--   groups that are registered for that namespace. Users that access the
--   namespace can share assets only with other users or groups in the same
--   namespace. They can't see users and groups in other namespaces. You
--   can create a namespace after your Amazon Web Services account is
--   subscribed to Amazon QuickSight. The namespace must be unique within
--   the Amazon Web Services account. By default, there is a limit of 100
--   namespaces per Amazon Web Services account. To increase your limit,
--   create a ticket with Amazon Web Services Support.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.CreateNamespace

-- | Creates an assignment with one specified IAMpolicy, identified by its
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN). This policy assignment is attached to the
--   specified groups or users of Amazon QuickSight. Assignment names are
--   unique per Amazon Web Services account. To avoid overwriting rules in
--   other namespaces, use assignment names that are unique.

--   within an Amazon Web Services account.

-- | The status of the assignment. Possible values are as follows:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ENABLED</tt> - Anything specified in this assignment is used
--   when creating the data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DISABLED</tt> - This assignment isn't used when creating the
--   data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DRAFT</tt> - This assignment is an unfinished draft and isn't
--   used when creating the data source.</li>
--   </ul>

--   physical tables.

-- | Creates a dashboard from a template. To first create a template, see
--   the <tt> CreateTemplate </tt> API operation.
--   
--   A dashboard is an entity in Amazon QuickSight that identifies Amazon
--   QuickSight reports, created from analyses. You can share Amazon
--   QuickSight dashboards. With the right permissions, you can create
--   scheduled email reports from them. If you have the correct
--   permissions, you can create a dashboard from a template that exists in
--   a different Amazon Web Services account.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.CreateDashboard

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateDashboard</a> smart constructor.
data CreateDashboard
CreateDashboard' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe DashboardPublishOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Parameters -> Maybe (NonEmpty ResourcePermission) -> Maybe (NonEmpty Tag) -> Text -> Text -> Text -> DashboardSourceEntity -> CreateDashboard

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme that is being used for
--   this dashboard. If you add a value for this field, it overrides the
--   value that is used in the source entity. The theme ARN must exist in
--   the same Amazon Web Services account where you create the dashboard.
[$sel:themeArn:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Maybe Text

-- | Options for publishing the dashboard when you create it:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>AdHocFilteringOption</tt> -
--   This status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. When
--   this is set to <tt>DISABLED</tt>, Amazon QuickSight disables the left
--   filter pane on the published dashboard, which can be used for ad hoc
--   (one-time) filtering. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>ExportToCSVOption</tt> - This
--   status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. The visual
--   option to export data to .CSV format isn't enabled when this is set to
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>VisibilityState</tt> for <tt>SheetControlsOption</tt> - This
--   visibility state can be either <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> or
--   <tt>EXPANDED</tt>. This option is <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> by default.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:dashboardPublishOptions:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Maybe DashboardPublishOptions

-- | A description for the first version of the dashboard being created.
[$sel:versionDescription:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Maybe Text

-- | The parameters for the creation of the dashboard, which you want to
--   use to override the default settings. A dashboard can have any type of
--   parameters, and some parameters might accept multiple values.
[$sel:parameters:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Maybe Parameters

-- | A structure that contains the permissions of the dashboard. You can
--   use this structure for granting permissions by providing a list of
--   IAMaction information for each principal ARN.
--   
--   To specify no permissions, omit the permissions list.
[$sel:permissions:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Maybe (NonEmpty ResourcePermission)

-- | Contains a map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or tags
--   assigned to the dashboard.
[$sel:tags:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Maybe (NonEmpty Tag)

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account where you want to create the
--   dashboard.
[$sel:awsAccountId:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Text

-- | The ID for the dashboard, also added to the IAMpolicy.
[$sel:dashboardId:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Text

-- | The display name of the dashboard.
[$sel:name:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> Text

-- | The entity that you are using as a source when you create the
--   dashboard. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you specify the type of object
--   you're using as source. You can only create a dashboard from a
--   template, so you use a <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> entity. If you need to
--   create a dashboard from an analysis, first convert the analysis to a
--   template by using the CreateTemplate API operation. For
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the
--   source template. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>ARN can contain any Amazon
--   Web Services account and any Amazon QuickSight-supported Amazon Web
--   Services Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> to list the replacement datasets for the
--   placeholders listed in the original. The schema in each dataset must
--   match its placeholder.
[$sel:sourceEntity:CreateDashboard'] :: CreateDashboard -> DashboardSourceEntity

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateDashboard</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

-- | Creates Amazon QuickSight customizations the current Amazon Web
--   Services Region. Currently, you can add a custom default theme by
--   using the <tt>CreateAccountCustomization</tt> or
--   <tt>UpdateAccountCustomization</tt> API operation. To further
--   customize Amazon QuickSight by removing Amazon QuickSight sample
--   assets and videos for all new users, see <a>Customizing Amazon
--   QuickSight</a> in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User Guide.</i>
--   
--   You can create customizations for your Amazon Web Services account or,
--   if you specify a namespace, for a Amazon QuickSight namespace instead.
--   Customizations that apply to a namespace always override
--   customizations that apply to an Amazon Web Services account. To find
--   out which customizations apply, use the
--   <tt>DescribeAccountCustomization</tt> API operation.
--   
--   Before you use the <tt>CreateAccountCustomization</tt> API operation
--   to add a theme as the namespace default, make sure that you first
--   share the theme with the namespace. If you don't share it with the
--   namespace, the theme isn't visible to your users even if you make it
--   the default theme. To check if the theme is shared, view the current
--   permissions by using the <tt> DescribeThemePermissions </tt> API
--   operation. To share the theme, grant permissions by using the <tt>
--   UpdateThemePermissions </tt> API operation.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.CreateAccountCustomization
