-- | Updates a dashboard in an Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   Updating a Dashboard creates a new dashboard version but does not
--   immediately publish the new version. You can update the published
--   version of a dashboard by using the UpdateDashboardPublishedVersion
--   API operation.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.UpdateDashboard

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateDashboard</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateDashboard
UpdateDashboard' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe DashboardPublishOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Parameters -> Text -> Text -> Text -> DashboardSourceEntity -> UpdateDashboard

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme that is being used for
--   this dashboard. If you add a value for this field, it overrides the
--   value that was originally associated with the entity. The theme ARN
--   must exist in the same Amazon Web Services account where you create
--   the dashboard.
[$sel:themeArn:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> Maybe Text

-- | Options for publishing the dashboard when you create it:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>AdHocFilteringOption</tt> -
--   This status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. When
--   this is set to <tt>DISABLED</tt>, Amazon QuickSight disables the left
--   filter pane on the published dashboard, which can be used for ad hoc
--   (one-time) filtering. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>ExportToCSVOption</tt> - This
--   status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. The visual
--   option to export data to .CSV format isn't enabled when this is set to
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>VisibilityState</tt> for <tt>SheetControlsOption</tt> - This
--   visibility state can be either <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> or
--   <tt>EXPANDED</tt>. This option is <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> by default.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:dashboardPublishOptions:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> Maybe DashboardPublishOptions

-- | A description for the first version of the dashboard being created.
[$sel:versionDescription:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> Maybe Text

-- | A structure that contains the parameters of the dashboard. These are
--   parameter overrides for a dashboard. A dashboard can have any type of
--   parameters, and some parameters might accept multiple values.
[$sel:parameters:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> Maybe Parameters

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that contains the dashboard
--   that you're updating.
[$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> Text

-- | The ID for the dashboard.
[$sel:dashboardId:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> Text

-- | The display name of the dashboard.
[$sel:name:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> Text

-- | The entity that you are using as a source when you update the
--   dashboard. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you specify the type of object
--   you're using as source. You can only update a dashboard from a
--   template, so you use a <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> entity. If you need to
--   update a dashboard from an analysis, first convert the analysis to a
--   template by using the CreateTemplate API operation. For
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the
--   source template. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can contain any
--   Amazon Web Services account and any Amazon QuickSight-supported Amazon
--   Web Services Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> to list the replacement datasets for the
--   placeholders listed in the original. The schema in each dataset must
--   match its placeholder.
[$sel:sourceEntity:UpdateDashboard'] :: UpdateDashboard -> DashboardSourceEntity

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateDashboard</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeArn:UpdateDashboard'</a>, <a>updateDashboard_themeArn</a>
--   - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme that is being used for
--   this dashboard. If you add a value for this field, it overrides the
--   value that was originally associated with the entity. The theme ARN
--   must exist in the same Amazon Web Services account where you create
--   the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dashboardPublishOptions:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_dashboardPublishOptions</a> - Options for
--   publishing the dashboard when you create it:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>AdHocFilteringOption</tt> -
--   This status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. When
--   this is set to <tt>DISABLED</tt>, Amazon QuickSight disables the left
--   filter pane on the published dashboard, which can be used for ad hoc
--   (one-time) filtering. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>ExportToCSVOption</tt> - This
--   status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. The visual
--   option to export data to .CSV format isn't enabled when this is set to
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>VisibilityState</tt> for <tt>SheetControlsOption</tt> - This
--   visibility state can be either <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> or
--   <tt>EXPANDED</tt>. This option is <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> by default.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionDescription:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_versionDescription</a> - A description for the
--   first version of the dashboard being created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:parameters:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_parameters</a> - A structure that contains the
--   parameters of the dashboard. These are parameter overrides for a
--   dashboard. A dashboard can have any type of parameters, and some
--   parameters might accept multiple values.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_awsAccountId</a> - The ID of the Amazon Web
--   Services account that contains the dashboard that you're updating.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dashboardId:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_dashboardId</a> - The ID for the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:UpdateDashboard'</a>, <a>updateDashboard_name</a> - The
--   display name of the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceEntity:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_sourceEntity</a> - The entity that you are using as
--   a source when you update the dashboard. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you
--   specify the type of object you're using as source. You can only update
--   a dashboard from a template, so you use a <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>
--   entity. If you need to update a dashboard from an analysis, first
--   convert the analysis to a template by using the CreateTemplate API
--   operation. For <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the source template. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can
--   contain any Amazon Web Services account and any Amazon
--   QuickSight-supported Amazon Web Services Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> to list the replacement datasets for the
--   placeholders listed in the original. The schema in each dataset must
--   match its placeholder.
newUpdateDashboard :: Text -> Text -> Text -> DashboardSourceEntity -> UpdateDashboard

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme that is being used for
--   this dashboard. If you add a value for this field, it overrides the
--   value that was originally associated with the entity. The theme ARN
--   must exist in the same Amazon Web Services account where you create
--   the dashboard.
updateDashboard_themeArn :: Lens' UpdateDashboard (Maybe Text)

-- | Options for publishing the dashboard when you create it:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>AdHocFilteringOption</tt> -
--   This status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. When
--   this is set to <tt>DISABLED</tt>, Amazon QuickSight disables the left
--   filter pane on the published dashboard, which can be used for ad hoc
--   (one-time) filtering. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>ExportToCSVOption</tt> - This
--   status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. The visual
--   option to export data to .CSV format isn't enabled when this is set to
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>VisibilityState</tt> for <tt>SheetControlsOption</tt> - This
--   visibility state can be either <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> or
--   <tt>EXPANDED</tt>. This option is <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> by default.</li>
--   </ul>
updateDashboard_dashboardPublishOptions :: Lens' UpdateDashboard (Maybe DashboardPublishOptions)

-- | A description for the first version of the dashboard being created.
updateDashboard_versionDescription :: Lens' UpdateDashboard (Maybe Text)

-- | A structure that contains the parameters of the dashboard. These are
--   parameter overrides for a dashboard. A dashboard can have any type of
--   parameters, and some parameters might accept multiple values.
updateDashboard_parameters :: Lens' UpdateDashboard (Maybe Parameters)

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that contains the dashboard
--   that you're updating.
updateDashboard_awsAccountId :: Lens' UpdateDashboard Text

-- | The ID for the dashboard.
updateDashboard_dashboardId :: Lens' UpdateDashboard Text

-- | The display name of the dashboard.
updateDashboard_name :: Lens' UpdateDashboard Text

-- | The entity that you are using as a source when you update the
--   dashboard. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you specify the type of object
--   you're using as source. You can only update a dashboard from a
--   template, so you use a <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> entity. If you need to
--   update a dashboard from an analysis, first convert the analysis to a
--   template by using the CreateTemplate API operation. For
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the
--   source template. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can contain any
--   Amazon Web Services account and any Amazon QuickSight-supported Amazon
--   Web Services Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> to list the replacement datasets for the
--   placeholders listed in the original. The schema in each dataset must
--   match its placeholder.
updateDashboard_sourceEntity :: Lens' UpdateDashboard DashboardSourceEntity

-- | Updates a dataset.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.UpdateDataSet

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateDataSet</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateDataSet
UpdateDataSet' :: Maybe (HashMap Text FieldFolder) -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnGroup) -> Maybe DataSetUsageConfiguration -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule) -> Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable) -> Text -> Text -> Text -> HashMap Text PhysicalTable -> DataSetImportMode -> UpdateDataSet

-- | The folder that contains fields and nested subfolders for your
--   dataset.
[$sel:fieldFolders:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text FieldFolder)

-- | Groupings of columns that work together in certain Amazon QuickSight
--   features. Currently, only geospatial hierarchy is supported.
[$sel:columnGroups:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnGroup)
[$sel:dataSetUsageConfiguration:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Maybe DataSetUsageConfiguration

-- | The configuration of tags on a dataset to set row-level security.
--   Row-level security tags are currently supported for anonymous
--   embedding only.
[$sel:rowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionTagConfiguration

-- | The row-level security configuration for the data you want to create.
[$sel:rowLevelPermissionDataSet:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | A set of one or more definitions of a <tt> ColumnLevelPermissionRule
--   </tt>.
[$sel:columnLevelPermissionRules:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Maybe (NonEmpty ColumnLevelPermissionRule)

-- | Configures the combination and transformation of the data from the
--   physical tables.
[$sel:logicalTableMap:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Maybe (HashMap Text LogicalTable)

-- | The Amazon Web Services account ID.
[$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Text

-- | The ID for the dataset that you want to update. This ID is unique per
--   Amazon Web Services Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
[$sel:dataSetId:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Text

-- | The display name for the dataset.
[$sel:name:UpdateDataSet'] :: UpdateDataSet -> Text

--   source.

-- | Updates an existing IAMpolicy assignment. This operation updates only
--   the optional parameter or parameters that are specified in the
--   request. This overwrites all of the users included in
--   <tt>Identities</tt>.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateIAMPolicyAssignment</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment
UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment' :: Maybe AssignmentStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (HashMap Text [Text]) -> Text -> Text -> Text -> UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment

-- | The status of the assignment. Possible values are as follows:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ENABLED</tt> - Anything specified in this assignment is used
--   when creating the data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DISABLED</tt> - This assignment isn't used when creating the
--   data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DRAFT</tt> - This assignment is an unfinished draft and isn't
--   used when creating the data source.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:assignmentStatus:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'] :: UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment -> Maybe AssignmentStatus

-- | The ARN for the IAMpolicy to apply to the Amazon QuickSight users and
--   groups specified in this assignment.
[$sel:policyArn:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'] :: UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight users, groups, or both that you want to assign
--   the policy to.
[$sel:identities:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'] :: UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment -> Maybe (HashMap Text [Text])

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that contains the IAMpolicy
--   assignment.
[$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'] :: UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment -> Text

-- | The name of the assignment, also called a rule. This name must be
--   unique within an Amazon Web Services account.
[$sel:assignmentName:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'] :: UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment -> Text

-- | The namespace of the assignment.
[$sel:namespace:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'] :: UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:assignmentStatus:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'</a>,
--   <a>updateIAMPolicyAssignment_assignmentStatus</a> - The status of the
--   assignment. Possible values are as follows:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ENABLED</tt> - Anything specified in this assignment is used
--   when creating the data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DISABLED</tt> - This assignment isn't used when creating the
--   data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DRAFT</tt> - This assignment is an unfinished draft and isn't
--   used when creating the data source.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:policyArn:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'</a>,
--   <a>updateIAMPolicyAssignment_policyArn</a> - The ARN for the IAMpolicy
--   to apply to the Amazon QuickSight users and groups specified in this
--   assignment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:identities:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'</a>,
--   <a>updateIAMPolicyAssignment_identities</a> - The Amazon QuickSight
--   users, groups, or both that you want to assign the policy to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'</a>,
--   <a>updateIAMPolicyAssignment_awsAccountId</a> - The ID of the Amazon
--   Web Services account that contains the IAMpolicy assignment.
--   
--   <a>$sel:assignmentName:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'</a>,
--   <a>updateIAMPolicyAssignment_assignmentName</a> - The name of the
--   assignment, also called a rule. This name must be unique within an
--   Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment'</a>,
--   <a>updateIAMPolicyAssignment_namespace</a> - The namespace of the
--   assignment.
newUpdateIAMPolicyAssignment :: Text -> Text -> Text -> UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment

-- | The status of the assignment. Possible values are as follows:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>ENABLED</tt> - Anything specified in this assignment is used
--   when creating the data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DISABLED</tt> - This assignment isn't used when creating the
--   data source.</li>
--   <li><tt>DRAFT</tt> - This assignment is an unfinished draft and isn't
--   used when creating the data source.</li>
--   </ul>
updateIAMPolicyAssignment_assignmentStatus :: Lens' UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment (Maybe AssignmentStatus)

-- | The ARN for the IAMpolicy to apply to the Amazon QuickSight users and
--   groups specified in this assignment.
updateIAMPolicyAssignment_policyArn :: Lens' UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon QuickSight users, groups, or both that you want to assign
--   the policy to.
updateIAMPolicyAssignment_identities :: Lens' UpdateIAMPolicyAssignment (Maybe (HashMap Text [Text]))

-- | Updates a template from an existing Amazon QuickSight analysis or
--   another template.

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateTemplate</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateTemplate
UpdateTemplate' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Text -> Text -> TemplateSourceEntity -> UpdateTemplate

-- | A description of the current template version that is being updated.
--   Every time you call <tt>UpdateTemplate</tt>, you create a new version
--   of the template. Each version of the template maintains a description
--   of the version in the <tt>VersionDescription</tt> field.
[$sel:versionDescription:UpdateTemplate'] :: UpdateTemplate -> Maybe Text

--   that you're updating.

-- | The entity that you are using as a source when you update the
--   template. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you specify the type of object
--   you're using as source: <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> for a template or
--   <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> for an analysis. Both of these require an
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN). For <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the
--   ARN of the source template. For <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt>, specify the
--   ARN of the source analysis. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can
--   contain any Amazon Web Services account and any Amazon
--   QuickSight-supported Amazon Web Services Region;.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> or <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> to list the
--   replacement datasets for the placeholders listed in the original. The
--   schema in each dataset must match its placeholder.

-- | Updates the resource permissions for a theme. Permissions apply to the
--   action to grant or revoke permissions on, for example
--   <tt>"quicksight:DescribeTheme"</tt>.
--   
--   Theme permissions apply in groupings. Valid groupings include the
--   following for the three levels of permissions, which are user, owner,
--   or no permissions:
--   
--   <ul>
--   
--   <li>User<ul><li><pre>"quicksight:DescribeTheme"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:DescribeThemeAlias"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:ListThemeAliases"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:ListThemeVersions"</pre></li></ul></li>
--   
--   <li>Owner<ul><li><pre>"quicksight:DescribeTheme"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:DescribeThemeAlias"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:ListThemeAliases"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:ListThemeVersions"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:DeleteTheme"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:UpdateTheme"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:CreateThemeAlias"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:DeleteThemeAlias"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:UpdateThemeAlias"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:UpdateThemePermissions"</pre></li><li><pre>"quicksight:DescribeThemePermissions"</pre></li></ul></li>
--   <li>To specify no permissions, omit the permissions list.</li>
--   </ul>
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.UpdateThemePermissions

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateThemePermissions</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateThemePermissions
UpdateThemePermissions' :: Maybe [ResourcePermission] -> Maybe [ResourcePermission] -> Text -> Text -> UpdateThemePermissions

-- | A list of resource permissions to be revoked from the theme.
[$sel:revokePermissions:UpdateThemePermissions'] :: UpdateThemePermissions -> Maybe [ResourcePermission]

-- | A list of resource permissions to be granted for the theme.
[$sel:grantPermissions:UpdateThemePermissions'] :: UpdateThemePermissions -> Maybe [ResourcePermission]

-- | The ID of the Amazon Web Services account that contains the theme.
[$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateThemePermissions'] :: UpdateThemePermissions -> Text

-- | The ID for the theme.
[$sel:themeId:UpdateThemePermissions'] :: UpdateThemePermissions -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateThemePermissions</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.

--   permissions to be revoked from the theme.

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateThemePermissionsResponse</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.

--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding

--   of resource permissions for the theme.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:UpdateThemePermissionsResponse'</a>,
--   <a>updateThemePermissionsResponse_status</a> - The HTTP status of the
--   request.
newUpdateThemePermissionsResponse :: Int -> UpdateThemePermissionsResponse

-- | The Amazon Web Services request ID for this operation.
updateThemePermissionsResponse_requestId :: Lens' UpdateThemePermissionsResponse (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme.
updateThemePermissionsResponse_themeArn :: Lens' UpdateThemePermissionsResponse (Maybe Text)

-- | The ID for the theme.
updateThemePermissionsResponse_themeId :: Lens' UpdateThemePermissionsResponse (Maybe Text)

-- | The resulting list of resource permissions for the theme.
updateThemePermissionsResponse_permissions :: Lens' UpdateThemePermissionsResponse (Maybe (NonEmpty ResourcePermission))

-- | The HTTP status of the request.
updateThemePermissionsResponse_status :: Lens' UpdateThemePermissionsResponse Int

-- | Updates an Amazon QuickSight user.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight.UpdateUser

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateUser</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateUser
UpdateUser' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Text -> Text -> Text -> Text -> UserRole -> UpdateUser

-- | A flag that you use to indicate that you want to remove all custom
--   permissions from this user. Using this parameter resets the user to
--   the state it was in before a custom permissions profile was applied.
--   This parameter defaults to NULL and it doesn't accept any other value.
[$sel:unapplyCustomPermissions:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Maybe Bool

-- | (Enterprise edition only) The name of the custom permissions profile
--   that you want to assign to this user. Customized permissions allows
--   you to control a user's access by restricting access the following
--   operations:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Create and update data sources</li>
--   <li>Create and update datasets</li>
--   <li>Create and update email reports</li>
--   <li>Subscribe to email reports</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   A set of custom permissions includes any combination of these
--   restrictions. Currently, you need to create the profile names for
--   custom permission sets by using the Amazon QuickSight console. Then,
--   you use the <tt>RegisterUser</tt> API operation to assign the named
--   set of permissions to a Amazon QuickSight user.
--   
--   Amazon QuickSight custom permissions are applied through IAMpolicies.
--   Therefore, they override the permissions typically granted by
--   assigning Amazon QuickSight users to one of the default security
--   cohorts in Amazon QuickSight (admin, author, reader).
--   
--   This feature is available only to Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition
--   subscriptions.
[$sel:customPermissionsName:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The URL of the custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider that provides
--   identity to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an
--   associated Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. This parameter
--   should only be used when <tt>ExternalLoginFederationProviderType</tt>
--   parameter is set to <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>.
[$sel:customFederationProviderUrl:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. The type of supported
--   external login provider can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com. When choosing the <tt>COGNITO</tt>
--   provider type, dont use the "CustomFederationProviderUrl" parameter
--   which is only needed when the external provider is custom.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider. When
--   choosing <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt> type, use the
--   <tt>CustomFederationProviderUrl</tt> parameter to provide the custom
--   OIDC provider URL.</li>
--   <li><tt>NONE</tt>: This clears all the previously saved external login
--   information for a user. Use <tt> DescribeUser </tt> API to check the
--   external login information.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The identity ID for a user in the external login provider.
[$sel:externalLoginId:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Maybe Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user name that you want to update.
[$sel:userName:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Text

-- | The ID for the Amazon Web Services account that the user is in.
--   Currently, you use the ID for the Amazon Web Services account that
--   contains your Amazon QuickSight account.
[$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Text

-- | The namespace. Currently, you should set this to <tt>default</tt>.
[$sel:namespace:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Text

-- | The email address of the user that you want to update.
[$sel:email:UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight role of the user. The role can be one of the
--   following default security cohorts:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   The name of the Amazon QuickSight role is invisible to the user except
--   for the console screens dealing with permissions.
[$sel:role':UpdateUser'] :: UpdateUser -> UserRole

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateUser</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.

--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding

--   <a>$sel:customPermissionsName:UpdateUser'</a>,

--   template. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you specify the type of object
--   you're using as source: <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> for a template or
--   <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> for an analysis. Both of these require an
--   Amazon Resource Name (ARN). For <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the
--   ARN of the source template. For <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt>, specify the
--   ARN of the source analysis. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can
--   contain any Amazon Web Services account and any Amazon
--   QuickSight-supported Amazon Web Services Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> or <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> to list the
--   replacement datasets for the placeholders listed in the original. The
--   schema in each dataset must match its placeholder.

-- | Options for publishing the dashboard when you create it:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>AdHocFilteringOption</tt> -
--   This status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. When
--   this is set to <tt>DISABLED</tt>, Amazon QuickSight disables the left
--   filter pane on the published dashboard, which can be used for ad hoc
--   (one-time) filtering. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>ExportToCSVOption</tt> - This
--   status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. The visual
--   option to export data to .CSV format isn't enabled when this is set to
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>VisibilityState</tt> for <tt>SheetControlsOption</tt> - This
--   visibility state can be either <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> or
--   <tt>EXPANDED</tt>. This option is <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> by default.</li>

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user name that you want to create for the user
--   you are registering.
registerUser_userName :: Lens' RegisterUser (Maybe Text)

-- | (Enterprise edition only) The name of the custom permissions profile
--   that you want to assign to this user. Customized permissions allows
--   you to control a user's access by restricting access the following
--   operations:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Create and update data sources</li>
--   <li>Create and update datasets</li>
--   <li>Create and update email reports</li>
--   <li>Subscribe to email reports</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   To add custom permissions to an existing user, use <tt> UpdateUser
--   </tt> instead.
--   
--   A set of custom permissions includes any combination of these
--   restrictions. Currently, you need to create the profile names for
--   custom permission sets by using the Amazon QuickSight console. Then,
--   you use the <tt>RegisterUser</tt> API operation to assign the named
--   set of permissions to a Amazon QuickSight user.
--   
--   Amazon QuickSight custom permissions are applied through IAMpolicies.
--   Therefore, they override the permissions typically granted by
--   assigning Amazon QuickSight users to one of the default security
--   cohorts in Amazon QuickSight (admin, author, reader).
--   
--   This feature is available only to Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition
--   subscriptions.
registerUser_customPermissionsName :: Lens' RegisterUser (Maybe Text)

-- | The URL of the custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider that provides
--   identity to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an
--   associated Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. This parameter
--   should only be used when <tt>ExternalLoginFederationProviderType</tt>
--   parameter is set to <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>.
registerUser_customFederationProviderUrl :: Lens' RegisterUser (Maybe Text)

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. The type of supported
--   external login provider can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com. When choosing the <tt>COGNITO</tt>
--   provider type, dont use the "CustomFederationProviderUrl" parameter
--   which is only needed when the external provider is custom.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider. When
--   choosing <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt> type, use the
--   <tt>CustomFederationProviderUrl</tt> parameter to provide the custom
--   OIDC provider URL.</li>
--   </ul>

--   QuickSight.

-- | Adds persistence of state for the user session in an embedded
--   dashboard. Persistence applies to the sheet and the parameter
--   settings. These are control settings that the dashboard subscriber
--   (Amazon QuickSight reader) chooses while viewing the dashboard. If
--   this is set to <tt>TRUE</tt>, the settings are the same when the
--   subscriber reopens the same dashboard URL. The state is stored in

-- | A flag that you use to indicate that you want to remove all custom
--   permissions from this user. Using this parameter resets the user to
--   the state it was in before a custom permissions profile was applied.
--   This parameter defaults to NULL and it doesn't accept any other value.
updateUser_unapplyCustomPermissions :: Lens' UpdateUser (Maybe Bool)

-- | (Enterprise edition only) The name of the custom permissions profile
--   that you want to assign to this user. Customized permissions allows
--   you to control a user's access by restricting access the following
--   operations:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Create and update data sources</li>
--   <li>Create and update datasets</li>
--   <li>Create and update email reports</li>
--   <li>Subscribe to email reports</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   A set of custom permissions includes any combination of these
--   restrictions. Currently, you need to create the profile names for
--   custom permission sets by using the Amazon QuickSight console. Then,
--   you use the <tt>RegisterUser</tt> API operation to assign the named
--   set of permissions to a Amazon QuickSight user.
--   
--   Amazon QuickSight custom permissions are applied through IAMpolicies.
--   Therefore, they override the permissions typically granted by
--   assigning Amazon QuickSight users to one of the default security
--   cohorts in Amazon QuickSight (admin, author, reader).
--   
--   This feature is available only to Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition
--   subscriptions.
updateUser_customPermissionsName :: Lens' UpdateUser (Maybe Text)

-- | The URL of the custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider that provides
--   identity to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an
--   associated Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. This parameter
--   should only be used when <tt>ExternalLoginFederationProviderType</tt>
--   parameter is set to <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>.
updateUser_customFederationProviderUrl :: Lens' UpdateUser (Maybe Text)

-- | The type of supported external login provider that provides identity
--   to let a user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated
--   Identity and Access Management(IAM) role. The type of supported
--   external login provider can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com. When choosing the <tt>COGNITO</tt>
--   provider type, dont use the "CustomFederationProviderUrl" parameter
--   which is only needed when the external provider is custom.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider. When
--   choosing <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt> type, use the
--   <tt>CustomFederationProviderUrl</tt> parameter to provide the custom
--   OIDC provider URL.</li>
--   <li><tt>NONE</tt>: This clears all the previously saved external login
--   information for a user. Use <tt> DescribeUser </tt> API to check the
--   external login information.</li>
--   </ul>
updateUser_externalLoginFederationProviderType :: Lens' UpdateUser (Maybe Text)

-- | The identity ID for a user in the external login provider.
updateUser_externalLoginId :: Lens' UpdateUser (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon QuickSight user name that you want to update.

--   contains your Amazon QuickSight account.
updateUser_awsAccountId :: Lens' UpdateUser Text

-- | The namespace. Currently, you should set this to <tt>default</tt>.
updateUser_namespace :: Lens' UpdateUser Text

-- | The email address of the user that you want to update.
updateUser_email :: Lens' UpdateUser Text

-- | The Amazon QuickSight role of the user. The role can be one of the
--   following default security cohorts:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   The name of the Amazon QuickSight role is invisible to the user except
--   for the console screens dealing with permissions.
updateUser_role :: Lens' UpdateUser UserRole

--   to restrict access to certain features. For more information, see
--   <a>Customizing Access to the Amazon QuickSight Console</a> in the

--   
--   Use <tt>GenerateEmbedUrlForRegisteredUser</tt> where you want to
--   provide an authoring portal that allows users to create data sources,
--   datasets, analyses, and dashboards. The users who accesses an embedded
--   Amazon QuickSight console needs to belong to the author or admin
--   security cohort. If you want to restrict permissions to some of these
--   features, add a custom permissions profile to the user with the <tt>
--   UpdateUser </tt> API operation. Use <tt> RegisterUser </tt> API
--   operation to add a new user with a custom permission profile attached.

--   QuickSight User Guide</i>:

--   the following:.
--

--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>

--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>

--   </ul>

--   data and insights to every user in your organization. This API
--   reference contains documentation for a programming interface that you
--   can use to manage Amazon QuickSight.
module Network.AWS.QuickSight

-- | API version <tt>2018-04-01</tt> of the Amazon QuickSight SDK
--   configuration.
defaultService :: Service

-- | You don't have access to this item. The provided credentials couldn't
--   be validated. You might not be authorized to carry out the request.
--   Make sure that your account is authorized to use the Amazon QuickSight
--   service, that your policies have the correct permissions, and that you
--   are using the correct access keys.
_AccessDeniedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | This resource is currently unavailable.
_ResourceUnavailableException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The identity type specified isn't supported. Supported identity types
--   include <tt>IAM</tt> and <tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt>.
_IdentityTypeNotSupportedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The domain specified isn't on the allow list. All domains for embedded
--   dashboards must be added to the approved list by an Amazon QuickSight
--   admin.
_DomainNotWhitelistedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Updating or deleting a resource can cause an inconsistent state.
_ConflictException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | This error indicates that you are calling an embedding operation in
--   Amazon QuickSight without the required pricing plan on your Amazon Web
--   Services account. Before you can use embedding for anonymous users, a
--   Amazon QuickSight administrator needs to add capacity pricing to
--   Amazon QuickSight. You can do this on the <b>Manage Amazon
--   QuickSight</b> page.
--   
--   After capacity pricing is added, you can use the GetDashboardEmbedUrl
--   API operation with the <tt>--identity-type ANONYMOUS</tt> option.
_UnsupportedPricingPlanException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more parameters has a value that isn't valid.
_InvalidParameterValueException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | This error indicates that you are calling an operation on an Amazon
--   QuickSight subscription where the edition doesn't include support for
--   that operation. Amazon Amazon QuickSight currently has Standard
--   Edition and Enterprise Edition. Not every operation and capability is
--   available in every edition.
_UnsupportedUserEditionException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Access is throttled.
_ThrottlingException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more preconditions aren't met.
_PreconditionNotMetException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The <tt>NextToken</tt> value isn't valid.
_InvalidNextTokenException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The resource specified already exists.
_ResourceExistsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An internal failure occurred.
_InternalFailureException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A resource is already in a state that indicates an operation is
--   happening that must complete before a new update can be applied.
_ConcurrentUpdatingException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | One or more resources can't be found.
_ResourceNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The user with the provided name isn't found. This error can happen in
--   any operation that requires finding a user based on a provided user
--   name, such as <tt>DeleteUser</tt>, <tt>DescribeUser</tt>, and so on.
_QuickSightUserNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | A limit is exceeded.
_LimitExceededException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The number of minutes specified for the lifetime of a session isn't
--   valid. The session lifetime must be 15-600 minutes.
_SessionLifetimeInMinutesInvalidException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | Create a value of <a>CreateTemplate</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionDescription:CreateTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createTemplate_versionDescription</a> - A description of the
--   current template version being created. This API operation creates the
--   first version of the template. Every time <tt>UpdateTemplate</tt> is
--   called, a new version is created. Each version of the template
--   maintains a description of the version in the
--   <tt>VersionDescription</tt> field.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:CreateTemplate'</a>, <a>createTemplate_name</a> - A
--   display name for the template.
--

--   be set on the template.

--   Contains a map of the key-value pairs for the resource tag or tags
--   assigned to the resource.

--   <a>createTemplate_awsAccountId</a> - The ID for the Amazon Web
--   Services account that the group is in. You use the ID for the Amazon
--   Web Services account that contains your Amazon QuickSight account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateId:CreateTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createTemplate_templateId</a> - An ID for the template that you
--   want to create. This template is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region; in each Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceEntity:CreateTemplate'</a>,
--   <a>createTemplate_sourceEntity</a> - The entity that you are using as
--   a source when you create the template. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you
--   specify the type of object you're using as source:
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> for a template or <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> for
--   an analysis. Both of these require an Amazon Resource Name (ARN). For
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the ARN of the source template. For
--   <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt>, specify the ARN of the source analysis. The
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can contain any Amazon Web Services
--   account and any Amazon QuickSight-supported Amazon Web Services
--   Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> or <tt>SourceAnalysis</tt> to list the
--   replacement datasets for the placeholders listed in the original. The
--   schema in each dataset must match its placeholder.
newCreateTemplate :: Text -> Text -> TemplateSourceEntity -> CreateTemplate

-- | Create a value of <a>RegisterUser</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional

--   Amazon QuickSight user name that you want to create for the user you
--   are registering.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customPermissionsName:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_customPermissionsName</a> - (Enterprise edition only)
--   The name of the custom permissions profile that you want to assign to
--   this user. Customized permissions allows you to control a user's
--   access by restricting access the following operations:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Create and update data sources</li>
--   <li>Create and update datasets</li>
--   <li>Create and update email reports</li>
--   <li>Subscribe to email reports</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   To add custom permissions to an existing user, use <tt> UpdateUser
--   </tt> instead.
--   
--   A set of custom permissions includes any combination of these
--   restrictions. Currently, you need to create the profile names for
--   custom permission sets by using the Amazon QuickSight console. Then,
--   you use the <tt>RegisterUser</tt> API operation to assign the named
--   set of permissions to a Amazon QuickSight user.
--   
--   Amazon QuickSight custom permissions are applied through IAMpolicies.
--   Therefore, they override the permissions typically granted by
--   assigning Amazon QuickSight users to one of the default security
--   cohorts in Amazon QuickSight (admin, author, reader).
--   
--   This feature is available only to Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition
--   subscriptions.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customFederationProviderUrl:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_customFederationProviderUrl</a> - The URL of the
--   custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider that provides identity to let a
--   user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated Identity and
--   Access Management(IAM) role. This parameter should only be used when
--   <tt>ExternalLoginFederationProviderType</tt> parameter is set to
--   <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_externalLoginFederationProviderType</a> - The type of
--   supported external login provider that provides identity to let a user
--   federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated Identity and Access
--   Management(IAM) role. The type of supported external login provider
--   can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com. When choosing the <tt>COGNITO</tt>
--   provider type, dont use the "CustomFederationProviderUrl" parameter
--   which is only needed when the external provider is custom.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider. When
--   choosing <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt> type, use the
--   <tt>CustomFederationProviderUrl</tt> parameter to provide the custom
--   OIDC provider URL.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:iamArn:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_iamArn</a> - The ARN
--   of the IAMuser or role that you are registering with Amazon
--   QuickSight.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginId:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_externalLoginId</a> - The identity ID for a user in
--   the external login provider.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sessionName:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_sessionName</a>
--   - You need to use this parameter only when you register one or more
--   users using an assumed IAMrole. You don't need to provide the session
--   name for other scenarios, for example when you are registering an
--   IAMuser or an Amazon QuickSight user. You can register multiple users
--   using the same IAMrole if each user has a different session name. For
--   more information on assuming IAMroles, see <a>assume-role</a> in the
--   <i>AWS CLI Reference.</i>
--   
--   <a>$sel:identityType:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_identityType</a> - Amazon QuickSight supports several
--   ways of managing the identity of users. This parameter accepts two
--   values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>IAM</tt>: A user whose identity maps to an existing IAMuser or
--   role.</li>
--   <li><tt>QUICKSIGHT</tt>: A user whose identity is owned and managed
--   internally by Amazon QuickSight.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:email:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_email</a> - The email
--   address of the user that you want to register.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userRole:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_userRole</a> - The
--   Amazon QuickSight role for the user. The user role can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:RegisterUser'</a>,
--   <a>registerUser_awsAccountId</a> - The ID for the Amazon Web Services

--   Web Services account that contains your Amazon QuickSight account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:RegisterUser'</a>, <a>registerUser_namespace</a> -

--   
--   <a>$sel:themeArn:UpdateDashboard'</a>, <a>updateDashboard_themeArn</a>
--   - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the theme that is being used for
--   this dashboard. If you add a value for this field, it overrides the
--   value that was originally associated with the entity. The theme ARN
--   must exist in the same Amazon Web Services account where you create
--   the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dashboardPublishOptions:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_dashboardPublishOptions</a> - Options for
--   publishing the dashboard when you create it:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>AdHocFilteringOption</tt> -
--   This status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. When
--   this is set to <tt>DISABLED</tt>, Amazon QuickSight disables the left
--   filter pane on the published dashboard, which can be used for ad hoc
--   (one-time) filtering. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>AvailabilityStatus</tt> for <tt>ExportToCSVOption</tt> - This
--   status can be either <tt>ENABLED</tt> or <tt>DISABLED</tt>. The visual
--   option to export data to .CSV format isn't enabled when this is set to
--   <tt>DISABLED</tt>. This option is <tt>ENABLED</tt> by default.</li>
--   <li><tt>VisibilityState</tt> for <tt>SheetControlsOption</tt> - This
--   visibility state can be either <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> or
--   <tt>EXPANDED</tt>. This option is <tt>COLLAPSED</tt> by default.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:versionDescription:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_versionDescription</a> - A description for the
--   first version of the dashboard being created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:parameters:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_parameters</a> - A structure that contains the
--   parameters of the dashboard. These are parameter overrides for a
--   dashboard. A dashboard can have any type of parameters, and some
--   parameters might accept multiple values.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_awsAccountId</a> - The ID of the Amazon Web
--   Services account that contains the dashboard that you're updating.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dashboardId:UpdateDashboard'</a>,

--   
--   <a>$sel:name:UpdateDashboard'</a>, <a>updateDashboard_name</a> - The
--   display name of the dashboard.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceEntity:UpdateDashboard'</a>,
--   <a>updateDashboard_sourceEntity</a> - The entity that you are using as
--   a source when you update the dashboard. In <tt>SourceEntity</tt>, you
--   specify the type of object you're using as source. You can only update
--   a dashboard from a template, so you use a <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>
--   entity. If you need to update a dashboard from an analysis, first
--   convert the analysis to a template by using the CreateTemplate API
--   operation. For <tt>SourceTemplate</tt>, specify the Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the source template. The <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> ARN can
--   contain any Amazon Web Services account and any Amazon
--   QuickSight-supported Amazon Web Services Region.
--   
--   Use the <tt>DataSetReferences</tt> entity within
--   <tt>SourceTemplate</tt> to list the replacement datasets for the
--   placeholders listed in the original. The schema in each dataset must
--   match its placeholder.

--   indicate that you want to remove all custom permissions from this
--   user. Using this parameter resets the user to the state it was in
--   before a custom permissions profile was applied. This parameter
--   defaults to NULL and it doesn't accept any other value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customPermissionsName:UpdateUser'</a>,
--   <a>updateUser_customPermissionsName</a> - (Enterprise edition only)
--   The name of the custom permissions profile that you want to assign to
--   this user. Customized permissions allows you to control a user's
--   access by restricting access the following operations:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Create and update data sources</li>
--   <li>Create and update datasets</li>
--   <li>Create and update email reports</li>
--   <li>Subscribe to email reports</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   A set of custom permissions includes any combination of these
--   restrictions. Currently, you need to create the profile names for
--   custom permission sets by using the Amazon QuickSight console. Then,
--   you use the <tt>RegisterUser</tt> API operation to assign the named
--   set of permissions to a Amazon QuickSight user.
--   
--   Amazon QuickSight custom permissions are applied through IAMpolicies.
--   Therefore, they override the permissions typically granted by
--   assigning Amazon QuickSight users to one of the default security
--   cohorts in Amazon QuickSight (admin, author, reader).
--   
--   This feature is available only to Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition
--   subscriptions.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customFederationProviderUrl:UpdateUser'</a>,
--   <a>updateUser_customFederationProviderUrl</a> - The URL of the custom
--   OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider that provides identity to let a user
--   federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated Identity and Access
--   Management(IAM) role. This parameter should only be used when
--   <tt>ExternalLoginFederationProviderType</tt> parameter is set to
--   <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:UpdateUser'</a>,
--   <a>updateUser_externalLoginFederationProviderType</a> - The type of
--   supported external login provider that provides identity to let a user
--   federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated Identity and Access
--   Management(IAM) role. The type of supported external login provider
--   can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com. When choosing the <tt>COGNITO</tt>
--   provider type, dont use the "CustomFederationProviderUrl" parameter
--   which is only needed when the external provider is custom.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider. When
--   choosing <tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt> type, use the
--   <tt>CustomFederationProviderUrl</tt> parameter to provide the custom
--   OIDC provider URL.</li>
--   <li><tt>NONE</tt>: This clears all the previously saved external login
--   information for a user. Use <tt> DescribeUser </tt> API to check the
--   external login information.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginId:UpdateUser'</a>,
--   <a>updateUser_externalLoginId</a> - The identity ID for a user in the
--   external login provider.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userName:UpdateUser'</a>, <a>updateUser_userName</a> - The
--   Amazon QuickSight user name that you want to update.
--   
--   <a>$sel:awsAccountId:UpdateUser'</a>, <a>updateUser_awsAccountId</a> -
--   The ID for the Amazon Web Services account that the user is in.
--   Currently, you use the ID for the Amazon Web Services account that
--   contains your Amazon QuickSight account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:UpdateUser'</a>, <a>updateUser_namespace</a> - The
--   namespace. Currently, you should set this to <tt>default</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:email:UpdateUser'</a>, <a>updateUser_email</a> - The email
--   address of the user that you want to update.
--   
--   <a>$sel:role':UpdateUser'</a>, <a>updateUser_role</a> - The Amazon
--   QuickSight role of the user. The role can be one of the following
--   default security cohorts:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   The name of the Amazon QuickSight role is invisible to the user except
--   for the console screens dealing with permissions.

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAnalysis</a> smart constructor.
data Analysis

-- | Create a value of <a>Analysis</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_status</a> - Status
--   associated with the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:themeArn:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_themeArn</a> - The ARN of
--   the theme of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSetArns:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_dataSetArns</a> - The
--   ARNs of the datasets of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sheets:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_sheets</a> - A list of the
--   associated sheets with the unique identifier and name of each sheet.
--   
--   <a>$sel:analysisId:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_analysisId</a> - The ID
--   of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_lastUpdatedTime</a>
--   - The time that the analysis was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_createdTime</a> - The
--   time that the analysis was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_name</a> - The descriptive
--   name of the analysis.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errors:Analysis'</a>, <a>analysis_errors</a> - Errors
--   associated with the analysis.
newAnalysis :: Analysis

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newCredentialPair</a> smart constructor.
data CredentialPair

-- | Create a value of <a>CredentialPair</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:CredentialPair'</a>,
--   <a>credentialPair_alternateDataSourceParameters</a> - A set of
--   alternate data source parameters that you want to share for these
--   credentials. The credentials are applied in tandem with the data
--   source parameters when you copy a data source by using a create or
--   update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the new data source with the existing credentials. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> originally used with these
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> is automatically allowed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:username:CredentialPair'</a>, <a>credentialPair_username</a> -
--   User name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:password:CredentialPair'</a>, <a>credentialPair_password</a> -
--   Password.
newCredentialPair :: Text -> Text -> CredentialPair

-- | The structure of a data source.

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDataSource</a> smart constructor.
data DataSource
DataSource' :: Maybe ResourceStatus -> Maybe DataSourceParameters -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe SslProperties -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (NonEmpty DataSourceParameters) -> Maybe VpcConnectionProperties -> Maybe DataSourceType -> Maybe DataSourceErrorInfo -> DataSource

-- | Create a value of <a>DataSource</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_status</a> - The HTTP
--   status of the request.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceParameters:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_dataSourceParameters</a> - The parameters that Amazon
--   QuickSight uses to connect to your underlying source. This is a
--   variant type structure. For this structure to be valid, only one of
--   the attributes can be non-null.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedTime:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_lastUpdatedTime</a> - The last time that this data
--   source was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_arn</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) of the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_createdTime</a> -
--   The time that this data source was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sslProperties:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_sslProperties</a>
--   - Secure Socket Layer (SSL) properties that apply when Amazon
--   QuickSight connects to your underlying source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataSourceId:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_dataSourceId</a> -
--   The ID of the data source. This ID is unique per Amazon Web Services
--   Region for each Amazon Web Services account.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_name</a> - A display name
--   for the data source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:alternateDataSourceParameters:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_alternateDataSourceParameters</a> - A set of alternate
--   data source parameters that you want to share for the credentials
--   stored with this data source. The credentials are applied in tandem
--   with the data source parameters when you copy a data source by using a
--   create or update request. The API operation compares the
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> structure that's in the request with the
--   structures in the <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> allow list.
--   If the structures are an exact match, the request is allowed to use
--   the credentials from this existing data source. If the
--   <tt>AlternateDataSourceParameters</tt> list is null, the
--   <tt>Credentials</tt> originally used with this
--   <tt>DataSourceParameters</tt> are automatically allowed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vpcConnectionProperties:DataSource'</a>,
--   <a>dataSource_vpcConnectionProperties</a> - The VPC connection
--   information. You need to use this parameter only when you want Amazon
--   QuickSight to use a VPC connection when connecting to your underlying
--   source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:type':DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_type</a> - The type of
--   the data source. This type indicates which database engine the data
--   source connects to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorInfo:DataSource'</a>, <a>dataSource_errorInfo</a> - Error
--   information from the last update or the creation of the data source.
newDataSource :: DataSource

-- | A <i>logical table</i> is a unit that joins and that data
--   transformations operate on. A logical table has a source, which can be
--   either a physical table or result of a join. When a logical table
--   points to a physical table, the logical table acts as a mutable copy
--   of that physical table through transform operations.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newLogicalTable</a> smart constructor.
data LogicalTable
LogicalTable' :: Maybe (NonEmpty TransformOperation) -> Text -> LogicalTableSource -> LogicalTable

-- | Create a value of <a>LogicalTable</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataTransforms:LogicalTable'</a>,
--   <a>logicalTable_dataTransforms</a> - Transform operations that act on
--   this logical table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:alias:LogicalTable'</a>, <a>logicalTable_alias</a> - A display
--   name for the logical table.
--   
--   <a>$sel:source:LogicalTable'</a>, <a>logicalTable_source</a> - Source
--   of this logical table.
newLogicalTable :: Text -> LogicalTableSource -> LogicalTable

-- | Information about the source of a logical table. This is a variant
--   type structure. For this structure to be valid, only one of the
--   attributes can be non-null.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newLogicalTableSource</a> smart constructor.
data LogicalTableSource
LogicalTableSource' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe JoinInstruction -> Maybe Text -> LogicalTableSource

-- | Create a value of <a>LogicalTableSource</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding

-- | Information about a dataset that contains permissions for row-level
--   security (RLS). The permissions dataset maps fields to users or
--   groups. For more information, see <a>Using Row-Level Security (RLS) to
--   Restrict Access to a Dataset</a> in the <i>Amazon QuickSight User
--   Guide</i>.
--   
--   The option to deny permissions by setting <tt>PermissionPolicy</tt> to
--   <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is not supported for new RLS datasets.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> smart constructor.
data RowLevelPermissionDataSet
RowLevelPermissionDataSet' :: Maybe Status -> Maybe Text -> Maybe RowLevelPermissionFormatVersion -> Text -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy -> RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | Create a value of <a>RowLevelPermissionDataSet</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_status</a> - The status of the row-level
--   security permission dataset. If enabled, the status is
--   <tt>ENABLED</tt>. If disabled, the status is <tt>DISABLED</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:namespace:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_namespace</a> - The namespace associated
--   with the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   <a>$sel:formatVersion:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_formatVersion</a> - The user or group
--   rules associated with the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   By default, <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>. When
--   <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is <tt>VERSION_1</tt>, <tt>UserName</tt> and
--   <tt>GroupName</tt> are required. When <tt>FormatVersion</tt> is
--   <tt>VERSION_2</tt>, <tt>UserARN</tt> and <tt>GroupARN</tt> are
--   required, and <tt>Namespace</tt> must not exist.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name (ARN)
--   of the dataset that contains permissions for RLS.
--   
--   <a>$sel:permissionPolicy:RowLevelPermissionDataSet'</a>,
--   <a>rowLevelPermissionDataSet_permissionPolicy</a> - The type of
--   permissions to use when interpreting the permissions for RLS.
--   <tt>DENY_ACCESS</tt> is included for backward compatibility only.
newRowLevelPermissionDataSet :: Text -> RowLevelPermissionPolicy -> RowLevelPermissionDataSet

-- | A template object. A <i>template</i> is an entity in Amazon QuickSight
--   that encapsulates the metadata required to create an analysis and that
--   you can use to create a dashboard. A template adds a layer of
--   abstraction by using placeholders to replace the dataset associated
--   with an analysis. You can use templates to create dashboards by
--   replacing dataset placeholders with datasets that follow the same
--   schema that was used to create the source analysis and template.
--   
--   You can share templates across Amazon Web Services accounts by
--   allowing users in other Amazon Web Services accounts to create a
--   template or a dashboard from an existing template.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTemplate</a> smart constructor.
data Template

--   - Time when this was last updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:Template'</a>, <a>template_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource
--   Name (ARN) of the template.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdTime:Template'</a>, <a>template_createdTime</a> - Time
--   when this was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:templateId:Template'</a>, <a>template_templateId</a> - The ID
--   for the template. This is unique per Amazon Web Services Region for
--   each Amazon Web Services account.

--   <a>uploadSettings_startFromRow</a> - A row number to start reading
--   data from.
--   
--   <a>$sel:containsHeader:UploadSettings'</a>,
--   <a>uploadSettings_containsHeader</a> - Whether the file has a header
--   row, or the files each have a header row.
--   
--   <a>$sel:textQualifier:UploadSettings'</a>,
--   <a>uploadSettings_textQualifier</a> - Text qualifier.
--   
--   <a>$sel:format:UploadSettings'</a>, <a>uploadSettings_format</a> -
--   File format.
--   
--   <a>$sel:delimiter:UploadSettings'</a>, <a>uploadSettings_delimiter</a>
--   - The delimiter between values in the file.
newUploadSettings :: UploadSettings

-- | A registered user of Amazon QuickSight.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUser</a> smart constructor.
data User
User' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe IdentityType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe UserRole -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> User

-- | Create a value of <a>User</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:email:User'</a>, <a>user_email</a> - The user's email address.
--   
--   <a>$sel:principalId:User'</a>, <a>user_principalId</a> - The principal
--   ID of the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:User'</a>, <a>user_arn</a> - The Amazon Resource Name
--   (ARN) for the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:userName:User'</a>, <a>user_userName</a> - The user's user
--   name.
--   
--   <a>$sel:identityType:User'</a>, <a>user_identityType</a> - The type of
--   identity authentication used by the user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderUrl:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_externalLoginFederationProviderUrl</a> - The URL of the
--   external login provider.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customPermissionsName:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_customPermissionsName</a> - The custom permissions profile
--   associated with this user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:active:User'</a>, <a>user_active</a> - The active status of
--   user. When you create an Amazon QuickSight user thats not an IAM user
--   or an Active Directory user, that user is inactive until they sign in
--   and provide a password.
--   
--   <a>$sel:role':User'</a>, <a>user_role</a> - The Amazon QuickSight role
--   for the user. The user role can be one of the following:.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>READER</tt>: A user who has read-only access to
--   dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>AUTHOR</tt>: A user who can create data sources, datasets,
--   analyses, and dashboards.</li>
--   <li><tt>ADMIN</tt>: A user who is an author, who can also manage
--   Amazon Amazon QuickSight settings.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_READER</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   <li><tt>RESTRICTED_AUTHOR</tt>: This role isn't currently available
--   for use.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginFederationProviderType:User'</a>,
--   <a>user_externalLoginFederationProviderType</a> - The type of
--   supported external login provider that provides identity to let the
--   user federate into Amazon QuickSight with an associated IAMrole. The
--   type can be one of the following.
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><tt>COGNITO</tt>: Amazon Cognito. The provider URL is
--   cognito-identity.amazonaws.com.</li>
--   <li><tt>CUSTOM_OIDC</tt>: Custom OpenID Connect (OIDC) provider.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:externalLoginId:User'</a>, <a>user_externalLoginId</a> - The
--   identity ID for the user in the external login provider.
newUser :: User
